title: tangy green beans
directions: Combine
green beans and water in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil;
cover,
reduce heat and simmer 8 minutes.
Fry bacon and onion
in
a
heavy skillet until bacon is crisp.
Remove mixture with a slotted spoon;
drain and set aside.
Pour off drippings from skillet.
Combine vinegar and sugar in skillet and
bring to a boil.
Add beans and bacon mixture.
Cook over medium heat until thoroughly heated.
Serves 3.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Add warm beer slowly.
Mixture will be tacky.
Put into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Brush the top with oleo after baking.
Mix remaining ingredients together and spread on top of warm bread.

title: make ahead casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into casserole which has been greased. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This may be made up to 24 hours ahead, placed into the refrigerator and then baked.

title: roasted pecan clusters
directions: Melt butter in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan.
Spread pecans evenly in pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes stirring every 10 minutes.
Place candy coating in top of double broiler, bring water to boil.
Reduce heat to low, and cook until coating melts.
Cool 2 minutes; add pecans and stir until coated.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let cool completely.
Yields about 4 dozen.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Filling:
In skillet combine first 15 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover tightly and simmer for 15 minutes. Uncover and cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from skillet.
Set aside.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, 3 tablespoons of sugar and melted margarine together and press in dish.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: georgia peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Combine flour, baking powder and sugar in a bowl. Stir in milk and mix thoroughly.
Pour flour mixture over melted butter and add peaches. Stir one time. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until crust is puffed and browned. Serve warm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: macaroni and beef
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan over medium heat, cook beef and onion until beef is browned and onion is tender, stirring to separate meat.
Drain off fat.
Stir in soup.
Add remaining ingredients. Heat through, stirring often.

title: see's candy
directions: In a large bowl combine chocolate bits, Marshmallow Creme, oleo, nuts and vanilla.
Set aside.
In heavy pan, combine sugar, salt and Pet milk.
Cook, stirring, until a full rolling boil begins; boil another 6 or 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour over other ingredients and mix together.
Store in refrigerator.

title: christmas coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine biscuit mix with sugar, cinnamon and allspice.
Beat banana, egg and vanilla into mixture, blending well.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 9-inch square pan.
Spoon cranberry sauce evenly over batter.
Combine brown sugar, flour and pecans. Blend in butter.
Sprinkle over cranberry sauce.
Bake for 25 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: not impossible impossible pie
directions: Add all ingredients together in a blender.
Blend.
Pour into 9-inch pie pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Put pie filling in dish.
Place enough thick loaf bread with crust cut to cover top of pie.
Melt margarine.
Add sugar, flour and egg.
Stir.
Pour this over bread.
Let stand 10 or 15 minutes.
Bake in a 350° oven until golden brown.

title: lasagne
directions: Bring milk and broth to boil.
Melt butter in medium saucepan over medium heat.
Add onions; cook until transparent.
Stir in flour; cook 2 minutes.
Whisk in hot milk mixture, thyme, salt and spices; boil 2 minutes, stirring.
Stir 2 cups sauce into spinach and greens.

title: squash relish
directions: Chop vegetables; cover with ice water, mixed with 1/2 cup salt.
Let stand 1 hour.
Drain and rinse, then drain again.
Pour boiled mixture over vegetables.
Put on low heat 10 to 15 minutes. Get hot, but do not boil, the last 4 ingredients.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: chicken salad
directions: Pressure cook chicken (skinned) until done, about 7 minutes. Cool, debone and cut into 1-inch chunks.
To chicken, add apple, grapes, celery and pecans or walnut pieces.
Mix thoroughly after each addition.
Use creamy Italian dressing, as much as necessary. Serve on bed of lettuce, garnish plate with small cluster of grapes with carrot sticks.
Serve with tossed salad.
Serves 4.

title: pineapple quick dessert
directions: Pour pineapple into a baking dish and cake mix (dry, as it comes from the box).
Cut
up
margarine
on
top.
Bake at 350° until brown and the cake mix is crusty.

title: chafing dish fruit
directions: Drain fruit.
Combine 2/3 cup syrup of each of the fruits in a saucepan.
Add orange juice and grated rinds; simmer uncovered until reduced by half.
If too sweet, stir in the juice and 1/2 lemon.
Transfer to top of double boiler.
Add drained fruit and dates and cook for about 15 minutes.
An electric frying pan can be used for the dish.
When ready to serve, transfer to chafing dish and serve hot.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: crabmeat roll
directions: Mix tomato juice and egg.
Add crumbs, parsley, celery and crabmeat.
Mix well.
Roll into finger lengths.
Wrap each with 1/2 strip bacon.
Broil, turning to brown evenly.
Makes 2 dozen rolls.
Fry in an electric frying pan, pouring off grease as it accumulates.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Mix water, soda and cocoa together and let stand.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and milk. Add vanilla, water, soda and cocoa mixture.
Let stand 1 minute. Add salt.
Bake in 3-inch pans for thick layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool before frosting with white or chocolate icing.

title: quick cinnamon fluff
directions: Cream the butter, sugar, egg and vanilla until light.
Sift dry ingredients. Combine all ingredients, including milk and mix until creamy.
Pour into a 9-inch square pan.
Dot the top with butter.
Generously sprinkle brown sugar and cinnamon on top and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: leek, potato and sausage soup
directions: In a dry, heavy saucepan, toast the cumin seed and the caraway seed over moderate heat, stirring for 2 to 3 minutes or until they are fragrant and transfer them to a plate.

In the pan, cook the leek in the butter, stirring occasionally for 5 minutes or until it is very soft; stir in the broth and the potato, peeled and cut into 1/2-inch dice and bring the liquid to a boil.
Simmer the mixture for 10 minutes or until the potato is tender; stir in the toasted seeds, the kielbasa, the cream and salt and pepper to taste and simmer the soup for 5 minutes.
Just before serving, stir in the spinach.
Serves 2.

title: baked rice
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, covered.
Remove cover and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: creamy coleslaw
directions: Fill blender container to top-cup marking with vegetables.
Add cold water just to cover vegetables.
Cover container; run just long enough to chop vegetables, about 3 to 4 seconds.
Pour mixture into strainer; drain thoroughly.
Repeat with remaining vegetables.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, lemon juice, salt, mustard and pepper.
Pour over chopped cabbage and green pepper; mix.

title: rocky road brownies
directions: Heat 1/2 cup of the chocolate chips and the butter over low heat until melted; cool.
Heat oven to 375°.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, vanilla, salt, eggs and chocolate mixture.
Spread in ungreased square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inch.
Bake 15 minutes. Sprinkle with marshmallows, nuts and remaining chocolate chips. Bake until marshmallows are golden brown and wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool completely; cut into 2 x 1-inch bars.
Makes 36 brownies.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Stir the ingredients together in a casserole dish and bake at 350° until bubbles or is hot.
Serve as an appetizer with Wheat Thins crackers.

title: claudia's cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, baking soda and salt until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, to the mixture and whip until fluffy.
Add flavor.
Scrape sides of bowl.
Add flour just to bring together. This is a soft dough but not sticky.
Scoop on lightly greased pans.
Press down with sugar bowl dipped in sugar.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: squash fritters
directions: Combine squash, onion, pepper, sugar, salt and flour.
Beat eggs and add to squash.
Add margarine.
Drop by tablespoons onto oiled griddle.
Cook until delicate brown.
Turn and brown other side.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pleasing potato casserole
directions: Mix together.
Put in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill. Dip with vegetables or corn chips or cut cocktail tomatoes in halves and scoop out centers. Drain on paper towels. Spoon spinach mixture into each half and serve as hors d'oeuvres.

title: beefy cheese ball
directions: In mixing bowl, combine Cheddar cheese and cream cheese, chopped sandwich meat, chopped green onions, dash of Accent, salt and 1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well by hand and form into ball.
Serve with crackers.

title: nick's turkey burgers
directions: Make just as you would a hamburger and place a pineapple ring on top in place of cheese.

title: karen fremuth's cider glazed fowl with fruit and nut stuffing(for pheasant, quail, grouse, duck or goose)
directions: Combine cider and cinnamon and boil down to about 1 cup. Remove cinnamon stick.
Stir in remaining ingredients and boil down to a thick syrup.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Chill canned milk for several hours.
Mix jello, hot water and salt.
Chill until half set; then beat until light and fluffy. Add lemon juice and sugar.
Beat cream until thick and add to the lemon mixture.
Crush wafers and cover the bottom of a 9 x 12 x 2-inch dish using only half of crumbs.
Pour in the mixture and cover with remaining crumbs.
Chill overnight or at least several hours, until set.
Will serve 12.

title: spanish sausage supper
directions: In a large skillet saute peppers, celery and onions in oil until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is almost absorbed, stirring occasionally.
Serves 4.
Serve with cornbread.

title: cherry or blueberry cheese pie
directions: In large bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in Eagle Brand until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour in crust and chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with pie filling before serving.

title: brazilian rice
directions: Saute rice, garlic and mushrooms in oil until rice begins to brown.
Stir in hot water and onion soup.
Add tomatoes, salt and oregano.
Pour into casserole. Cover and bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in egg.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Fold in blueberries. Grease and flour an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry yogurt dip
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Serve as a dip with fresh fruit.

title: chinese won ton cookies
directions: Mix sugar, raisins and coconut in large bowl.
Place a scant teaspoon in each won ton skin.
Moisten edges, fold into triangle and deep fry for 2 to 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain thoroughly on paper towels.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 250!

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into loaf.
Bake in a shallow bowl or pan at 350° for about 1 1/4 hours.

title: pork roast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle roast with salt, pepper and cinnamon; rub into meat.
Place roast on rack in baking pan, fat side up.
Bake about 3 to 3 1/2 hours (allow 25 minutes per pound).
Place pears and sweet potatoes around meat; continue baking.
Spoon off fat.

title: crab mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Heat gelatin, soup and cream cheese until melted.
Use a wire whip to cream it.
Remove from heat and add all other ingredients.
Pour into mold and chill. Unmold and serve with crackers.
Makes one large mold or two small.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of shrimp soup

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Put first 8 ingredients in a large bowl; mix thoroughly.
Heat 2 tablespoons of fat in skillet.
Form mixture into 1-inch balls and drop into skillet, a few at a time, and brown on all sides. Remove and keep in warm place.
Continue until all meat balls are browned.
Add fat as needed.
Add hot water to the drippings in skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Blend flour with cold water.
Stir into water in skillet and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Return meat to skillet and simmer on low heat 30 minutes.
Serve over rice, mashed potatoes or noodles.
Serves 6.

title: penne alla napolitana
directions: Cook mostaccioli for 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain; toss with one tablespoon olive oil.
Return to pan and keep warm.
Saute garlic slowly in three tablespoons of olive oil until softened but not browned.
Add olives, basil, red pepper and tomato sauce.
Heat; stir in cheeses and heat, stirring until chunks begin to melt. Pour over mostaccioli.

title: wild rice salad
directions: Cook and cool rice and peas (separately) and mix with tomato, pepper, scallions and artichokes.
Add almonds
and mix with the dressing.
Let set for several hours before serving.

title: apple torte(from 1975 edition)
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add flour, baking powder and salt, sifted together.
Add apples (sliced), then add lemon juice and nuts.
Bake in buttered 6 x 9 1/2-inch dish for 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve hot or cold with whipped cream, ice cream or hard sauce.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix in mixer until blended (it will be lumpy).
Pour in long pan and freeze.
Take out 15 minutes prior to serving.
Cut in blocks and serve.

title: microwave salmon loaf
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Combine all ingredients and cover dish.
Microwave on High for 15 minutes.

title: "more"
directions: Cook and rinse noodles.
Season and brown meat with onion. Drain meat and canned vegetables.
Add together ingredients; simmer and season with soy sauce to taste.

title: shrimp dill dip
directions: Gradually blend, sour cream, miracle whip and cream cheese, beat until smooth.
Add lemon juice, mix well with a fork.
Add garlic, salt, dill and tabasco sauce, mix well.
Add horseradish. Pat shrimp dry with paper towel.
Cut shrimp (large ones) in about 4-5 pieces.
Mix lightly with ingredients.
Adjust seasonings to taste.
Serve with shredded wheat crackers, chips or corn chips. Tastes best the second day after made.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: chinese five spice split pea soup
directions: During cooking time for standard pea soup, add the first 5 ingredients.
Stir frequently.
Near end of cooking time, add large pinch of Chinese Five Spice powder and stir.
Add salt to taste if necessary. Serve with French bread.

title: parmesan vegetable toss salad
directions: Cut up broccoli, cauliflower and sliced onion; place in large bowl.
Combine mayonnaise, sugar and Parmesan cheese together; pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate for 3 to 4 hours or overnight. Add lettuce, water chestnuts, bacon bits and croutons just before serving.
You may put cashew nuts, if desired.
Very good even after refrigerated for a few days, if some left over.

title: ham and cheese pinwheels
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with seasonings.
Spread on ham slices and roll up.
Fix with a toothpick.
Refrigerate overnight. Before serving, slice in bite size pieces and top each with a slice of stuffed olive.

title: easy cinnamon rolls
directions: Cut shortening into flour with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add 1 cup milk, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a floured surface; knead lightly.

title: baked squash
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Drain and mash with butter, salt and pepper.
Add slightly beaten egg, bread and onion.
Mix all well.
Pour 1/2 mixture in casserole.
Then add cheese to top. Add remaining mixture and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Mix all at least 2 hours before serving and refrigerate.

title: tater tots tuna casserole
directions: Saute onion, celery, green peppers, butter and salt, then add pepper and tuna; break up pieces of tuna.
Combine mayo, milk and Worcestershire; stir into mixture.
Spread in a shallow baking dish.
Place Tater Tots on top of tuna.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: rick's easy spread
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: christmas nut thins
directions: Blend sugar and butter together.
Add well beaten eggs.
Sift in flour and salt.
Add nuts; add vanilla and mix until smooth and light.
Drop onto greased baking sheet, spaced well apart.
Place half a pecan in center of each cookie.
Bake at 375° about 10 minutes.

title: micro-scalloped potatoes
directions: Spray casserole dish, layer sliced potatoes and cheese.
Add minced onions in milk and pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Cover and vent.
Cook on High 10 to 12 minutes, rotate dish 3 times.
Broil to brown.

title: granny's sweet potato pie
directions: Mix potatoes, margarine and sugar.
Beat.
Add flour and eggs. Beat.
Add milk and nutmeg.
Beat.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Cook at 350° until done.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare chicken breasts (cut in half).
Cook the broccoli for 5 minutes; drain.
Mix soup, salad dressing, lemon juice and curry powder.
Place the broccoli on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cube the chicken over it.
Pour the soup mixture over the chicken. Sprinkle with the bread crumbs, mixed with the butter.
Bake until browned, about 40 to 45 minutes, in 350° oven.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles as directed and drain.
In a large skillet, cook and stir onion in margarine until tender. Stir in 2 cans soup, pimentos, salt and pepper.

title: butter cookies
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Add flour and soda.
Roll in balls the size of pecan, then press on pan with 2 fingers.
Bake at 300° for 8 to 10 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: pepper cookies
directions: Heat oil and wine together on medium heat. Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Roll out in strips about the size of your thumb. Cut in 4-inch lengths. Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 400° on an ungreased baking sheet.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and green pepper.
Drain fat and turn into a 2 1/2-quart crock-pot.
Add vinegar, sugar, chili powder and tomatoes.
This will fill a 2 1/2-quart cooker.
Cover and cook on high until it bubbles, then turn to low and simmer at least 4 to 4 1/2 hours, or all day.

title: hunter's stew
directions: Brown venison and sausage in hot oil in a large Dutch oven. Add onion and celery. Cook until tender. Add remaining ingredients, except carrots and potatoes.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Add carrots.
Cook, uncovered, 30 minutes. Add potatoes and cook an additional 30 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer ingredients in a large glass bowl as listed.

title: butter pecan candy
directions: Roast chopped pecans in butter at 250° for 15 minutes.
Melt cream cheese in top of double boiler.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Mix well; add nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper. Let dry on one side, then turn each and let dry on other side. Store in covered container.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Place in a greased casserole and top with crushed cornflakes (2 cups).
Drizzle with 1/4 cup melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: 15 bean soup
directions: Wash beans thoroughly.
Place beans in a pan; cover with water and 2 tablespoons salt.
Soak overnight.
In the morning; drain, add 2 quarts of water.
Add ham bone and bring to a boil.
Simmer slowly 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Remove ham bone.
Add onion, tomatoes, chili powder, garlic, ham, carrot, celery, salt and pepper. Simmer until vegetables are done.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into loaf pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pineapple	in
cake pan, then add cherry pie filling; sprinkle cake mix on top, then sprinkle brown sugar over all.
Cut up 2 sticks of butter on top of cake mix.
Make sure all the cake mix is wet.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: caramel pie
directions: Mix 1/4 cup sugar, flour and milk. Cook until thick. Add well beaten eggs. Beat together and set aside. Put 1 cup sugar in iron skillet and cook until melted. Put other mixture into melted sugar and cook until creamy. Add butter and vanilla.

title: pizza dip
directions: Spread the cream cheese into the bottom of a rectangle cake pan or a pan of similar size. If the cheese is hard to spread, you can microwave it in a covered bowl for 1 minute and check to see if it is soft enough. If not, then microwave for 30 seconds more and check again. Keep repeating until it is soft enough to spread. Layer pizza sauce on top of cream cheese. Sprinkle with pepperoni and Mozzarella cheese. You can also add any other toppings you like on pizza, such as sausage (cooked already), onions, mushrooms, black olives or green peppers. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and bubbly. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Reserve 2/3 for topping.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Cook hamburger meat and onion until done; drain fat.
Add soup, sauce, milk and chilies.
Mix well.
Add diced cheese to mixture.
In large 9 x 13-inch greased casserole dish, put one layer of tortillas (quartered).
Add part of meat mixture and alternate with tortillas until all of mixture is used.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until bubbly.
Do not add salt.
Serve with a salad.
(Three casserole dishes, each approximately 6 x 9-inches, may be used.
Two may be frozen before baking for later use.
If frozen, thaw to room temperature before baking.)

title: perfect corn bread
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients together; stir in corn meal. Mix eggs, milk and shortening together in a separate bowl, then place with the dry ingredients. Mix just until smooth, not too long; can be a little lumpy. Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan or small iron skillet. Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: new york champagne punch
directions: Using sharp knife, cut top to bottom from pineapple.
Carefully cut and peel pineapple.
Cut pineapple in half and core.
Chop half of the pineapple into tidbit sizes.
Using a coarse grater, shred remaining pineapple, reserving any juice.
Halve any large strawberries.
Set fruit aside.
In large punch bowl, stir lemon and orange juice, sugar and curacao until sugar is dissolved.
Stir in champagne, white wine, club soda and ice ring (if you made one, pineapple, pineapple juice and strawberries).

title: fruit and nuts cake
directions: Heat milk and marshmallows until marshmallows melt.
Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
May be pressed in butter molds or made into small balls. Chill in refrigerator.

title: english muffins with seafood and cheese
directions: Soften the butter in a small bowl with an electric mixer or wooden spoon.
Mix in the cheese, seafood and seasonings.
Spread the mixture on halved muffins.
Place them on a cookie sheet; broil until bubbly.

title: frozen strawberry jam
directions: Mix berries and pectin; dissolve and let stand 30 minutes. Add sugar and Karo and stir until dissolved.
Put in containers and freeze.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding.
Add Cool Whip, marshmallows and nuts.

title: chocolate cracker candy
directions: Line cookie pan with foil.
Place crackers side by side on bottom of pan.
Boil sugar and butter for 5 minutes and pour over crackers, smoothing with back of spoon.
Bake in preheated oven for 5 minutes.
(There should be bubbles all over.)
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips all over the top.
Wait 3 minutes and spread chocolate with back of spoon.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Combine sausage, onion and green pepper in skillet; cook until sausage is brown.
Drain well and set aside.
Combine water, soup and salt in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Add rice; cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 7 minutes.
Put in casserole; cover and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: cornish hens and rice
directions: This is prepared in a crock-pot.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients; form into a ball.
Roll in nuts, if desired.
Chill.
Serve with an assortment of crackers.

title: bread pudding
directions: Place cubed bread in 9 x 13-inch baking dish; mix in a bowl melted butter, eggs, milk, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and sugar.
Blend well.
Pour over bread; sprinkle raisins over and bake at 350° until firm, about 50 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes. Mix all ingredients together. Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Add crushed corn flakes and 1/4 cup butter to top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: christmas punch
directions: Boil sugar and water together for 5 minutes; cool.
In punch bowl, stir sugar syrup with cranberry juice and pineapple juice. Add thawed lemonade and number of cans of water as stated on can. Stir in lime juice.
Add ice or ice mold.

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Combine dressing mix and oil; add dill, garlic and lemon pepper. Pour over crackers; stir to coat. Place in warm oven for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Bring milk, cocoa, sugar and margarine to a boil.
Cook 2 1/2 to 3 minutes.
Add vanilla; remove from heat and add oatmeal and pecans.
Mix well and quickly.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper to cool.

title: spanish rice
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add rice, onion and green pepper.
Cook and stir until mixture is lightly browned.
Add remaining ingredients.
Quickly bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix all ingredients together except frankfurters.
Dip frankfurters into batter.
Fry in deep hot fat about 4 minutes or until brown.
Turn and cook until a golden brown.

title: turtles
directions: Melt package of caramel candies and milk in double boiler. Add 2 cups pecans.
Drop by teaspoonful on well buttered wax paper.
Melt chocolate almond bark.
Dip candy in chocolate by toothpick.

title: meat sauce for hot dogs
directions: Saute onion in oil 2 minutes.
Add beef; cook until browned, breaking up.
Add tomato sauce, chili powder, salt and pepper. Cover; simmer 30 minutes.
Uncover for the last 5 minutes of cooking.
Serve on hot dogs with mustard and chopped onions.
This can be frozen.

title: jello with applesauce
directions: Combine cinnamon drops in hot water.
Stir until dissolved., Add celery for salad.

title: cottage pie(english dish)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown onion and meat in oil.
Stir in flour; cook for 2 minutes.
Add stock and simmer for 5 minutes. Add rest of the ingredients.
Season.
Put mixture into a baking dish and cover with mashed potatoes, marking their surface with a fork.
Cook for 45 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into a loaf in a shallow baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Allow meat loaf to stand five minutes before slicing.
Makes 6 servings.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix thoroughly. Store in plastic container.
Use 1/3 cup of mix to each cup. Fill cup with hot water.

title: banana fritters
directions: In a large bowl mix flour, sugar, cinnamon and baking powder. In another bowl beat together eggs, milk, mashed banana and vanilla.
Stir liquid ingredients all at once into flour mixture, stirring until smooth.
Let batter rest 30 minutes.
Pour oil into a large saucepan to half full and heat over medium heat to 350°. Drop batter by tablespoon into hot oil.
Cook 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Repeat with remaining batter.
Keep warm in a 250° oven.
To serve, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix mayonnaise and sugar well. Add cocoa, vanilla, water, baking soda and salt. Mix together. Stir in flour and mix well. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Melt oleo over medium heat.
Add sugar, cocoa, salt and milk. Bring to boil stirring often.
Cook exactly 1 minute.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oats, stirring well.
Quickly drop by tablespoon on waxed paper.

title: blushin' russian
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Yields 1-1/2 cups of dressing.

title: applesauce rhubarb muffins
directions: Stir flours, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda and salt together.
Make well in center and set aside.
In medium bowl, beat eggs and stir in brown sugar, applesauce and oil.
Add egg mixture to well in flour mixture.
Stir until moistened.
Fold in rhubarb. Fill 2/3 full in muffin pan.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: turkey salad in melon shells
directions: Place diced turkey in bowl with celery and green pepper. Season with salt.
Blend in mayonnaise, lemon juice and chutney. Chill.

title: party mints
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and just enough milk to mix well.
Roll out, cut and dry.

title: english trifle
directions: Make pudding ahead and chill.
Chunk pound cake and layer in large compote with pudding and fruit.
Top with Cool Whip; refrigerate overnight.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice as directed on package.
Combine all other ingredients.
Slightly beat eggs before adding to other ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with milk or cream.

title: cabbage and jello salad
directions: Grate cabbage, carrots and diced celery.
Mix together.
Place in individual molds filling halfway.
Pour Jell-O over this.
The Jell-O should be seasoned with vinegar, salt and pepper per double pack.
Chill and serve on lettuce.

title: raisin bread or sweet rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast, salt, sugar and dried milk in water.
Add melted margarine and 3 cups flour; mix.
Add raisins and mix again. Add flour to knead.
Knead.
Let rise until doubled (covered). Knead down.
Shape into loaves; let rise again.
Bake 40 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 large loaves.

title: banana slush punch
directions: Mix water and sugar in large container until sugar dissolves (overnight if need be).
Add frozen lemonade and orange juice. Add pineapple juice.
Put bananas through blender.
Mix all these ingredients together and freeze.
Remove from freezer; mash with potato masher to slush up.
Add cold 7-Up (or Bubble-Up), 1 bottle, or up to 5 bottles if needed.

title: great aunt bess' easy rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add all other ingredients but flour. Stir.
Add enough flour to make dough stiff enough to handle. Roll out, cut with biscuit cutter, brush with melted butter and fold over like pocketbook rolls.
Brush again with butter.
Let rise in a warm place.
Bake at 425° until done.
Preparation Time: 2 hours.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Arrange rhubarb in a greased 8 x
8-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with the sugar mixed with 2 tablespoons flour.
Set aside.
Blend oats, brown sugar, flour and butter.
Use as a topping for the prepared rhubarb.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes. Serve warm or cold with cream or whipped topping.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place raw rice in roaster; sprinkle onion soup over rice. Place pieces of chicken, skin side up, over rice.
Mix soups and water.
Pour over chicken and bake, uncovered, for 2 hours at 350°.

title: one pot minestrone
directions: Combine all ingredients (except Parmesan cheese and pasta shells) in a huge pot and let simmer on low heat for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes and carrots are tender.
Cook pasta shells separately and add to soup for about the last few minutes of cooking time.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread on bread.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put over sweetened berries or fruit.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 30 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix well and put in baking pan.
Cover with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: southern corn bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Beat egg and milk. Beat in dry ingredients, then melted shortening.
Pour into greased 8-inch pan. Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes until brown.

title: ham and cheese bake
directions: Arrange lightly
toasted bread in buttered baking dish; trim to fit.
Sprinkle
ham and cheese over toast layer.
In a bowl mix eggs
with	milk
or
half	and
half, salt, mustard, pepper and nutmeg.
Pour
the	egg mixture slowly over the ham and cheese layer.
Bake
at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown and eggs are stiff.
Serves 4.

title: swiss cheese quiche
directions: Cook.
Drain bacon.
Crush.
Sprinkle bacon, ham and onion over crust; add cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper together.
Pour into crust.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until knife in center comes out clean.

title: zucchini crumb pie(tastes like apple pie)
directions: Cook zucchini in lemon juice with sugar and raisins.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Add crust mix, cinnamon and nutmeg to thicken. cool.

title: old-fashioned chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and butter together.
Then add eggs; add meal, milk, vinegar and flavor.
Cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Put in greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Cover with corn flake crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: caramel sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients, except water.
Stir over heat until mixture is thick and turns rich caramel color.
When mixture leaves sides of pan, remove pan from heat; add hot water, a little at a time.
Return to heat; simmer 2 to 3 minutes; let cool.
Serve with ice cream, pancakes or cake.

title: beef or chicken parmigiana
directions: Melt oleo or butter in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Place your cutlets in baking dish.
Bake in hot oven at 375° for 15 minutes. Turn meat and continue baking 15 minutes or until tender.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt, flour and cocoa; stir in egg yolks.
Add milk and cook until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
Turn into cooked pie shell and top with meringue made with reserved egg whites.

title: chicken a la chardon
directions: Beat eggs with salt and pepper to taste and 2 teaspoons garlic powder; set aside.
Combine bread crumbs, 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder and Parmesan cheese.
Dip each chicken piece in egg mixture, then roll in crumb mixture.
Arrange chicken pieces in a single layer in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs together.
In a separate bowl, make a paste of food coloring and cocoa.
Add to the first mixture.
Add vanilla to buttermilk, salt and flour.
Add this to the first mixture.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Add vinegar and soda; stir gently.
Bake in 2 layer pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli as directed on box.
Saute onion in oleo. Warm soup and Cheez Whiz.
Mix all together, including the cooked rice.
Bake at 300° for about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: caramel pecan pie
directions: Cream butter, flour and sugar until smooth.
Beat egg.
Add milk, then stir into creamed mixture.
Cook in top of double boiler until thickened, stirring constantly.
Cool, then add vanilla and pecans, lightly toasted.
(Microwave works well for this.)
Pour into pastry shell and chill.
Top with Cool Whip just prior to serving.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (except crackers and butter) and put in a baking dish.
Top with Ritz crackers (about 18).
Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: 3 bean casserole
directions: Brown ground meat and drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook in crock-pot on low for 3 to 4 hours.

title: mexican pecan candy
directions: Mix sugar, milk and soda.
Cook to form a soft ball.
Add butter, vanilla and nuts.
Cream and drop on waxed paper. Sprinkle with salt.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add; mix well.
Fold in remaining ingredients. Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350° in a greased and floured tube pan.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, baking powder and salt.
Add milk, beaten eggs, oil, creamed corn, chilies and 1 1/2 cups of cheese.
Put in buttered 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375°, uncovered, for 45 minutes or until done.

title: hamburger potato dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add soup and water, potatoes and seasoning.
Bake in casserole or cook in skillet, stirring occasionally.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until potatoes are done.

title: cracker cookies
directions: Line crackers on foil-lined cookie sheet.
Have crackers touch each other.
Melt margarine and sugar.
Pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes until it bubbles up well.
Spread chocolate chips over crackers and bake 3 to 4 minutes.
Spread chips over crackers.
Press in nuts.
Cool some and cut while still warm. Cool in refrigerator.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: norwegian pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and unbeaten egg. Mix until well blended. Add vanilla; mix and stir in nuts and apples. Pour into greased pie dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: basic pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, mixing well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flour, stirring in a small amount at a time. Pour into greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan (can use a tube pan). Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix and chill until firm.
Roll into small balls and chill again.
Melt 1 large package chocolate chips and 1/2 block of shaved paraffin in double boiler.
Dip balls into chocolate mixture and put on wax paper to dry.

title: ham loaf
directions: In a 9 x 5-inch pan, combine the butter and brown sugar. Drain the pineapple, reserving 1/4 cup of the juice.
Spread pineapple over butter and brown sugar.
Combine remaining ingredients, including pineapple juice.
Mix well.
Press into loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Invert to serve.

title: blueberry waffles
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Stir in yolks, milk and butter.
Fold in whites.
Loosely add blueberries.
Bake in a hot waffle iron. I double the recipe and freeze the extras to toast on a hurried morning.

title: stuffed tuna bread
directions: Cut ends from bread. Cut loaf in half and hollow out.
Mix all ingredients including bread you hollowed out. Spoon mixture onto bread halves. Reassemble bread. Wrap and refrigerate 2 hours or overnight.
To serve, cut into slices.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add drained pineapple.
Put in oblong dish.
Cover with marshmallows.
Let jell.

title: spice cake
directions: Sift flour with spices, salt, baking powder and soda.
(You can use a whisk.)
Cream shortening and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, beating well after each addition.
Add flour mixture alternately with thick sour milk to creamed butter and sugar mixture.
Beat thoroughly.
Bake in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 to 50 minutes in a 350° oven.
Let cake stand in pan while preparing icing.
Broiled Coconut Icing on this is very good.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Heat oven
to
Grease pan.
Sift flour; add salt to potatoes.
Add shortening; mix milk in gradually.
Roll out dough and
cut
with biscuit cutter or shape with hands.	Bake 15 minutes or until brown.
Butter at once.
Serve hot.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown and drain beef and sausage.
Make meat sauce in large saucepan with tomato sauce, tomatoes, tomato paste, basil, oregano, garlic, lemon juice, sugar, salt, pepper, beef and sausage.
Simmer over low heat, uncovered, for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spicy hawaiian punch
directions: Melt red hots in pineapple juice.
Add grapefruit juice mix; then add the chilled ginger ale.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Beat until creamy the butter, sugar and egg yolks.
Fold in Cool Whip along with chopped candy bars.
Break cake in pieces. Put half in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour half of the Cool Whip mixture over this and put rest of cake in pan.
Top with remaining Cool Whip mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: corn relish
directions: In a large kettle, combine all the ingredients and bring slowly to a boil.
Simmer for 20 minutes and pack boiling hot into hot jars.
Seal at once.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Mix flour and cheese.
Add Rice Krispies and margarine.
Mix well with hands.
Roll marble size balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes about 235 small puffs.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers (do not peel).
Slice cucumbers.
Add onions, green peppers, garlic and pickling salt.
Cover mixture with crushed ice.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain well.

title: pickled squash
directions: In a large bowl (not metal), mix sliced squash and salt and set aside for 1 hour.
Mix all seasoning ingredients with squash, then place combined mixture in a large pan; bring to a boil and pour into jars.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Put soup and sour cream into chicken when done. Salt and pepper to taste. Layer bottom of baking dish with 1/2 of bread crumbs, then a layer of chicken, one layer of broccoli and one layer of rice. Repeat. On top of casserole, spread cornbread crumbs and 2 tablespoons melted margarine. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: hazelnut muffins
directions: Grease 5 (3 1/2-inch) muffin pans or 12 (2 1/2-inch) cups. In large cooking bowl, stir the flour, 2/3 cup nuts, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In medium mixing bowl, combine the egg, milk and oil.
Add egg mixture all at once to dry mixture.
Stir just until moist.
Put into muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove and cool.
Can be frosted if you want.

title: golden cream soup
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle flour over cold milk and shake.
Gradually add to hot mixture, stirring until thickens.
Remove from heat and add sliced cheese.

title: country fried chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a plastic bag; shake to mix. Place 2 or 3 pieces of chicken in the bag; shake well.
Repeat the procedure with remaining chicken.
Heat 1/2-inch of oil in a large skillet to 350°; add chicken and brown on all sides.
Reduce heat to medium; cover and cook 30 minutes or until chicken is tender. Remove cover and cook an additional 10 minutes, turning occasionally.
Drain well on paper towels.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Blend mustard and a small amount of vinegar in saucepan.
Add remaining vinegar, water, sugar, salt, celery seed, mustard seed and cloves; mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Cool.
Combine whole eggs and onion slices in bowl.
Add cooled vinegar mixture.
Chill, covered, overnight. Yield:
12 servings.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; spread in pan for sheet cake. Mix together the remaining 3 ingredients; spread over the top of the first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook onions and peppers slowly in Crisco until onions turn yellow.
Add meat; saute until meat falls apart.
Add tomatoes, rice and seasonings.
Put in casserole.
Cover and cook slowly for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: chocolate chip spice cookies
directions: Preheat oven at 375°.
Cream together eggs, both sugars and shortening and set aside.
Combine spices, flour and baking powder.
Add vanilla and milk and mix in remaining ingredients. Spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pineapple-cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix together pineapple, flour/sugar mixture and cheese. Put in casserole dish. Combine melted butter and crushed crackers. Place over pineapple mixture. Bake in preheated oven for 25 minutes or until top is slightly brown.

title: chicken divan
directions: Place broccoli in bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan.
Place chicken on top.
Mix curry powder, lemon juice, mayonnaise and soup.
Pour over chicken and cover with grated cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: maple pecan pie
directions: Melt butter; add sugar, salt, maple syrup and eggs.
Beat until well blended.
Fold in pecans; break large halves in half. Pour filling into crust and bake at 370 for 35 minutes until set. Cool.

title: creamed potato casserole
directions: Cream potatoes and add other ingredients.

title: viennese brownies
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
In a separate pan melt butter and chocolate; cool.
Beat eggs; add sugar and chocolate mixture. Sift flour, baking powder and salt and add this to chocolate mixture and mix well.
Pour half of chocolate mixture into greased 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Spread cream cheese mixture over it and top with the rest of chocolate mixture.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: ham glaze
directions: In saucepan, blend wine and lemon juice into cornstarch.
Add 1/2 of jam.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Stir in remaining jam and margarine.
Heat and stir until margarine is melted.
Brush ham with glaze.
Garnish ham with parsley or watercress.

title: barbecued pecans
directions: Mix sugar and vinegar in quart jar.
Add pecans and shake to coat nuts.
Place in shallow pan.
Bake in 250° oven, stirring frequently, for 30 minutes until lightly browned.
Add melted butter and seasoned salt; toss well.
Continue baking until toasted.
Store in tight container in refrigerator.
Yield:
2 cups.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Bring to boil all ingredients and pour into a warm crock-pot. Cook on high for 6 hours.
Cook without the lid.
At end of six hours, pour into pint jars.
Will yield around 4 to 5 pints.

title: susan's mint chocolate  cheese ball
directions: Stir 1 1/2 cups mix into 8 ounce softened cream cheese.
Shape into ball. Wrap in plastic and refrigerate until firm.
To serve, let stand at room temperature 20 to 30 minutes until softened and serve with Nabisco Famous Chocolate Wafers (usually found with Ice Cream Toppings).

title: smothered meatballs
directions: Combine beef and crumbs.
Add eggs, milk and seasonings and mix thoroughly.
Shape into balls and brown in oil.
Add onion soup and cook slowly for 20 minutes or until meatballs are tender. Variation: Use mushroom soup, flatten balls into patties and wrap each with strip of bacon.

title: rice pilaf
directions: In large Teflon or electric skillet melt butter then add noodles and saute until slightly browned.
Add rice and broth and simmer for 1/2 hour, stir often.
If it gets too thick, add a little water.
Serves 8, good with oven-baked chicken breasts.

title: frozen lemon crunch
directions: Blend the first 5 ingredients with hands until mixed.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place in a 375° oven until golden brown; stir occasionally while browning.
Reserve 3/4 cup for topping. Pat remainder into 10-inch pie tin.
Cool.
Beat egg yolks until light yellow.
Gradually add 1/2 cup white sugar; continue beating until thick and light.
Add lemon juice; beat.
In separate bowl, beat egg whites until stiff, adding remaining white sugar.
Whip cream; fold into egg white mixture.
Fold in egg yolk mixture and pour into crust.
Add topping and freeze.
Yields 8 servings.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Mix sugars, butter, Crisco, egg and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake about 10 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: pumpkin seed snack
directions: After you've removed the seeds from the pumpkin, don't throw them away.
Separate the seeds from the pulp and rinse under cool water.
Drain on paper towels.
Spread on cookie sheet and cover with melted margarine.
Salt to taste.

title: kim's crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt butter in deep pan on low heat. Add onion, bell pepper and garlic and saut for 10 minutes. Stir in flour. Season crawfish tails with salt, pepper and paprika and add tails to vegetables. Add water. Stir and cook slowly for 20 minutes. Add soup and simmer for 5 minutes. Serve on dirty rice and sprinkle with onion tops and parsley.

title: broccoli-cauliflower slaw
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and mayonnaise. Cut or chop the heads of broccoli, cauliflower and onion.
Pour mixture over and stir.
Let set overnight.

title: beef stew
directions: Rinse and pat dry stewing meat.
Cut in smaller pieces.
Add all ingredients in 5-quart cooking dish.
Mix dissolved beef cubes and can of soup with preceding ingredients, adding salt and pepper and any other spices you might like.
Cook in oven at 350°. Time 2 to 3 hours, covered.
Do not need to brown meat first.

title: virginia apple pudding
directions: Melt butter in 2-quart casserole.
Combine next 6 ingredients to make batter; pour on butter.
Drain apples; pile in center of batter.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) until batter covers fruit and crust browns, 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: stir-fry vegetables
directions: Cook garlic in oil.
Add celery, pepper strips and oregano. Cook until tender-crisp.
Add beans and carrots.
Heat through. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: veal casserole
directions: Salt and pepper meat.
Flour with flour.
Brown meat and put in a glass casserole.
Cook bell peppers, mushrooms and onion. Remove from heat and add basil, white wine, water and bouillon cube.
Pour over meat and cover with foil.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the 1/4 cup catsup, in a large bowl.
Press into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or shape into a loaf on a bake and serve platter.
Spread the 1/4 cup catsup over top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Allow to sit a few minutes before slicing.
Serves 8 or 10.

title: janie batten's sweet potato pie
directions: Mix everything together.
Makes 2 pies.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift
dry
ingredients into a large bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients
well
and
add to dry ingredients.
Mix just until the
liquids coat the flour.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan and bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Whip Dream Whip according to package directions to make 2 quarts.
When whipped, add chocolate syrup (Hershey's) while continuing to whip.
When blended, dish into dessert dishes and top with whipped topping and chocolate shavings or miniature chocolate chips.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute carrots and onion in oil.
Mix with black pepper, mayonnaise, salt and red pepper.
Grease a casserole dish with 1 tablespoon of margarine.
Pour mixture in dish.
Sprinkle crushed crackers over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheese.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt 4 tablespoons butter, add flour and salt.
Add milk slowly.
Cook until sauce thickens.
Add sliced potatoes and bring to a boil.
Arrange in a 9 x 13 baking dish and dot with remaining butter.
Bake a 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Yields 12 servings.

title: muddy buddies
directions: Place cereal in a large bowl; set aside.
Microwave chocolate chips, Reese's pieces and oleo.
Add vanilla.
Pour chocolate mixture over cereal.
Place combined mixture in zipper bag with powdered sugar and shake.

title: hot chopped beef dip
directions: Whip cream cheese and milk together.
Chop dried beef and add to cream cheese.
Add onion, garlic salt and pepper.
Fold in sour cream.
Put in shallow baking dish.
In saucepan melt 2 tablespoons butter; add 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Spoon over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cheese souffle(my all time favorite food!)
directions: Stir Cheddar cheese into hot white sauce.
Remove from heat. Stir in egg yolks, well beaten.
Beat egg whites until stiff with cream of tartar.
Fold in the cheese mixture with a wire whisk. Pour into ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Make a groove 1 inch from edge with a knife.
Set casserole in pan of water 1 inch deep.
Bake until puffed and brown, about 50 minutes at 350°. Serve immediately!
Serves 4.

title: turkey and fruit salad
directions: Cut turkey into julienned strips (4 1/2 x 1/2-inch).
Cut celery diagonally into slices (1/4-inch).
Combine with fruits and almonds and mix thoroughly.
Fold into turkey.
Combine salad dressing, lemon juice, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce and curry powder and mix thoroughly.
Gently stir into turkey mixture. Cover and refrigerate.
Serve each portion on chilled lettuce leaf.
Garnish with strawberry or other brightly colored fruit.

title: date nut chews
directions: Mix together.
Spread in wax paper-lined cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into bars while warm.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Place soup, mayonnaise and cream cheese in saucepan and heat on low until blended together. With wire whisk, whip cream cheese until completely melted. Melt gelatin in 1/4 cup hot water. Add soup mixture and stir well. Stir in celery, onion and shrimp. Pour into well-oiled mold. Chill at least 5 hours. Serve with Triscuit crackers.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Add cherries and nuts, blending with a spoon.
Bake at 350° for 45-50 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: country fried pork chops
directions: Wipe the chops with a damp cloth and slash the fat a bit around the edges to keep them from curling during cooking.
In large skillet, fry bacon until crisp, then remove and drain on absorbent paper.
Dip the chops in flour, then in lightly beaten egg, then roll in crumbs.
Brown quickly in bacon fat, turning with spatula, being careful not to loosen crumbs.
After they are browned, add salt, pepper and 1/2 cup cream.
Reduce heat, cover pan and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes until chops are tender. Remove meat to a hot platter; add 1/2 cup cream to the pan.
Pour this over chops, then sprinkle with crumbled bacon bits.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Cookie Crust:
Spray a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan with cooking spray.
In a large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat the flour, butter or margarine (cut in pieces), sugar and salt until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Press firmly into prepared pan. Bake 20 to 23 minutes or until golden brown.
Top with filling and complete baking.

title: deep freeze daiquiri
directions: Put half of the ingredients in a blender. Pour into freezer container. Blend the other half of the ingredients and put into same container.
Freeze for at least 12 hours.
Thirty minutes before serving, remove container from freezer and stir. When ready, pour into glasses and stir again.
Never freezes solid, will be slushy.

title: almond chicken salad
directions: Mix all together and chill 4 or 5 hours.
Serve on bed of lettuce.

title: cheesecake
directions: Blend cream cheese and sugar.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour into baked graham cracker crumb crust and top with favorite topping. Cool, then serve.

title: nutty puddin' cake
directions: Use milk and prepare pudding as directed on box.
Immediately stir dry cake mix into pudding.
Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chips (as many or as few as you like) and nuts on top of cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Reserve 1 cup of tomato sauce.
Combine all remaining ingredients.
Spoon into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Heat reserved tomato sauce and serve over meat loaf.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken delight
directions: Place skinned chicken in casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Whole chicken, cut-up, may be used as well.
Serve with rice.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Mix and pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta.
Cool.
Add drained beans and all other ingredients.
Toss with desired amount of salad dressing.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: On wax paper, stir together flour and baking powder; set aside.
In large pan, melt butter.
Remove from heat; stir in 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs until smooth.
Gradually stir in flour mixture until a smooth dough forms.
Cover tight and refrigerate at least 1 hour or up to 3 days.
Mix rest of sugar and cinnamon on wax paper.
Roll dough into balls by a teaspoon and roll in mix.
Bake at 375° on nonstick cookie sheet for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: tangy chicken
directions: Cut chicken; remove skin.
(If using wings, cut the tips.) Arrange in a single layer in a pan or glass dish.
In saucepan (or microwave) melt the margarine, honey and mustard together.
Pour the melted mixture over the chicken.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Turn pieces after 35 minutes.
Can use for pork chops, also.

title: mexican salad
directions: In a skillet brown
and
drain beef.
Add seasoning and kidney beans; leave on low
heat
until
beans
are hot.
In a bowl mix lettuce, cheese,
Doritos and dressing.
Add beef and bean mixture; mix well.
Serve hot.

title: olive royale salad
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Mix dressing with curry powder.
Pour over salad and toss well.
May prepare ahead of time but do not add dressing until just before serving.

title: whiskey sour slush
directions: Mix and freeze.
Serve 1/2 slush with 1/2 ginger ale or 7-Up.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper in a paper bag; put chicken in bag and shake. Melt enough butter and vegetable shortening to cover the bottom 2-inches of a large skillet. Add chicken; cover skillet. Cook slowly for 30 minutes. Uncover; drain fat. Add enough water to cover bottom of skillet. Cover skillet again; simmer for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat loaf mix in hot, melted Crisco in a large pot.
Add onion.
Add garlic clove.
Add tomato paste, 2 teaspoons of salt and 1 teaspoon of pepper.
Add water.
Add whole tomatoes with juices, chopped into small pieces.
Add 1 tablespoon of salt and 1 teaspoon of pepper and bring mixture to a hard boil.
Reduce heat to simmer, cover and let cook 2 to 3 hours.
Stir occasionally. Remove garlic clove when done.
Sauce can be frozen for later use.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix wet ingredients.
Combine all and mix well.
Bake an hour at 350° or use microwave on High for 14 minutes, turning cake every 4 minutes.
Cool completely and frost.

title: grandma's pot roast
directions: *Use however many you need.

title: loquat pie
directions: Peel and seed loquats.
Fill bottom crust.
Mix sugar, cornstarch, butter and lemon juice.
Pour over fruit, then cover with a top crust and bake until lightly browned at 350° about 1 hour.

title: brown sugar sauce
directions: Melt butter and add brown sugar and flour.
Mix until smooth and add boiling water.
Cook until thick.
Pour over egg that has been slightly beaten and add flavoring.
Good on spice cake or gingerbread.

title: pineapple-zucchini bread
directions: Beat together sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in the pineapple, zucchini, walnuts and raisins.
In a separate bowl, combine the flour, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add to zucchini mixture. Mix just until well blended.
Pour into 2 greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crab smitty
directions: Remove cartilage from crabmeat.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add crabmeat, lemon juice, salt, pepper, onion juice, liquid hot pepper sauce and thyme.
Saute briefly until crabmeat is just heated through.
Cover and simmer for 2 to 3 minutes until edges of ham curl and flavors are well-blended.
May be served on toast.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fix-a-pizza
directions: Arrange the Fritos chips in a 12-inch pizza pan.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese slices.
Saute ground beef with garlic until light brown.
Add tomato paste, salt, pepper, oregano, mushrooms and eggs.
Mix well.
Spread beef mixture over cheese.
Sprinkle with tomato pieces and Cheddar cheese.
Top with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: Brown onions in butter; add stock and cook slowly until onions are soft.
Serve with croutons and sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Roll biscuit pieces in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Arrange in Bundt pan along with nuts.
Melt butter and stir in brown sugar.
Pour over biscuits and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn out of pan immediately.

title: cocoa mocha frosting
directions: Sift sugar, salt and cocoa together.
Cream butter until soft; add part of sugar mixture gradually, beating thoroughly.
Add remaining sugar mixture alternately with warm coffee, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Makes enough frosting to cover tops of 2 (9-inch) layers.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Peel and mash avocados; add lemon juice, salt and pepper. Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasonings.
Cover large shallow platter with foil; layer on bean dip, then avocado mixture and sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle onions, tomatoes and olives; top with shredded cheese.
Chill about 3 hours before serving.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray jelly roll pan with cooking spray.
Put all ingredients in food processor and blend until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Press firmly
into prepared pan. Bake for 20 to 23 minutes, until golden brown.
Top with filling and finish baking.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring, until thickened. Serve over hot biscuits.

title: mashed potato candy
directions: Mix potato and sugar.
Stir in coconut, vanilla and salt. Blend well.
Press into large pan so candy will be 1/2 inch thick. Melt chocolate over hot water.
Pour over candy.
Cool and cut into pieces.

title: spoon bread
directions: Melt 1/2 stick margarine in pan. Mix all ingredients and pour in pan. Cook in 375° oven approximately 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Make in a 10 to 12-cup electric percolator.
Put spices into basket.
Put liquid into the pot.
Let percolate until hot.
Pour into heatproof cups or mugs.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: creamy potato hokkaido style
directions: Peel potatoes and slice.
Cook potatoes with vegetable cubes and milk on medium heat until tender.
Add Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with spring onions before serving.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix with electric mixer the milk, lemon juice and egg yolks. Pour into pie shell.
Whip egg white until stiff.
Add 1/4 cup sugar.
Beat until well mixed.
Top pie with egg white mix and brown in oven.
Allow to set overnight in refrigerator before serving.

title: artichoke omelet
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients in a heavy saucepan until almost done.
Cool slightly then add eggs and cheese.
Put in an oiled casserole and bake in a 300° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Bring to a boil margarine, cocoa and water.
Pour over flour and sugar.
Add eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into ball and roll in 1 cup of chopped pecans.
This can be frozen for later use.

title: creamy baked chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese slices.
Combine soup and wine.
Spoon evenly over chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing mix around the chicken. Drizzle oleo over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: "heart smart" baked chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a blender, place oatmeal, Parmesan cheese, salt, paprika and pepper.
Cover and blend about 1 minute or until thoroughly mixed.
In shallow dish, place oatmeal mixture.
In separate shallow dish, mix garlic and milk.
Roll chicken pieces in oatmeal mixture, then dip in milk mixture and roll again in oatmeal.
Place chicken in a large shallow baking pan; drizzle with margarine.
Bake for about 1 hour or until fork can be inserted in chicken with ease.
Garnish with parsley and cherry tomatoes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: penne with broccoli
directions: In a saute pan over medium heat, heat the olive oil.
Add the garlic and cook for 2 minutes.
Add the steamed broccoli and saute for 1 minute.
Add chicken stock; raise the heat to high and cook until a lot of the liquid has evaporated, not all, stirring occasionally.
Bring water to a boil while cooking broccoli and cook penne.
Toss the pasta with broccoli sauce and season with pepper to taste.
Add Romano cheese.
Save some for serving.
Toss again and serve.

title: cheese baked chicken
directions: Toss cheese and cracker crumbs together lightly in a bowl. Dip chicken in melted margarine, then roll in cracker and cheese mixture. Place in lightly greased casserole dish.
Pour remaining butter over chicken.
Sprinkle with parsley and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: peter pan salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water and hot water and let cool. Crush graham crackers.
Put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix rest of ingredients and put in dish. Put jello on top of ingredients and put in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Mix all together.
Spoon into muffin pan.
Dough will be sort of sticky.
Cook 20 minutes on 350°.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large pot and simmer for 3 to 4 hours.
Makes a lot!

title: poverty pudding
directions: Mix and put in square Pyrex cake pan or a round casserole. Mix 1 cup brown sugar and 2 cups hot water and pour over the batter.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
This makes its own sauce. Serve warm or cold.

title: gooey coffee cake
directions: Lightly sprinkle 1/2 c. pecans over bottom of greased 9 x 13 pan (or 2 round cake pans). Place frozen rolls at random on top of nuts. Pour melted butter over rolls. Make a mixture of brown sugar, 1/2 c. pecans, and dry pudding. Sprinkle over rolls. Cover pan or pans with a tea towel and let set overnight. Bake at 350° for 30 min. Turn over onto plate.

title: peter pan soup
directions: Cook onion and celery in butter until tender.
Blend in peanut butter.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in water; add to peanut butter mixture gradually, blending well after each addition.
Stir in lemon juice; heat to serving temperature.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Beat together first 6 ingredients.
Mix and beat all remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Finely chop mushrooms, then combine with lemon juice. Melt butter in large skillet.
Add shallots and saute. Add mushrooms, bay leaf and thyme. Cook, stirring frequently, until liquid completely evaporates.

title: jackie's special salad
directions: Grate cabbage, pepper, carrots and celery.
Boil vinegar, water, sugar and celery seed until dissolved.
Cool and stir through cabbage mixture.
Freeze.

title: raspberry liqueur
directions: Simmer sugar and water until sugar is dissolved.
Cool and pour over raspberries in a wide-mouth gallon jar.
Add liquor. Cover loosely and set in a cool, dark place for 3 months.
Strain out raspberries and strain again through several layers of cheesecloth.
Pour into clean quart bottles.

title: lemon smothered chops
directions: In casserole dish place pork chops; cover meat with lemon slices, onion rings, salt and pepper.
Pour tomato juice over mixture.
Dot with butter.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: dilly dressing
directions: *I use 2 teaspoons dried minced onion.

title: health bread
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients until shortening melts.
Then let cool until temperature is right for yeast.
Add whole wheat flour and sprinkle yeast on top of flour, then stir.
Add all-purpose flour until moderately stiff.
Turn out onto floured area and knead 5 to 7 minutes.
Place in greased bowl and let rise for 1 hour.
Punch down and divide into thirds.
Let rest 10 minutes. Put into greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch pans.
Cover and let rise 35 to 45 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: barbara bush's oatmeal lace cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and sugar.
Mix together until well blended.
Drop by slightly heaped 1/4 teaspoonful 4-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
(Only bake about 6 to 8 at a time.)
Bake at 375° for 4 to 6 minutes until lightly browned.
Let stand a few seconds then remove from pan.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt oleo in baking pan (9 x 13-inch).
Add cracker crumbs, chips and nuts.
Pour milk evenly over the top.
Bake 25 minutes. Do not bake longer; they are done!
Cool and cut in squares.

title: date cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream margarine and sugars.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Fold in nuts and dates. Roll into balls and press down with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: lo-cal, low sugar congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add milk and cream cheese (room temperature).
Add pineapple and rest of ingredients.
Chill several hours to congeal.

title: lemon bar brownies(in honor of stallion, "blackjack parlay")
directions: Beat.
After the first mixture (the crust) is baked and removed from the oven, pour the lemon mixture over and bake at 350°
for 20 minutes, or until it seems solid.
Cool until lukewarm and sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.
Cut into squares to serve.
Very rich; very delicious!

title: vidalia onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter; add pepper.
Cook until lightly browned.
Sprinkle onions with flour; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add beef broth and simmer 30 minutes.
Taste and add salt to taste.
Place soup in individual ovenproof dishes.
Place toast on top and sprinkle with cheese.
Place under broiler or in 400° oven until cheese is melted.
Serves 6.

title: velveeta cheese fudge
directions: Melt cheese and margarine in top of double boiler.
Sift cocoa and sugar together until smooth (at least 6 times).
Mix into melted cheese mixture.
Blend with wooden spoon.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Press into lightly buttered 9 x 13-inch pans. Let set.
Makes 7 pounds.

title: burger bundles
directions: Prepare stuffing according to "in bird" directions.
Mix hamburger and milk together well.
Make a meatball and flatten it on a plate so it is about 6 inches in diameter.
Put a ball of stuffing in the middle and mold the hamburger around it so it looks like a huge meatball.
Top each meatball with a generous spoonful of mushroom soup right out of the can (use the entire can).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes its own gravy.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute onion and peppers in margarine.
Mix all ingredients and put in greased casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: quick tater tot bake
directions: In a skillet, brown meat and onion. Season with salt and pepper. Place in a greased 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish. Top with potatoes. Combine soup and milk or water. Pour over potatoes. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Yield: 2 to 3 servings.

title: marshmallow cake
directions: Mix all but marshmallow cream; put in floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
While cake is baking, set marshmallow cream in hot water until cake is done.
Spread over hot cake.

title: yams
directions: Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until liquid is thick.

title: baked beans with ground meat
directions: Brown lightly the meat, onion and bell pepper.
Add pork and beans, ketchup, brown sugar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce. Put this in a baking dish.
Place strips of bacon on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: salmon mousse
directions: Oil a 1 1/2-quart mold.
Place the gelatin and water in a small saucepan; stir over low heat until the gelatin is dissolved, 3 to 5 minutes.
Set aside to cool.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Cream together and knead until smooth.
Add food coloring, if desired, and knead until mixture is an even color.
Form cherry size balls and roll in sugar. Flatten with a fork or place in mold.
Let stand overnight.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: praline pecan crunch
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Combine cereal and pecans in a 9 x 13-inch pan; set aside.
Combine corn syrup, brown sugar and margarine in a 2-cup microwavable bowl.
Microwave at High 1 1/2 minutes; stir. Microwave at High 1/2 to 1 1/2 minutes, or until boiling.
Stir in vanilla and baking soda; pour over cereal mixture.
Stir to coat evenly.
Bake for 1 hour, stirring every 20 minutes.
Spread on baking sheet to cool; break into pieces.
Makes 10 cups.

title: hot hominy casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Drain hominy.
Mix all ingredients in a casserole bowl, except cheese.
Dot cheese on top.
Place in oven at 300° for about 20 minutes.	All ingredients are cooked, but should be bubbly hot.
Onions should cook in the 20 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles. While cooking, mix cheese, mushroom soup and tuna. Drain noodles and mix with cheese, mushroom soup and tuna mixture. Pour into 8 x 8 baking dish. Cover with potato chips.
Bake at 300° until hot and bubbling.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: In greased pan, arrange raw rice and then chicken pieces.
In bowl, combine chicken soup, onion soup and water.
Pour over chicken and bake uncovered for about 2 hours in 350° oven.

title: fried pork chop glaze
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a jar while frying pork chops. Turn heat low and pour over chops; simmer as glaze.

title: johanna kromas's scones
directions: Mix ingredients together until you have a soft dough.
Use dough and fill 2 large pie tins.
Bake in medium oven (350°) until done.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 5 minutes.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt cheese and butter in double boiler or microwave.
Stir well after melted. While cheese and butter are melting, sift sugar and cocoa.
Pour cheese mixture over sugar and cocoa.
Add vanilla. Stir well.
Press into buttered casserole dish. Chill until set.

title: creole wieners
directions: Pan broil bacon, cut into 1/2-inch squares until half done. Saute onions until lightly browned.
Stir in tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Place wieners on top.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes. Uncover and boil hard 8 to 10 minutes.

title: applesauce fruit cake
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients together.
Combine walnuts, raisins and cherries.
Beat until light the shortening, sugar and eggs. Add applesauce.
Blend well.
Add sifted dry ingredients, mixing well.
Stir in cherries, nuts and raisins.
Put in greased angel food cake pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Place meat in bottom of a 2-quart casserole.
Next, add the green beans.
Pour the mushroom soup over the beans and hamburger.
Spread the mashed potatoes over the top.
Cover the casserole and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican-style french rolls
directions: Grease 2 large cookie sheets; sprinkle with cornmeal.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In large bowl, combine 3 cups flour, salt, sugar and yeast.
In small saucepan, heat 2 cups water and shortening until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add warm liquid to flour mixture.
Blend at low speed until moistened; beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in 1 1/2 to 2 1/4 cups flour to form a stiff dough.

title: simple apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease or coat with nonstick cooking spray a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: double chocolate cupcakes
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a medium bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine orange juice, water, oil, vinegar and vanilla. Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened. Fold in chocolate morsels.
Spoon into foil or paper lined muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Remove from pans immediately.
Cool on a wire rack. Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Makes 1 dozen.
Contains about 153 calories each. Preparation time:
30 minutes.

title: salmon ball
directions: Drain, debone and flake salmon.
Combine with cream cheese, lemon juice, onion, horseradish, salt and liquid smoke.
Mix thoroughly.
Chill for several hours.
Shape mixture into a ball and roll in nuts and parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: sweet and sour chestnuts
directions: Cut bacon strips in thirds; wrap around chestnuts and secure with toothpick.
(May need to cut chestnuts in half.)
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Drain oil.
Prepare mixture (sugar, catsup and lemon juice).
Pour over chestnuts and bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding, milk, Eagle Brand and water.
Stir in Cool Whip. Layer in dish in this order: wafers, bananas and filling.
You may wish to top it with Cool Whip.

title: gerry's peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine shortening, salt, soda and peanut butter; mix well. Add white, then brown sugar.
Cream well.
Add beaten eggs; mix well.
Add flour and mix again.
Drop by the teaspoonful onto a greased cookie sheet.
Press with a floured fork.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: cheddar cheese egg casserole
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Remove crusts from bread.
Butter bread slices and line bottom of pan.
Fry or microwave bacon; crumble over bread.
Sprinkle cheese over bacon.
Mix thoroughly mustard, milk and eggs.
Pour over bread, bacon and cheese.
Cover pan and refrigerate at least 8 hours or overnight.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: tamale casserole
directions: In 2-quart casserole, layer tamales, onions, Ranch Style beans, then tamales, onions, corn chips (crushed) and chili beans. Sprinkle with grated cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add more cheese and let it start to melt.

title: eastern shore corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook on top of stove until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour into well-greased baking pan and bake at 425° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Really best if baked in a large black iron frying pan.

title: braised steak
directions: Mix flour, salt, pepper, oil and steak.
Rub flour mixture into meat well.
Brown in Dutch oven or kettle.
Add beer, broth, onions, garlic, bay leaf and thyme.
Bring to boiling; cover and simmer over low heat 2 1/2 to 3 hours until tender.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except Kisses, on lowest speed. Shape dough into balls. Roll in sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Top each cookie with a candy Kiss immediately when taken out of oven.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook onions, celery and green pepper in hot fat until brown. Stir in flour, salt, pepper, tomatoes and water; cook until slightly thick, stirring frequently.
Add cooked, cleaned shrimp. Serve over hot cooked rice.
Serves 6.

title: quick and easy oatmeal candy
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa, and butter in large pan on stove. Bring to a boil. Boil long enough to dissolve sugar and cocoa. Be sure to mix well. Remove from heat and add oatmeal, peanut butter, and vanilla flavoring. Stir well.
