When thoroughly mixed, place by spoonfuls on a waxed paper or nonstick cookie sheet and place in refrigerator to cool.

title: play dough
directions: Mix well until moistened.
Cool and knead on floured board. Store in covered container.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Combine strawberries and 1 1/2 cups sugar in a heavy saucepan and bring to a boil; stir constantly.
Boil, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Add remaining sugar and boil 15 minutes, stirring frequently, until the mixture reaches 221° on a candy thermometer. Skim foam.
Cool.
Cover and allow to stand at room temperature for 24 hours; stir occasionally.
Spoon into clean jars and refrigerate.
Yields 3 half pints.

title: special sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine
sweet	potatoes
with next 8 ingredients.
Add 1/4 cup peanuts, finely chopped.
Place in a 2 quart casserole and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Combine coconut, brown sugar and remaining
peanuts (1/2 cup).
Sprinkle over top of sweet potato mixture
and
bake approximately 10 minutes longer, or until lightly browned.
Makes about 6 to 8 servings.

title: shoepeg corn, english pea salad
directions: Rinse and drain vegetables well.
Heat sugar, vinegar, oil and celery seed together.
Pour over vegetables (including peppers and onions), combine and chill overnight.

title: savory dried cranberry sauce(to be served with pork, chicken or ham)
directions: In a small saucepan, whisk together the brown sugar and the cornstarch and add the wine and broth, whisking until the mixture is smooth.
Add the vinegar, cranberries, tarragon and salt to taste.

Simmer the sauce, stirring occasionally, for 15 minutes. Stir in the minced parsley and simmer the sauce for 1 minute more. Serve either with the meat or cover meat with sauce and then cook (grilled is excellent) or pan-fry pork with sauce covering the meat.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: chicken cordon bleu in skillet
directions: Brown chicken and ham in oil.
Add other ingredients.
Cook until rice is done.
Serves 4.

title: luscious flan
directions: Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar in a heavy saucepan; place over medium heat.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sugar melts and syrup is light golden brown.
Pour syrup into 6 (6 ounce) custard cups; let cool.
Combine milks in medium saucepan or heat in microwave until bubbles form.
Combine egg substitute, 1/4 cup sugar, salt and almond extract; beat well and gradually stir about 1 cup hot milk into egg mixture; add to remaining milk and pour mixture into custard cups.
Cover with aluminum foil and place cups in a shallow pan of hot water.
Bake at 325° for about 40 minutes or until done.

title: shelby's red velvet cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil, buttermilk, cocoa and baking soda. Add food coloring to batter.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 350° until done.
For a very moist cake, don't overbake or brown. Let cake cool.

title: quick rice and beans
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan over medium high heat cook bacon until crisp.
Add garlic, coriander and cumin.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix together peaches, sugar and flavoring.
Put margarine in baking pan in 350° oven to melt.

title: six week muffins
directions: Mix cereal, sugar, flour, baking soda and salt in a large bowl.
Add beaten eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Store in refrigerator in covered container.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Mix together and put into pie plate.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Put under broiler until bubbly.
Makes 2 cups.

title: mandarin orange cake delight
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and oranges until blended.
Pour into two round 9-inch cake pans or 3 square pans which have been greased. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and ice.

title: swedish meatballs(kottbullar)
directions: Follow the recipe for meatballs.
Shape mixture into a loaf and place on a buttered baking dish.
Brush with beaten egg and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Baste the loaf occasionally.
Add a little water if necessary.

title: apricot pie filling
directions: Bring juice, water and sugar to boil.
Add Clear Jell to water and stir well.
Then add to juice.
Cook 10 minutes. Remove, then add jello, butter, salt and apricots.
Cut apricots in smaller slices if slices are too big.

title: easy strawberry dessert
directions: Tear angel food cake in bite size pieces and put in large casserole.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add all other ingredients, stir until well mixed.
Pour over cake.
Chill well.

title: mrs. solomon's nut horn cookies
directions: Place ground nuts in a bowl.
Add butter or margarine, then sugar.
Make a paste with this mixture so that it is of spreading consistency.
Add flavoring; mix well.
If the mixture is still too thick, add a little water, a tablespoon at a time, until the desired consistency is reached (spreading almost like peanut butter).
Set aside.

title: angel food bars
directions: Mix together, but do not beat.
Use jelly roll pan.
Bake in 350° oven 20 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Mix in a large bowl the flour, soda and salt together.
Mix well.
Add the remaining ingredients except chocolate kisses.
Mix at medium speed with electric mixer until well combined, scraping bowl occasionally.
Chill dough for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable souffle salad
directions: Step 1: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water. Add cold water, vinegar, mayonnaise, salt and pepper. Blend well with rotary beater. Pour into freezing tray.

title: apple cinnamon bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake until done.

title: spring garden wild rice
directions: Prepare wild rice as directed.
Set aside.
Saute onions, celery and bell peppers in butter until tender.
Do not brown. Combine sauteed ingredients with rice.
Add thyme and serve.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook bacon, drain and cut into pieces.
Add onion to drained fat and cook until tender and lightly browned.
Add potatoes and water and cook until tender.
Soak crackers in milk.
Add corn and soaked crackers to the mixture.
Heat to a boil.

title: triple cheese dip
directions: Whip softened cream cheese.
Mix with all other ingredients and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mash bananas.
Add ingredients and pour lemon juice over this. Blend; stir well.
Freeze.

title: chris' favorite salisbury steaks
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs in cup and fill to 3/4 mark with milk.
Add to ground meat along with bread crumbs, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix everything with hands and roll into egg shaped patties approximately 4 ounces each.
Place in a covered roaster and bake for 1/2 hour.
Remove from oven and pour gravy over patties.
Bake for another 1/2 hour or until done.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, cocoa, butter and milk.
Bring to a boil; boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Beat until thick and smooth.
Spoon onto waxed paper to cool.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press dough onto pizza pan and bake until light brown.
Mix sugar and cream cheese.
Spread on cookie when done.
Layer bananas and oranges.
Cover with pie filling.
Refrigerate until served.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Chill juice and ginger ale.
Mix well in punch bowl.
Add about 4 or 5 cups of ice cream.
Serve.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Rinse and scrub potatoes; pat dry.
Prick a few times with fork and bake at 375° for
1 hour or until soft.
Cut thin slice off top of each potato and carefully scoop out pulp.
Place pulp in mixing bowl.
Separate eggs; add yolks to pulp.
Blend until smooth.
Add butter and cream; season to taste with salt and pepper.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold into pulp mixture.
Fill shells with mixture. Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Top as desired with green onions, chives, parsley, bell pepper or mushrooms or include in mixture.

title: banana nut bread
directions: In a large bowl, mash bananas.
Add sugar, oil, vanilla and eggs.
In another bowl, mix dry ingredients, then add to banana mix.
Stir well.
Add walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Combine milk, flour, sugar, egg and seasoning.
Stir in chilies, onions and squash mixture until consistency of potato patties.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook until it thickens.
Pour into browned pie shell.
Top with margarine from egg whites.
Brown in oven until margarine becomes brown.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix everything together and chill.

title: paul newman cake
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13-inch oblong pan according to directions. While hot, poke large holes in cake and pour milk in holes all over cake.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl. Process in blender until smooth. Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: burger bites for children
directions: Take two wafers and 1 mint.
Put a squirt of mustard (yellow frosting), a squirt of ketchup (red frosting) and a squirt of pickle (green frosting) on one side of vanilla wafer; put your hamburger together.
Have fun eating your candy hamburger.

title: mystery pecan pie
directions: In a food processor, process until fluffy the cream cheese, 1 egg, 1/3 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Spread the mixture in the bottom of the shell.
Sprinkle the pecans over the cheese mixture.
Beat the remaining 3 eggs with an electric mixer until foamy. Do not overmix.
Add the corn syrup, the remaining 1/4 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon vanilla and the salt.
Mix well.
Pour this over the pecans.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: london broil with olive sauce
directions: Broil flank steak 2 to 3 inches from source of heat for about 8 minutes.
Turn and broil 8 minutes longer or until well browned and to desired degree of doneness.
Cut meat diagonally across grain into very thin slices.
Keep warm.

title: jewish crumb cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating each 1 minute at high speed.

title: pecan bars
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix sugar, butter, vanilla and egg in bowl.
Stir in flour.
Press dough in bottom and 1/2 inch up sides of ungreased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake until edges are light brown, about 10-15 minutes.
Beat brown sugar, corn syrup, vanilla and eggs with a spoon; stir in pecans.
Pour over crust and bake until set, 25-30 minutes.
Loosen edges from side of pan while warm. Cool completely and cut into bars about 1 1/2 by 2-inches.
Cover and refrigerate any remaining bars.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Melt butter, stir in cake mix and add 2 eggs.
Divide and spread 3/4 the way up in 2 greased 9 x 9-inch pans.
Mix softened cream cheese, powdered sugar and 2 eggs.
Divide and pour on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit smoothies
directions: Peel and cut banana into large chunks.
Place in a plastic bag; seal and freeze 5 to 6 hours or overnight.
Place all ingredients in a blender.
Blend until smooth.

title: sex in the pan
directions: Mix pecans, flour, sugar and butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 25 minutes; cool well.
Blend cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 1/2 container of Cool Whip.
Spread on base.
Mix puddings and milk.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Ice with remainder of Cool Whip.
Top with shaved chocolate.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers.
Slice or chop green pepper and dice onion.
Mix together 1/2 to 3/4 cup Miracle Whip, canned milk (to thin), vinegar, sugar (to taste), salt and pepper.
Mix with cucumbers.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Cook chicken quickly in oil.
Add broccoli and broth and simmer 2 minutes.
Add soy sauce that has been mixed with cornstarch and sugar and stir until thickened.
Simmer 2 minutes. Mix in green onions and sprinkle on cashews.
Serve over hot cooked brown rice.
Very quick.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Will be puffed and brown.

title: pink lady salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and stir. Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: glazed potato doughnuts
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool until lukewarm.
Stir in yeast, potatoes and eggs. Gradually add enough flour to make soft dough.

title: anytime muffins
directions: Combine oats and boiling water; let cool.
Mix together eggs, sugar, oil and buttermilk.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients with All-Bran just until moistened.
Store in covered containers in refrigerator up to 6 weeks.
Bake in well-greased muffin tins. Raisins, nuts or chopped dates may be added to batter before baking at 375°
for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen muffins.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla. Pour into prepared crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until done.
Mix all ingredients with cooked squash.
Put half of stuffing on bottom of dish.
Put the squash mixture in and cover with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° until brown, or about 30 minutes.
Makes 2 dishes and freezes well.

title: tea cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, butter, egg and vanilla. Add 1 cup of flour, stir, half of the milk, stir.
Add cup of flour and rest of milk; stir.
If mixture is not thick enough, add more flour.
Roll out thin and cut out cookies.
Bake until golden brown.

title: wild rice chicken
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Combine rice, chopped chicken, water chestnuts, celery and onion.
Place into 2 1/2-quart baking dish; stir mayonnaise and mushroom soup together and spread on top of chicken mixture.
Bake, covered, in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: salad dressing
directions: Put all in pint jar; add enough milk to shoulder of jar and shake well.
Good for cole slaw, potato salad and macaroni salad.

title: hotsy cheesy dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Microwave until melted together.
Stir several times.
Stir in scallions.
Can be used as a dip for chips or vegetables.
Also, can be served over baked potatoes.

title: fruit muffins(low-fat)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spray muffin pans with nonstick cooking spray.
Stir baking soda into yogurt.
In a mixing bowl, combine sugar, whole wheat flour, all-purpose flour and baking powder. Stir in the yogurt mixture, oil, egg whites and vanilla until just combined.
Fold in fruit.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix shortening, butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla thoroughly.
Blend in flour, soda, salt and chocolate chips.
I sift all my dry ingredients before adding to creamed mixture; stir in chips last with spoon.
I also add an extra 1/2 cup flour for softer, rounder cookies.
I roll the dough into balls, the size of walnuts (almost) and place almost touching on the cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: peanut butter crisscross
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in peanut butter.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Stir flour stuff into creamy stuff.
Roll cookie dough into balls and crisscross lightly with fork.
Bake 8 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: sweet cucumber pickles(no sugar)
directions: Wash pickles and drain. Pack in cans. Pour the mixture over them. Cool. Seal.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and eggs.
Chop all vegetables and eggs and mix with salad dressing.
Chill and serve.

title: epiphany tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
To serve, use 2 teaspoons of mix to 1 cup boiling water.

title: e. z. fudge
directions: In a large skillet, combine sugar, margarine, salt and evaporated milk.
Bring to a full boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil for 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips, marshmallows and vanilla.
Stir until completely melted and smoothly blended.
Place in buttered 9-inch pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind washed cranberries into a bowl.
Peel and core apples; grind into bowl with cranberries.
Grate orange peel into bowl with cranberries and apples.
Cut orange in half and squeeze juice and bulk into same bowl.
Add sugar and stir well.
Add crushed pineapple and stir well.
Chill overnight.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter or margarine.
Add eggs one at a time. Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Put 1/2 cup flour in at a time, alternating with sour cream.
Add vanilla and lemon.
Grease and flour bottom and sides of a 12-inch tube pan.
Put wax paper on bottom of pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, cornstarch and salt in a saucepan. Gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Gradually stir at least half of the hot mixture into the 3 egg yolks, slightly beaten, then blend into hot mixture in saucepan. Boil 1 minute more.
Remove from heat and add margarine and vanilla.
Pour into 9-inch baked pie shell.
Spread meringue lightly on pie filling, sealing edges well.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: golden pecan pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add eggs, syrup, vanilla and margarine.
Beat with electric mixer until blended. Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: joanie's soft popcorn balls
directions: Mix first four ingredients in a large saucepan.
Cook to soft ball stage on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and add butter. Pour syrup over corn and mix.
Form into soft balls.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown the hamburger meat with the onion, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Drain meat.
Mix together remaining ingredients and let simmer while you prepare the noodles.

title: pennsylvania dutch horseradish sauce
directions: Whip the sour cream.
Add other ingredients and whip again. Chill.

title: elephant ears
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine all ingredients except cinnamon and sugar; mix well.
Divide dough into 12 pieces.
Let sit 10 minutes.
Roll out on floured board.
Using hands, stretch each piece into circular shape.
Heat oil in 10-inch skillet. Place each piece of dough into hot grease.
Turn once, to lightly brown.
Place on absorbent paper towel.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mix.

title: parmesan potato sticks
directions: Mix the Parmesan cheese, bread crumbs, salt, garlic powder and pepper together.
Dip the potato sticks in butter, then roll in cheese and bread crumb mixture.
Place on cookie sheet.
Drizzle with any leftover butter.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour and shortening. Add nuts.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, slightly brown. Stir occasionally while hot. Cool.
Mix the cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla. Stir into whipped cream. Spread Thank You blueberries or cherries on top.

title: orange pudding
directions: Soak bread in milk/water mixture. Beat egg yolks well. Blend sugar and cornstarch in top of double boiler and cook 15 minutes, stirring often. Add egg yolks and cook 5 more minutes, stirring. Let custard cook and pour over orange sections. Prepare meringue and place on pudding. Put in a 300° oven 12 to 15 minutes. Turn oven off and leave in oven another 15 minutes. Serve chilled.

title: pita pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spread sauce on one side of the unsliced pita bread.
Sprinkle green pepper, mushrooms, onion and black olives over sauce.
Sprinkle cheese over vegetables.
Place on ungreased pizza pan or cookie sheet.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes or until done.

title: moussaka #2
directions: Slice the eggplant, rind and all, 1/4 inch thick.
Salt thoroughly each slice and set aside in large bowl for 20 minutes (this is to remove the poison).

title: watercress soup(great for those cold winter days!  rich in calcium and iron!)
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into even sized pieces.
Put the potatoes, water and stock cubes into a large saucepan.
Wash and chop the watercress.
Reserve 2 tablespoons.
Add the rest to the saucepan together with the stems.
Bring to a boil, then simmer gently for about 15 minutes or until the potatoes are tender.
Let cool a bit, then puree in a blender.
Mix the potato flour or cornmeal with the cream or milk and add this to the soup, stirring.
Simmer the soup for 5 to 10 minutes more.
Add the reserved watercress leaves.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Serves 4.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and squeeze all moisture from spinach.
Place in food processor.
Add remaining ingredients and process until well blended.
Refrigerate for 6 hours or overnight to blend seasonings.

title: she-crab soup
directions: Combine butter and flour, cooking over low heat for 3 to 4 minutes.
Saute celery, carrots and onions.
Heat milk and chicken broth together.
Add butter, flour, seasoning, vegetables and crab meat.
Simmer over low heat for about 30 minutes.
Then add sherry and half and half.
Simmer for another five minutes.

title: deep dish pizza pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients and knead.
Use 1/4-1/2 dough for pizza pie.
Pat 1/2 dough into 9 X 13 pan.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Sift flour with baking powder; add to creamed mixture, 1 spoonful at a time, alternating with milk.
Add vanilla; stir in crushed pineapple and juice and blend well.
Pour batter into well-greased 10-inch tube pan. Place in cold oven.
Turn oven to 325° and bake 1 1/2 hours or until top springs back when touched lightly. Let stand a few minutes in pan.
Run knife around edges and remove carefully to rack.
Combine butter, powdered sugar and about 1 cup drained pineapple.
Cook until clear.
Pour over cake.
Let run down sides.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Blend honey and butter until smooth.
Add the eggs and mix well.
Mix in flour, salt, baking powder and spices, alternating with pumpkin, raisins, and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased baking sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: spaghetti meat loaf
directions: Prepare spaghetti and sauce as directed on package.
Combine spaghetti, 1 cup sauce and the grated Parmesan cheese.
Place in an 8-inch square baking dish. Combine meat, green pepper, mushrooms, egg, onion and seasonings.
Mix lightly. Spread on spaghetti. Top with remaining sauce.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Top with cheese. Put back into oven just to melt cheese. Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken with garlic
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray baking dish with Pam.
Arrange celery on bottom of dish.
Top with chicken and garlic.
Sprinkle with oil, parsley, tarragon and pepper.
Pour wine over all. Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour until chicken is tender.

title: cheese bread
directions: Melt margarine then mix it and all other ingredients.
Stir only enough to mix.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans and soup; place in a baking dish 1/2 the mixture.
Add layer of the onion rings.
Add remaining mixture and top with onions.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well all ingredients and chill overnight.

title: our best bran muffins
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Set aside.
Measure All-Bran cereal and milk into mixing bowl.
Stir to combine.
Let stand 1 to 2 minutes or until cereal is softened. Add egg and shortening. Beat well. Add dry ingredients to cereal mixture, stirring only until combined.
Portion batter evenly into 12 greased 2 1/2-inch muffin pan cups. Bake in oven at 400° for about 25 minutes or until muffins are golden brown.
Serve warm. Yields 12 muffins.

title: maple syrup pie
directions: Beat eggs, flour and butter until smooth.
Add maple syrup and milk; stir.
Blend; pour in pie crust.
Add walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato icebox rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients except eggs and flour; add eggs.
Add flour.
If needed to make the right stiffness, add a little more flour.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Shape and let raise for 2 hours.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Put all ingredients in blender; blend until smooth, about 15 to 20 seconds. Fry in oil.

title: easy chicken and vegetable skillet
directions: Sprinkle tenderloins with salt and black pepper.
Heat butter and oil in large skillet.
Add chicken tenderloins and onion. Cook until chicken is tender.
Sprinkle flour in pan and stir.
Add broth and stir.
Add remaining ingredients (except noodles or rice).
Cover pan and simmer for about 10 minutes. Serve over noodles or rice.

title: b b q ribs
directions: Dip ribs in flour and brown in small amount of oil.
Place ribs in sauce made with remaining ingredients.
Spoon sauce over ribs to make sure they are covered.
Cover pan and simmer at 220° for 1 1/2 hours or more.
Turn ribs once or twice.
Add water as needed, in small amounts.

title: easy burritos
directions: Fry shells in a tablespoon of grease lightly in frypan.
Mix onion and spice with hamburger.
Place 4 tablespoons of meat on each shell and sprinkle with cheese.
Roll shells and place on a cookie sheet.
Pour the can of kidney beans over the shells and then the can of salsa over the kidney beans.
Sprinkle any remaining hamburg over the salsa.
Heat in a 350° oven for 10 minutes and sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Serve.

title: butter cookies with sour cream
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill in refrigerator until firm. Roll out and cut.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a bowl and set aside.

title: rum balls
directions: In large bowl, combine dry ingredients with extract and frosting.
Make balls, using 1 teaspoon measure, being sure mixture is well blended.
Roll balls in powdered sugar.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix oleo with dip.
Mix spinach and dip mixture.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Even spinach haters like this casserole.

title: french onion soup
directions: In large skillet, cook onions in butter until tender, about 20 minutes.
Transfer onions and butter to crockery cooker; add condensed beef broth, water, Worcestershire sauce and pepper. Cover and cook on low heat setting for 4 to 6 hours.
Ladle soup into bowls; garnish with cheese crackers or slices of toasted French bread if desired.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook on medium heat sugar, butter and evaporated milk.
Bring to a boil.
Boil exactly 5 minutes (no longer).
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter, the jar of marshmallow cream and vanilla. Beat until smooth.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: lemon chicken stir fry
directions: Cook chicken and cut into one inch strips or into cubes. Place with pasta. Heat 2 tsp. oil in skillet or stir fry pan. Add carrots and pepper. Stir fry 2-3 minutes, add asparagus and squash. Stir fry 1-2 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender. Whisk water, lemon juice and soup. Mix in small bowl. Add sauce to vegetable mixture. Reduce heat for about 5 minutes until sauce has thickened. Add pasta and chicken, toss to coat. Grate cheese over pasta and enjoy.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Saute hamburger and onion and add remaining ingredients.
Cook well.
Mix 1 cup flour with 1 cup water and simmer until thick to make gravy.
Blend gravy with hamburger mix to complete sauce for hot dogs.

title: raisin puff cookies
directions: Cook raisins and water until water is gone. Set aside to cool. Cream together the oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Add soda, salt and flour. Stir in raisins. Roll in ball and dip in sugar.
Bake at 350° for approximately 8 minutes.

title: rhubarb cherry pie
directions: Line pie pan with pastry.
Put in rhubarb and part of the sugar and tapioca, then put in cherries, food coloring and rest of sugar and tapioca.
Top with lattice crust.
Bake 60 minutes (400° for 15 minutes and 350° for remaining time).

title: cracker jacks
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Mix popcorn and peanuts on a large cookie sheet and place in the oven.
Mix all remaining ingredients in a saucepan over medium heat; stir until boiling.
Bring syrup to hard ball stage (260° on candy thermometer).
This takes 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove popcorn from oven and quickly pour the syrup over it.
Place back in oven for 15 minutes.
Stir, every 5 so that all popcorn is coated.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Brown pork in saucepan.
Add onions and saute until onions are tender.
Add clam
juice and
bring to boiling point.
Add potatoes, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Add clams and milk.
Simmer about 30 minutes.
Do not boil.

title: tuna spread
directions: Blend the cream cheese and other ingredients, except tuna. Add the tuna gradually; beat until well blended.
Pack in small bowl or mold.
Chill for 3 hours.
Serve with snack crackers.

title: party chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, almonds, onion, celery and green pepper.
Mix cream with mayonnaise, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Toss together with chicken.
Add grapes and toss lightly.
Arrange salad greens and top with chicken salad.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked liver and onions
directions: Soak liver for 2 hours at least (can soak overnight) in 6 cups cold water and 1/2 cup vinegar.
Drain in colander and rinse with cold water.
Lay out on paper towels.
Roll each piece of liver in cracker crumbs.
Lay a strip of bacon on waxed paper; lay the cracker crumbed piece of liver on the bacon strip and roll into a ball.
Put liver balls tightly into a lightly greased 8 1/2 x 11-inch glass baking dish.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Place sliced onions on top, recover and bake an additional 15 to 20 minutes or until onions are tender.

title: black magic cake
directions: Combine all dry ingredients together; mix well.
Add all the other ingredients.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes for a long pan; bake for 30 to 35 minutes for round pan.
Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: apricot salad
directions: Combine
Jell-O, sugar and water in a small pan.
Bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve sugar and Jell-O.
Remove from heat. Stir in fruit.
Set aside to cool.

title: squash relish
directions: Mix squash, onions, bell pepper, hot pepper, pimientos and salt together; let stand overnight in plastic container.
Next morning, mix vinegar, sugar and pickle spice, cumin and celery seed tied in cloth.
Put in pan and bring to a boil.
Add mix to squash mixture and boil for 15 minutes.
Put in hot jars and seal.
Ready to eat. Makes 6 quarts.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients and pour in well greased and floured Bundt cake pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese vegetable mix
directions: Bring soup and milk to boil.
Add vegetables and cook on low for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in cheese to melt through.

title: good overnight cookies
directions: Mix well and put in rolls.
Roll each roll in waxed paper so it will not dry out.
Cool overnight and slice into cookies.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: summer casserole
directions: Cook squash in a small amount of boiling water until tender, but still crisp; drain.
Saute onion in butter; add squash, stirring to mix.
Spoon mixture into lightly greased quart baking dish.
Layer with eggs, then cheese, then corn chips.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: heavenly brownies
directions: Beat sugar and eggs together with electric mixer at high speed for 5 minutes.
Add cocoa and flour.
Stir in melted margarine by hand.
Stir in nuts, vanilla and salt.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Ice if desired or dust with powdered sugar.

title: pumpkin surprise
directions: Mix pumpkin, eggs and milk together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Pour melted butter over cake mix.
Top with sprinkled nuts.

title: cheese casserole bread
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Sift flour, sugar and salt in mixing bowl.
With pastry blender, cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add egg, softened yeast and milk; beat well.
Stir in cheese, parsley, oregano and garlic.
Turn into greased casserole dish.
Let rise 45 minutes.
Beat egg and brush top. Sprinkle sesame seeds over egg.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cheater stew
directions: Put all in oven roaster and cover.
Can be baked in slow oven all day or at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: good luck fudge
directions: Boil sugar, milk, cocoa, syrup and butter over medium heat for 4 minutes.
Add nuts and vanilla and beat until cool and starts to thicken.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in butter.
Cut chicken breasts in half; saute with the preceding.
Add remaining ingredients except the vegetables.
Simmer until cheese melts.
In 9 x 13-inch casserole, put vegetables on bottom; cover with chicken mixture. Bake at 350° to heat through, about 1/2 hour.
Longer if taken out of the refrigerator.

title: chinese-style cabbage
directions: Heat shortening in skillet.
Drop in vegetables; stir well. Cover tightly; steam 5 minutes on medium heat, stirring several times.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pork chop potato bake
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides.
Combine soup, sour cream and milk.
Stir in potatoes and add one cup of cheese.
Spread mixture in a greased 3 quart baking dish.
Arrange pork chops on top. Bake, covered in 350 degree oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Sprinkle the rest of the cheese and onion rings on top.
Bake, uncovered for 5 more minutes.
Serves:
6. To serve 4:
use 4 chops and halve the rest of the ingredients.

title: pineapple crumb cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Beat the egg whites and fold in. Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes in long pan.

title: autumn chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, grapes, almonds and oranges in a bowl.
Combine mayonnaise, onion and desired salt.
Add to chicken mixture, stirring gently.
Spoon onto lettuce leaves.
Yields:
4 cups.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken, rice, undrained mixed vegetables and soup in a bowl; mix well.
Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, or until golden brown and bubbly.

title: cherry bars
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, flavorings and eggs; add flour. Spread 3/4 batter on a greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch aluminum cookie sheet.
Add pie filling on top of the batter and then add the rest of the batter.
Dot on top of the pie filling and bake. (Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.) Let cool for 1/2 hour, then drizzle icing back and forth on top of everything.
Let set 1 hour and cut into squares.

title: ham `n' cheese egg loaf
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs until frothy, about 1 minute. Add milk and mustard. Combine the flour, baking powder and salt. Add to egg mixture and beat until smooth. Stir in bacon, ham and cheeses. Transfer into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until golden brown and a toothpick inserted near center comes out clean. Cool 10 to 15 minutes. Run knife around edges of pan to remove. Slice and serve warm. Refrigerate left overs. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: dieter's delight(blender)
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender jar and cover.
Blend at high speed for 30 seconds until thick and foamy.
Pour into small glasses.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Chop fresh broccoli, or layer 1 bag frozen broccoli cuts in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Drain and add pimento.
Layer on sliced water chestnuts, drained.
Spoon cream of celery soup (undiluted) evenly over vegetables.
Prepare 1/2 of an 8-ounce package of Pepperidge Farm stuffing, using 2/3 cup water, 2 tablespoons margarine and 2 cups stuffing mix.
Layer evenly over soup.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, until bubbly.

title: marinated beef chuck roast
directions: Marinate 8 hours on each side in refrigerator.
Cook on grill.

title: cheese straws
directions: Grate cheese with fine grater.
Place grated cheese in refrigerator to keep cold.
Measure flour into a large mixing bowl; mix in cayenne pepper and salt.
Cut butter into small pieces and blend into flour with pastry blender.
Add cheese and continue to blend until the mixture is yellow all the way through. Let stand at room temperature and keep working with fingers.
Put dough in cookie press, using star shape.
Press straws into 2 to 3-inch lengths.
Place about 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 10 to 12 minutes or until straws begin to brown very lightly around the edges.
(Do not overcook.)
Makes about 10 dozen.
Store in tightly covered container between layers of waxed paper.
Cheese straws keep this way for several weeks.
Freeze for longer storage.

title: party franks
directions: Brown onion, garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce in pan. Then add the rest of the ingredients and simmer on low for an hour. Recipe can be doubled.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Drain and set aside.
In a bowl, mix soup, mayonnaise, eggs, cheese and onions.
Fold broccoli into mixture and turn into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter; sprinkle with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Can be made ahead.

title: for eggnog lovers
directions: Whip Egg Beaters and sugar substitute together and combine with 2 types of milk and flavoring. Mix well. Chill overnight if possible. Pour into tumblers and dust with nutmeg. Preparation time: 10 minutes.

title: chow mein
directions: Cook rice.
Prepare and have ready the first 5 ingredients. Combine in a small bowl the next 5 ingredients.
Heat in large skillet the oil.
Add meat; stir-fry just until done.
Remove from heat.
In another skillet, stir-fry in 1 tablespoon oil each vegetable just until slightly cooked.
Add each vegetable to meat skillet after stir-frying.
Just before serving, reheat meat mixture and add sauce.
Cook just until sauce thickens and clears. Serve hot with rice.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk and yeast to dry mixture.
Mix well. Cover and refrigerate.
Punch down.
Pinch off dough.
Roll out and cut.
Let rise 1/2 to 2 hours.
Bake on greased sheet 10 minutes at 375° to 400° degrees.

title: nan seller's pumpkin pies
directions: In blender put pumpkin and milk and blend until smooth. Place all remaining ingredients in mixing bowl
and
mix well, then add pumpkin mixture.
Mix well.
Pour even amounts into 4 (9-inch) unbaked pie shells. Bake at 375° for 40
to
minutes.

title: potato supreme
directions: Cook, peel and cool potatoes.
Grate together potatoes, butter and cheese.
Blend in other ingredients.
Place into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: "no bake" pumpkin pie
directions: Slowly blend together all ingredients, except pie crust.
Pour into a baked and cooled crust.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Top with whipped cream or "Cool Whip" just before serving.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to package directions; drain.
Place in greased baking dish.
Mix onion, celery, cheese and salad dressing.
Sprinkle over vegetables.
Melt butter; mix with crushed crackers.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dad's "yummy" brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease (well) a 13 x 9-inch pan with margarine.
Crush graham crackers until they are very fine crumbs. Stir in condensed milk and chocolate chips.
Spoon and press into greased pan.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Allow to cool slightly, then remove promptly.

title: taco chili
directions: Brown beef with diced onion and celery. Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.

title: walnut cheese ball
directions: In small mixing bowl, soften cream cheese and blend in sherry. Add butter, cheese spread and horseradish; mix well.
Cover; chill thoroughly about 4 hours.
Shape into a ball and roll in walnuts.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: szechuan noodle toss
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain.
Place spaghetti in a large salad bowl; set aside.
Heat 2 tablespoons sesame oil in a large skillet.
Add red pepper, green onions and garlic; saute 2 minutes.
Stir in spinach; cover and cook over medium heat 3 minutes or until spinach wilts. Remove from heat; cool.
Spoon mixture over pasta.
Add chicken and water chestnuts.
Combine remaining 2 tablespoons sesame oil, soy sauce and remaining ingredients; stir well.
Pour over pasta; toss gently to coat.
Yields 6 servings.

title: six layer dinner
directions: Slice potatoes to cover bottom of greased baking dish.
Pour the uncooked rice over the potatoes.
Brown the ground beef in a skillet; spread over rice.
Spread the onions over the meat, then the green peppers.
Pour the tomatoes over all.
Season as desired.
Bake in a slow oven at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: egg dip
directions: Chop eggs fine; combine with remaining ingredients.
Chill until served.

title: jane's peasant pasta
directions: In a saucepan, saute onions in olive oil until softened.
Add the chicken or beef and brown over medium heat.
Put tomatoes through a mill and add to mixture.
Season to taste.
Simmer uncovered approximately 20 minutes.
Add peas, lower heat and cook an additional 10 minutes.
Cook and drain pasta according to directions.
Toss pasta with sauce, sprinkle with cheese and serve. Yields 4 servings.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Meanwhile, soften yeast in the warm water.
In a large bowl put sugar and shortening.
Pour milk over sugar and shortening.
When lukewarm, add 1 cup flour; mix well.
Beat in eggs.
Beat in remaining flour.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface; allow to set 5 to 10 minutes.
Knead; form dough into a large ball and place in deep greased bowl.
Turn dough to bring greased surface to top.
Cover with towel or lid.
Let rise until dough is doubled, about 1 hour.

title: chocolate snowballs
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla. Mix well.
Combine flour and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture. Fold in nuts and chips.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool cookies slightly before rolling them in confectioners sugar. Yields about 4 dozen.

title: uncle charly's cornbread
directions: Lightly grease 9 to 10-inch skillet. Heat skillet in 400° oven until hot. Mix together all ingredients. Pour batter into hot pan and cook at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown and firm to touch.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all together.
Refrigerate.
Serve with plate of fresh fruit.

title: hobo bread
directions: Put raisins, cold water and soda in bowl and soak overnight. Add remaining ingredients together and mix.
Pour into 1 one pound coffee can and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tropical punch
directions: Serves 25 to 30.

title: 4 layer chocolate pudding dessert
directions: Mix together and spread in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.

title: turkey turnovers
directions: Melt butter and blend with flour.
Add milk while stirring, keeping mixture smooth.
Add meat and seasoning, heat until mixture thickens.
Cool.
Roll pastry 1/8-inch thick and cut out 24 pieces allowing 2 pieces for each turnover.
Place one piece on baking sheet and 1 heaping tablespoon of meat filling.
Moisten edge with cold water and cover with second piece of pastry.
Crimp edges with fork and prick each turnover to allow steam to escape. Bake at 450°
about 20 minutes or until brown.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: bell pepper relish
directions: Grind vegetables, saving the juice.
Add other ingredients. Cook 30 minutes on medium heat.
Put in jars and seal.

title: chocolate banana nut bundt cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter a 10-inch Bundt pan and dust with flour.
Toss the chips and nuts with 2 tablespoons of the flour and set aside.

title: butter crunch
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar. Return to heat and wait for sugar and butter to bubble.
Add water and syrup.
Mix well.
Cook over low heat for 15 to 20 minutes (hard crack stage).
Remove from heat.
Add nuts.
Pour on lightly greased baking sheet.
Spread to 1/4-inch thick.
Spread melted chocolate over the top of the crunch as it begins to harden. Sprinkle nuts over chocolate, if desired.

title: seven-up salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix the cream cheese, water and jello until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: orange no-bake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except coconut in large bowl with hands. Shape cookies; roll in coconut.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Mix soups and milk in bowl; set aside.
Brown hamburger and onion in skillet; add soup mixture.
In long cake pan, layer 2 tortillas; pour 1/2 mixture and sprinkle 1/2 cheese; repeat layers.
Top with cheese.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 400°.
I also use it as a dip with Doritos.
If used as a dip, omit tortillas and do not bake, just heat on top of stove until hot through.

title: tamale pie
directions: Prepare Vegetable Filling.
In a large skillet, heat oil; add onion and green pepper.
Saute until onion is transparent.
Stir in corn, beans, tomatoes, vegetable juice cocktail, fresh cilantro (if desired), the chili powder, cumin and salt.
Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Place filling in a 2-quart casserole dish. Excellent with Cornbread Topping.

title: enchiladas
directions: Heat oil in a large frying pan.
Heat enchilada sauce in a separate saucepan.
Dip the tortillas (one at a time) in the hot oil to soften; then dip them in the hot enchilada sauce.
Fill each tortilla with the cheese and onion; then roll up.
Place each side by side in a long baking dish.
Place the remaining cheese, onion and sauce over the top of the rolls and bake at 400° for about 20 minutes (or until the cheese has melted).

title: skillet meatball stew
directions: In large bowl, mix beef, crumbs, onion, egg, 1 teaspoon bouillon, 1/4 teaspoon thyme and pepper. Form into balls. In a large skillet, brown meatballs in oil; remove from skillet. Stir flour into drippings until smooth. Cook and stir until brown. Add water, remaining bouillon granules and 1/4 teaspoon thyme. Bring to a boil, stirring. Add meat, potatoes, carrots and celery. Cover. Simmer 35 minutes. Add green onions. Cook 5 minutes. Serve.

title: layered garden salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, Miracle Whip and sugar together.
Spread over first 5 layered ingredients.
Add 4 ounces grated Cheddar cheese. Crumble 6 to 8 slices crisp bacon over cheese.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: crab bisque soup
directions: In the
top
of
the
double
boiler blend flour with a little cream
until
smooth.
Slowly
stir
rest
of cream and bring to a "just boil" over direct heat, stirring constantly. Stir in crabmeat and rest of ingredients.
Serves 6.

title: fruit slices
directions: Cut together like pie crust the flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and shortening.
Add the egg and milk mixture to the crust. Roll out 1/2 of dough; place in jelly roll pan (10 x 15-inch). Spread the fruit filling over the bottom crust; cover with top crust.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour, or until lightly browned. Frost with powdered sugar glaze.

title: seafood fettucine
directions: Melt 1 to 2 tablespoons butter in frypan.
Saute scallops and shrimp until done, 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from pan and reserve. Saute onions, garlic and mushrooms in 1 to 2 tablespoons butter until tender.
Remove and reserve with seafood.
Melt cube butter in large pan, add flour, salt and pepper, stirring constantly, so it doesn't lump.
Slowly add milk, stirring constantly, until mixture bubbles and is of medium-thin consistency.
Add seafood and onion-garlic mixture.
Toss with cooked fettucine.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: kedgeree
directions: Cook rice and drain.
Flake the salmon.
Add to the rice and leave for 5 minutes to steam through.
Turn into a serving dish and sprinkle first with finely chopped parsley and then with chopped hard-boiled egg.

title: jambalaya (rice cooker)(club member: lee higginbotham)
directions: Brown meat of choice (ground, round, roast or sausage).
Add all ingredients in rice cooker. Press cooking cycle.
May use cooked leftover meat!

title: squash casserole
directions: Put 1/2 of bread mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread squash mixture over.
Top with remaining bread mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: triopeta
directions: Crumble Feta cheese in large bowl.
Add cottage cheese, then flour.
Beat cream cheese and eggs; add to mixture.
Use 11 x 16-inch cookie sheet.
Butter and add 8 sheets of filo to bottom. Add filling and place 10 more buttered sheets of filo on top. Score with knife and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder and baking soda.
Stir in mayonnaise, add water and vanilla.
Mix well.
Put into 2 round pans or a 13 x 9-inch pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until tester comes out clean.
Frost with your favorite icing.

title: muffins or corn sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease skillet or pan and preheat. Beat egg in bowl; then add remaining ingredients and blend well. Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes one 9-inch skillet or one 9-inch square pan.
(Batter should be creamy and pourable.
If too thick, add a little more liquid.)

title: good healthy gravy
directions: Note:
It's really easy to make healthy gravy for your mashed potatoes, open-faced hot roast beef sandwiches, turkey and meat loaves.
Here's the scoop.

title: quick bean dip
directions: Heat together all ingredients in microwave.

title: low-fat turkey and macaroni salad
directions: Use lemon juice to cook turkey, then put macaroni in with turkey.
Next, add spaghetti sauce.
Add all other ingredients. Stir and let simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs and flavorings.
Cream all together well.
Add flour and milk.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Let cake cool before removing from pan.

title: zucchini bread or 24 muffins
directions: Mix liquid ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients together; mix until combined thoroughly.
Grease and flour bread loaf pans or muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: homemade noodles
directions: In a bowl, place flour.
Make a well.
Drop in remaining ingredients.
Mix with fork, then fingers until it forms stiff dough.
Roll out very thin on floured surface.
Cut as you desire. Drop into hot beef or chicken broth or potato soup and cook.
If broth is weak, may add bouillon cube for more flavor.

title: snappers
directions: Arrange pecan halves on a greased baking sheet, flat sides down in groups of four.
Center one vanilla caramel atop each cluster of pecans.
Heat in a 325° oven until caramels soften (about 7 to 8 minutes).
Remove from oven and with a buttered spatula, flatten caramels over pecans.
Cool slightly; remove from pan to waxed paper.
Spread tops with melted semi-sweet chocolate.

title: lemon squares(chewy)
directions: Prepare the day before.
Cut butter into flour until it makes small balls.
Pat out into ungreased 12 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Beat eggs.
Add brown sugar, coconut, baking powder and vanilla.
Spread over baked base. Return to oven and bake for 27 minutes.
Blend powdered sugar, lemon rind and juice.

title: spanish casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Melt 1 stick margarine.
Pour over stuffing.
Sprinkle stuffing mixture on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: lace cookies
directions: Dump all together in a bowl and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into powdered sugar, covering well with sugar. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake about 12 minutes at 350°.

title: crab bisque(low-fat)
directions: In 3-quart microwave casserole, place mushrooms and white wine.
Cover and microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes, or until mushrooms are tender, stirring once.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Blend in milk.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 9 to 12 minutes, or until mixture thickens slightly and bubbles, stirring 2 to 3 times with a whisk.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and microwave on High 3 to 5 minutes, or until hot, stirring once. Makes 6 (1 cup) servings.

title: mexican layer dip
directions: *Sargento makes a 4 cheese Mexican blend.

title: chinese beef with string beans
directions: Prepare all ingredients before starting to cook the dish. Clean the beans and string, if necessary.
Cut into crosswise halves.
Trim the flank steak of all fat and slice across the grain into paper-thin slices.
Mix the soy sauce, sherry and cornstarch together and set aside.	Grate the ginger.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix mayonnaise, chili sauce, olives, chives, egg, paprika, salt and pepper.
Chill well.
Serve with green salads.
Makes 3/4 cup.

title: chicken broccoli bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare stuffing according to package directions; set aside.
In 2-quart greased casserole combine soup, sour cream, broccoli and chicken.
Top with prepared stuffing; cover and bake 30 minutes.
Remove cover and sprinkle with cheese. Bake 5 minutes more until cheese is melted.
Yields 4 servings.

title: new england mountain pancakes
directions: In a bowl mix milk, oil, eggs and wheat germ.
In a larger bowl, mix all dry ingredients.
Combine both bowls together, mixing thoroughly.
Add vanilla extract and mix well.
Bake on hot griddle (greased).
Turn over when top side is bubbly.
If you prefer thinner pancakes, increase milk, for thicker pancakes, decrease milk.

title: beefy bean-a-roni
directions: Cook ground beef until browned.
Add celery, cook until celery is transparent; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients except cheese.
Pour into 1 1/2 qt. casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with cheese at last 10 minutes of cooking.

title: one dish breakfast
directions: Place slices of bread in bottom of casserole dish.
Sprinkle cooked sausage over bread, then sprinkle grated cheese over sausage.
Mix well beaten eggs with half and half and pour over bread, sausage and cheese.
Cook in oven for approximately 30 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook peppers, celery and onions in some of the broth until tender.
Add chili powder and continue simmering.
Cook noodles in remaining broth and add to chicken mixture.
Add other ingredients and bake in a casserole for 30 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.
Garlic may be omitted.

title: gwen's apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease well and flour one 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a large bowl, measure the flours and the sugar, oil, eggs, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla extract. Beat until well mixed.
(This is hard work, but worth it.)
Keep beating until well mixed.
Sometimes I get my hands right in the bowl and mix.
It's good for me and it doesn't hurt the cake. Anyway, next, you stir in the apples, nuts and currants.
(You can use raisins, but chop them first.)
Spread batter evenly into pan. Bake 1 hour or until cake is golden brown. Cool cake in pan on wire rack about 10 minutes. Remove from pan and cool completely on rack. Wrap and refrigerate.
Or eat it while it is hot with fresh butter. Enjoy.

title: oatmeal crust
directions: Combine, mix and press into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Cool, chill or freeze.
Fill with pudding, rice dream, or as desired.

title: stir-fry broccoli and mushrooms
directions: In large skillet or wok, heat 2 tablespoons Canola oil over medium heat.
Add mushrooms; saute, stirring constantly, for 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove from pan; set aside.

title: mexican dinner
directions: Brown hamburger and drain. Add taco seasoning and enough water to cover bottom of pan. Set simmer until water is gone. Add chicken soup and Ro-tel tomatoes. Heat on low until warm. Cut tortillas into 1/4's begin with a little filling to cover bottom of baking dish, then add tortillas and cheese and more filling. Repeat layers. Sprinkle cheese on top. Heat in 350° oven until warm and cheese is melted.

title: velvet salad
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in 1 c. boiling water.
Dissolve Marshmallows in 1 c. hot water.
Combine and add the cream cheese, pineapple and Miracle Whip and whipped cream.
Pour into an oblong pan (8x13-inch) or individual molds; chill until firm.

title: striped delight
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, sugar, and butter.
Press firmly into 9 x 13 greased pan.
Beat cream cheese with sugar and milk until smooth.
Fold in half the cool whip and spread over crust.
Prepare pudding using 3
1/2 cups milk.
Pour over cheese layer.
Chill several hours.
Spread rest of cool whip on top.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix together the sugar, cocoa and milk in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Continue boiling for 2 minutes. Then add peanut butter, salt and oleo.
Take off heat. Add oatmeal and vanilla. Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper and cool.

title: frozen lemon squares
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and crumbs; press into an 8 or 9-inch square pan.
In bowl, beat egg yolks.
Stir in milk, then lemon juice and food coloring if desired.
Pour mixture over crust.
Top with whipped topping.
Freeze until firm.

title: microwave chocolate candy
directions: Line an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan with foil.
Sift together sugar and cocoa into a 2-quart baking dish.
Add milk and butter; do not stir.
Place in microwave oven for 2 1/2 minutes or until butter just melts.
Add vanilla.
Stir until all ingredients are well blended.
Turn fudge into aluminum foil lined pan.
Smooth top.
Place in freezer for 10 minutes to set.
Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: texas bugs in a log
directions: Fill trimmed and chilled celery stalks with cream cheese and top with peanut butter.
Add a swarm of raisins (Texas Bugs).

title: cracker jacks
directions: Mix
first 4 ingredients; boil 5 minutes.
Add soda and vanilla;
mix
mixture
with
popped popcorn.
Cook in oven at 175° to 200° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and clean chicken off bones and skin.
Then mix in soup and sour cream.
Season to taste.
Put in an 8 x 8-inch casserole dish.
Prepare Stove Top as directed and spread on top of chicken mixture.
Bake until heated through, about 20 minutes.

title: rhubarb chiffon pie
directions: Cook together the rhubarb and water.
Then add sugar, eggs and cornstarch.
Put into 2 baked pie shells.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: raisin cream pie
directions: Put raisins in colander; pour boiling water over.
Combine eggs, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt, lemon juice and margarine. Mix thoroughly by hand (do not use mixer).
In unbaked pie shell, pour raisins and nuts.
Pour egg mixture into unbaked pastry shell over nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until set in center.

title: dutch potatoes
directions: Peel and core potatoes.
Put wiener in center of each.
Place in baking pan with drippings.
Add milk.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: praline pecans and cranberries
directions: Preheat oven to 250°. Grease bottom of 13 x 9 pan. Set aside. Cover large baking sheet with heavy-duty foil. Set aside. Spread pecans in single layer in prepared baking pan.

title: no bake pumpkin pie
directions: In a small bowl, blend milk, egg, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt.
Set aside.
In a medium saucepan, sprinkle unflavored gelatin over water; let stand 1 minute. Stir over low heat until gelatin is completely dissolved, about 2 minutes.
Blend in milk mixture. Continue stirring over low heat until mixture is slightly thickened, about 5 minutes. Blend in pumpkin. Turn into prepared crust. Chill until firm.
Add whipped cream, if desired.

title: rice and corn casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
Add remaining ingredients; heat through.
Serve.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Turn oven on to 350°.
Beat until stiff, but not dry the salt and egg whites.
Fold in nuts and chocolate chips or Chinese noodles, Spanish peanuts, etc.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheets.
(I use greased wax paper on my cookie sheets.) Put in oven and turn oven off.
Leave overnight.

title: easy beef cabbage casserole
directions: Chop the cabbage, salt and pepper to taste.
Place in a greased 9x13 baking dish.
Brown ground beef with chopped onion, drain.
Stir in uncooked rice. Place meat and rice mixture on cabbage, salt and pepper again to taste.
Cover with tomato soup and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Mix the Jell-O into the cottage cheese and pineapple. Add nuts if desired. Chill overnight.

title: mediterranean feta dip
directions: Mix dry soup mix, sour cream, cucumber, Feta, onion and oregano.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: miniature pizzas
directions: Flatten one biscuit to a thickness of approximately 1/4-inch. Then slice the sausage to 1/2-inch wedges.
Lay sausage on flattened biscuit and flatten to cover biscuit.
Then roll up until sausage is covered.
Slice roll into 1/2 to 3/4-inch wedges.
Lay wedges onto a cookie sheet or flat pan, sprayed with Pam.
Flatten wedges and add pizza sauce to each wedge.
Add other toppings at this time.
Place cookie sheet into a preheated 400° oven and cook for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool and enjoy. (One can of biscuits will make about 40 pizzas.)

title: curried fruit
directions: Melt butter; add brown sugar and curry powder.
When melted, add the fruit and bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour.
Stir two or three times.
Refrigerate overnight.
The next day warm again in oven.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O and let set.
Add the remaining ingredients.

title: italian roast beef
directions: Place roast and all ingredients in crock-pot. Cook all day on LOW or 1/2 day on high.

title: pork chop suey
directions: Brown pork in oil.
Add and saute onions, celery and mushrooms for 3 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with 1/4 cup of water.
Add salt, molasses and soy sauce with remainder of water.
Mix altogether and pour over meat.
Cook slowly, covered, until tender (can use slow cooker) or on top of stove.
Add and heat the chop suey vegetables.
Serve over rice.
Top with Chinese noodles.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli casserole 2
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Heat soup (undiluted).
Add cheese, mayonnaise and egg. Heat until well blended.
Arrange drained broccoli in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Pour sauce over broccoli.
Dot with margarine and top with crumbs.
Bake until bubbly.

title: quick quiche
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a 10-inch pie plate. Sprinkle meat/vegetables, onions and cheese in pie plate.
Beat salt, milk, biscuit mix and eggs together until smooth.
Pour milk mixture into pie plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean (30 to 35 minutes).
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: rhubarb meringue dessert
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix margarine, sugar and flour.
Press in an ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: ribbon cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat until blended.
Line a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with wax paper.
Spoon 1/3 of dough into a small bowl.
Add almond extract and 5 drops red food coloring.
Stir until blended. Spread evenly into prepared pan.
Spoon half of remaining dough into small bowl.
Stir in nuts.
Spread evenly over dough in pan. Melt chocolate.
Stir into remaining dough.
Spread evenly over dough in pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: continental chicken
directions: Arrange beef on bottom of greased crock-pot.
Wrap each boned chicken piece with a bacon strip and place on top of the dried beef.
Mix the soup and sour cream together.
Pour over chicken. Cover and cook on low for 7 to 9 hours or high for 3 to 4 hours. Serve over hot buttered noodles.
Makes 8 servings.

title: oatmeal crisps
directions: Cream together shortening and sugars; add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Add and mix in the flour, salt and soda.
Mix in oats, nuts and raisins or chips; mix well.
Chill dough.

title: never fail pound cake
directions: Beat sugar and Crisco until creamy.
Add eggs and beat well one at a time.
Add other ingredients and beat well.
Bake at 325° 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Do not open oven door for first hour while cake is cooking.

title: coconut quickie
directions: Mix the vanilla with condensed milk.
Add coconut.
Grease and flour a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: grandma's green salad
directions: Place in bowl.
Add 2 cups boiling water and beat until foamy. Refrigerate until slightly hardened.
Whip again.
Add large can crushed pineapple and Cool Whip.
Garnish with maraschino cherries and nuts if desired.
Chill until hardened.

title: coconut delight
directions: Mix and spread in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the Crisco, margarine, sugar and salt.
Add beaten egg, vanilla and milk.
Mix flour and baking powder into the creamed mixture.
Chill.
Roll out fairly thin on floured board and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: jello fruit salad
directions: Mix according to instructions on box, using 7-Up instead of the water, which gives jello a real twang to whatever you put into the jello (fruit or vegetables). Chill until serving.

title: yogurt pops
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine yogurt and grape juice concentrate; stir well. Pour into small frozen pop molds or 5-ounce wax coated paper cups, filling 3/4 full and freeze (about 1 hour), then insert Popsicle sticks. Tear off cups when frozen solid.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together sugar, mayonnaise, egg, water and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and cocoa.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: manicotti
directions: Brown meat in large skillet.
Add onion, garlic and celery. Saute.
Add next 4 seasonings.
Set aside.
Boil manicotti with a little oil in water to keep noodles from sticking together according to directions.
Do not overboil.

title: neiman marcus cake
directions: Combine ingredients in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: quik chocolate pie
directions: Combine in saucepan beaten eggs, sugar, milk, cornstarch and Quik.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, stir constantly. Pour into baked pie shell, then top with meringue.

title: bubble pizza
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Brown beef in a large skillet over medium heat until no longer pink. While meat cooks, open tube of biscuits and cut each biscuit into sixths.
Spray a 10 inch deep dish pie plate or 9 inch square baking pan.
When beef is done, drain well and return to pan.
Stir in pizza sauce, seasonings, and other optional items if desired.
Spoon sauce evenly over the top and bake for 12-15 minutes, until biscuits are cooked through and cheese is melted.
Remove from oven and allow to set 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 4-6 servings.

title: roasted garlic turnips
directions: To roast garlic: cut the bottom off a medium head of garlic, place on a square of aluminum foil, and drizzle 1/2 t olive oil over it.
Seal and bake at 375 F approximately 30 minutes.
Garlic should be very soft.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel, core and chop apples and immediately toss them in a bowl with lemon juice.
In a separate bowl combine brown sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg and stir into apples.
Set aside.

title: corn souffle casserole(the most delicate flavor!)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs and add most of milk and the corn in a mixing bowl.
Add floured mixed well with reserved milk. Add sugar and salt.
In deep casserole dish (Pyrex or Corning Ware), melt your butter.
Then add your corn mixture.
Bake in a slow oven at 325° to 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve immediately. A delicate taste.

title: fritters
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Add milk gradually and well beaten eggs. This may be used as a foundation for all fritters; one tablespoon sugar should be added if fruits are used.

title: chicken and dumplings(an old southern favorite.)
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder into large bowl. Blend in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk; mix well.
If too dry, add 1 teaspoon more milk.
Mixture should be consistency of biscuit dough.

title: black beans
directions: Heat olive oil.
Add onion, pepper and bay leaf.
Cook until translucent.
Add black beans and water.
Simmer 10 minutes. Serves 6.

title: beef casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cut steak into bite-size pieces. Combine all ingredients, except sour cream, in a 2-quart casserole and cover tightly.
Bake for 3 hours.
Stir in sour cream and serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 6.

title: beet soup
directions: Add all ingredients, except sour cream.
Simmer until ingredients are tender.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine and saute onion.
Add broccoli and simmer a little.
Add soup and cheese.
Simmer until cheese is melted.
Add rice and mix well.
Bake in casserole dish at 350°
for 25 to 30 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: diet lasagna
directions: Saute onion and ground meat.
Add seasonings, tomato sauce and mushrooms.
Squeeze liquid from thawed spinach and mix with cottage cheese.
Cut Mozzarella cheese in strips.
In a 7 x 11-inch baking dish, arrange in layers the spinach mix, meat mix and Mozzarella; repeat.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Serves 4.

title: won-tons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place Won-Ton wrappers in muffin pan and bake until starting to brown. Only takes a few minutes. Mix together, sausage and Hidden Valley Ranch. Stir in cheese. Pour mixture into baked Won-Tons. Sprinkle some cheese over top. Bake until cheese melts.

title: parmesan baked chicken
directions: Mix onion rings, cheese, paprika, bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Beat egg with milk.
Dip chicken in egg mixture and roll in crumb mixture.
Place in dish.
Pour melted butter over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cover with foil first 30 minutes, then uncover last 30 minutes.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix.
Shape in loaf.
If it seems dry, add more milk.
Slice onion on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Baste occasionally with water or chicken broth.
Serve with Mustard Sauce.

title: chicken salad
directions: Toss apples with vinegar in bowl to coat thoroughly; set aside.
Drain when ready to mix with other ingredients.
Combine sugar, cinnamon, pepper and mayonnaise; stir into apples.
Add chicken and mix.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Mix together milk, salt and baking powder.
Add to creamy mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Bake at 250° for 1/2 hour.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add beaten eggs and creamed corn.
Mix well.
Slowly add milk and mix all well.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Crumble corn flakes and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 400° for 60 minutes or until center doesn't jiggle.

title: sweet potatoes with apples
directions: Mix together in saucepan sugar, cornstarch, salt, margarine and hot water.
Stir over medium heat until thick.
Put sweet potatoes and apples in layers in buttered casserole dish.
Pour sauce over.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until sweet potatoes are tender.

title: lemon sponge pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add butter, juice, lemon peel and egg yolks, then scalded milk.
Fold in egg whites.
Set in a 1 1/2-quart buttered pan in hot water.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Serves 4 to 6.

title: almond roca cookies
directions: Mix first six ingredients together in order.
Pat in bottom of cookie sheet with sides.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Immediately spread chocolate chips over; after they have melted, sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Cut into diamond shapes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: In a large bowl, combine 2 cups flour and yeast. In small saucepan, combine milk, water, the 1/2 cup sugar, oil and salt. Heat. Stir over medium heat until just warm. Add milk mixture and egg yolks to dry mixture. Beat with electric mixer on low speed for 30 seconds, scraping sides of bowl often. Beat on high speed for 3 minutes. Using a wooden spoon, stir in as much remaining flour as you can. Turn dough onto flat surface. Knead in enough flour for soft dough, 3 to 5 minutes. Cover for 10 minutes. Roll out into rectangle. Spread with softened butter. Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon. Roll up. Slice into 12 parts. Put into greased 9 x 13 pan. Cover. Let rise 20 minutes. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: tamale casserole
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Grease and flour a 2 or 3-quart baking dish.
Lightly brown meat; drain.
Add garlic powder, seasoned salt, chili powder and tomato paste; mix well.
Stir in water. Gently fold in beans and corn.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes, stirring often.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer chicken and soup in casserole dish, starting and ending with soup.
Toss bread crumbs with margarine.
Spread crumbs over chicken mixture.
Bake covered at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Uncover and bake for 10 minutes.

title: long valley elk chili
directions: In a large Dutch oven, put vegetable oil, onion, green peppers, garlic and ground elk.
Brown until meat turns gray.
Add all seasonings except cornstarch/flour and mix well.
Add tomato juice and crushed tomatoes.
Let simmer for 45 minutes.
Add beans and simmer 15 minutes more.
Mix cornstarch with 1/4 cup water and slowly add to pot until thickened.
Put into bowls and sprinkle with shredded Monterey Jack cheese; serve with crackers. Serves 8 to 10.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add other ingredients.
Bring to a boil and let simmer for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: marinated fruit salad
directions: Pare, core and slice apples and pears.
Halve, peel, pit and slice peaches.
Cut pineapple into chunks.

title: okoshi(puffed rice)
directions: Put margarine, Karo syrup, peanuts and sugar in a large pot. Cook on medium-high heat until mixture just begins to caramelize and turns light brown in color (approximately 10 to 13 minutes). Add Puffed Rice cereal and toss to coat evenly.
Spread in roasting pan.
Cut while still warm.

title: pizza
directions: Put yeast and warm water in warm place; let bubble for 10 minutes.
Add sugar, salt, oil and flour.
Stir and knead lightly. Let rise 20 to 30 minutes.
Pat out very thinly with edges on the sides on a cookie pan or pizza pan, greased.

title: one dish meal
directions: Chop celery, onion and green pepper together.
Brown meat in skillet.
Arrange in layers the potatoes, rice, celery and meat. Season each layer with salt and pepper. Pour tomatoes over all. Put bread crumbs on top.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: skillet candied sweet potatoes
directions: Mix in skillet brown sugar, butter, water and salt.
Cook until mixture boils; add sweet potatoes.
Cook slowly, stirring occasionally, until potatoes get caramelly (about 20 minutes).

title: wheat germ cornbread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients well.
Beat eggs, combine with rest of wet and dry ingredients, just until they are mixed.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with sesame seed. Bake in preheated 350° oven about 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool slightly before cutting.

title: barbecue in a biscuit
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add brown sugar and 1/2 to 3/4 of bottle of barbecue sauce.
Let simmer for 4 to 5 minutes.
Place biscuits in muffin pan; press each one as flat as possible.
Spoon beef mixture in each muffin cup.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: rumtopf with ice cream* * * * *
directions: This is also called "Worthy Sauce".
You are supposed to give a starter to someone you think is worthy of it.
I had a friend from Oklahoma who joined the Mormon Church and quit drinking and smoking.
She couldn't think of anyone more worthy than she was, so she ate it all herself.

title: asparagus lasagna bianco
directions: Cook noodles, drain and cut in half crosswise.
In saucepan, cook garlic and thyme in oleo.
Blend in flour.
Cook and stir 2 minutes.
Stir in milk; stir and cook until thick.
Season with salt and pepper.
In buttered dish, layer 1/3 noodles, sauce, cheese, ham and asparagus.
Repeat twice.
Cover and microwave on High for 9 to 10 minutes, turning twice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: "gramma's coconut cookie delights"
directions: Cream sugars and margarine.
Add eggs, vanilla, baking soda and salt and mix.
Add flour and mix.
Add coconut; mix all together.

title: cuban black bean soup
directions: Spray pot with Pam.
Soak beans in water.
Cover overnight. Drain.
Add enough water to cover.
Add bay leaf and jalapeno. Cover pot.
Bring to boil.
Turn to very low and simmer. Partially cover for 2 hours.
In skillet, heat oil and onions. Stir in garlic.
Cook a little more.
When beans are tender, add onion mixture to beans.
Season with salt.
Simmer for 20 minutes. Serve with rice and onions.

title: dump cake
directions: This cake can be made in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan or a 1 piece tube pan.
The "dump" method is to simply dump in the ingredients.
Do not stir.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Break half of crackers in crust and add cinnamon and cream of tartar.
Mix together sugar and water.
Pour most of it over crackers.
Let crackers soak a few minutes, then add rest of liquid.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and bake until well done.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Combine the first four ingredients until crumbly,
press into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour one-half of mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass cake pan or dish.
Let set in refrigerator, then spread a layer of sour cream over set mixture (soften the sour cream with several gentle mixing strokes).
Pour remaining one-half of Jell-O mixture over sour cream.
Let set in refrigerator. Serve.

title: ham and cheese pockets
directions: Prepare bread dough according to instructions through the first raising.
Punch down dough and divide into 16 equal pieces.
Shape pieces into round balls and flatten.
Place one piece of ham and one piece of cheese onto each dough.
Bring dough up and around ham and cheese, shaping into a ball.
Seal dough carefully.
Place on baking sheet.
Cover.
Leave in warm place to rise until double. Butter tops of rolls and place in preheated 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until tops are golden.
Cool slightly before serving.

title: mexican layer dip
