directions: Layer refried beans and cheese; microwave for 1 to 2 minutes until cheese melts.
On top of cheese, layer salsa, sour cream, black olives and then tomatoes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chocolate candy pie
directions: Combine melted chocolate bars and water that has been mixed with instant coffee and melted chocolate.
Stir well and add Cool Whip.
Beat until mixed well.
Add to crust.
Freeze approximately 6 hours.
Serve.

title: frozen lemon dessert
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and gradually beat in sugar.
Add the lemon juice, peel and salt.

title: aunt eileen's lemon-lime chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in a shallow bowl.
Mix garlic, salt, sugar, mustard, vinegar, lime and lemon juices, blending well. Whisk in olive oil; add pepper.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate, preferably overnight, at least a few hours. Remove from refrigerator an hour before cooking to come to room temperature.
Grill for 4 minute per side or until done.
(Do not overcook as this will toughen chicken.)
These may also be cooked under the broiler for same amount of time.
Easily doubled.

title: sweet cherry mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water; then add cold water.
Drain cherries and pineapple; add juice to gelatin mixture.
Place fruit in bottom of ring mold.
Pour half of slightly thickened gelatin over fruit.
Chill.
Whip cream; add cream cheese and whip until blended.
Add remaining gelatin; mix well.
Pour on top of chilled fruit mold.
Chill overnight.
Yields 8 servings.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: On waxed paper, stir together flour and baking powder.
Set aside.

title: cinnamon apple muffins
directions: Mix and place in greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Combine, then add nuts.
Fill greased loaf pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
This will make 2 large loaves, 4 small loaves or 12 cupcakes.
Can serve with lemon sauce, plain or with whipped cream.

title: chicken oregano
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Arrange chicken on foil covered baking sheet.
Brush with oil mixture.
Broil 1/2 hour each side, brushing often.
Serve hot or cold.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Cut beef across grain into thin strips.
Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger.
Add beef.
Toss and set aside.
Heat oil in wok.
Add beef and toss over high heat until browned.
Cook on low heat until tender, about 30 to 40 minutes.
Turn up heat and add vegetables.
Toss until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Mix cornstarch with water.
Stir and cook until thickened.
Add tomatoes and heat.
Serve over boiled rice.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Heat oil at medium heat.
Add onions and cook until soft, about 6 to 8 minutes.
Stir in garlic and green pepper.
Saute for 2 minutes.
Blend flour, add sauce and simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in water, thyme, parsley, shrimp, salt, pepper and cayenne.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: creamy tacos
directions: Brown beef with onion.
Melt cheese.
Add all other ingredients.
Can be kept warm in crock-pot.
Serve over corn chips.

title: impossible pie
directions: Place ingredients in a blender and beat for 2 minutes.
Pour in greased pie tin.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: garden frittata
directions: Steam broccoli and carrots for 10 minutes.
Beat together eggs, Egg Beaters, cottage cheese, salt and pepper.
Stir in carrots and broccoli and mushrooms.
Spray 10-inch round pan with Pam.
Pour in egg mixture.
Bake at 350° until eggs are cooked and knife inserted in center comes out almost clean.
Top with tomatoes; sprinkle with Parmesan.
Broil 1 to 2 minutes.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Mix everything together and put in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Peel, core and dice apples.
Place in a bowl and add eggs and mix.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured pan and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done in a 325° oven.

title: frozen banana salad
directions: Combine ingredients well.
Freeze.
Cut into squares; serve on lettuce.

title: chicken salad
directions: Blend together the curry powder, salt, mayonnaise, cream and onion.
Add to all other ingredients, except almonds.
Chill for 4 or 5 hours.
Sprinkle almonds on top before serving.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend all ingredients and chill before serving.
Serve with fresh fruit, apple wedges or strawberries.

title: milk chocolate pie
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Add well beaten egg yolks and mix (reserve whites for meringue and set aside).
Add margarine and canned milk with enough regular milk to make 3 cups.
Place in heavy saucepan and cook thick.
A heavy pan is very important. Beat with electric mixer and pour into a baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix margarine, cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
In a large bowl, mix milk, pudding and whipped topping.
Combine mixtures, stirring well.
Layer with cookies and pudding.
The last layer should be cookies.
Put in a large plastic flower pot and refrigerate overnight.
Arrange plastic flowers in "dirt" before serving.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add eggs, butter, etc.
Pour into shell and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: crunch graham treats for a party
directions: Combine cereal, raisins and nuts.
Melt chocolate pieces, peanut butter and margarine in medium sized saucepan over low flame, stirring frequently.
Turn off flame; stir in vanilla. Pour melted mixture over cereal; stir until coated.
Pour 10x sugar into food storage bag.
Add cereal mixture and shake until all pieces are coated.
Store in airtight container.
Makes about 25 cups.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple; partially thaw strawberries.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add strawberries and pineapple.
Add nuts. Pour one half of mixture into mold or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let set for 1/2 hour or so in refrigerator.
Spread sour cream on top of Jell-O.
Then pour on second half of Jell-O.
Refrigerate until set.

title: junior mint mousse
directions: In small saucepan, dissolve cocoa in milk.
Add butter and Junior Mints and stir over low heat until mixture is smooth. Transfer to bowl; cool slightly.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Step 1:
(May be done ahead.)
Open up chilis and clean. Layer in greased large casserole (sprinkle with Cheddar cheese). Blend milk, eggs, flour and salt in blender.
Pour over cheese and chili layers.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Stir jello and water until completely dissolved.
Stir in sugar until dissolved (thoroughly).
Add both pineapple and lemon juices; stir.
Chill until loosely set, then add remaining ingredients to jello mixture.
Mix until thoroughly blended.
Pour into lightly oiled mold and chill until set.

title: lasagna florentine
directions: In large pan cook onion and garlic in oil.
Add pasta sauce; simmer 15 minutes.
In bowl mix Ricotta, spinach, 1 cup Mozzarella, Parmesan and eggs.

title: apple-nut torte
directions: Mix all together by hand, batter will be thick.
Also, by hand, blend in apples.
Grease and flour 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mushroom barley soup
directions: Place all ingredients in a large soup pot and bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat and simmer, partially covered, for about 1 hour.

title: punch
directions: Add ginger ale and sherbet just before serving.

title: open apple cake with glaze
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients.
Add next 3 ingredients and mix.
Add last 2 ingredients.
Mix all together.
Make like a ball.
Put in greased and floured cookie pan; spread on sides and bottom of pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 225° oven.
While still warm, put on glaze.

title: caramel pie
directions: Rub 1 cup sugar in a heavy iron skillet; melt over low heat. Mix 1 cup sugar, flour and salt in a bowl.
Combine egg yolks and milk, mixing well.
Pour this into skillet with melted sugar; continue to stir constantly until smooth and thick.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.
Bake until golden brown.

title: spicy black bean soup
directions: Wash the beans in cold running water.
Place the washed beans in a large bowl and cover with 8 cups of cold water.
Allow to soak for 8 to 12 hours or overnight.
Drain when fully soaked.

title: ham rolls
directions: Lay a slice of ham on table; place a slice of cheese on top. Top with a spoonful of stuffing. Roll and layer in a baking dish. Pour cheese soup over top and bake at 350 for 45 minutes.

title: chili-cheese bars
directions: Mix egg, flour, margarine, cornmeal and chili powder together. Press into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients together; spread evenly over baked layer.
Return to oven for additional 20 minutes.
When cool, cut into 3 x 1-inch bars.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Bake 20 minutes at 400 degrees.

title: ham and cheese swirls
directions: Spread a thin layer of Dijonnaise evenly over the puff pastry sheet.

Top evenly with ham slices, then with Swiss cheese slices. Starting on one of the long sides, roll up, as tight as possible, into a log shape. Trim off any excess ham and cheese that extends outside the roll. Cut the roll into 1/2-inch thick slices with a serrated knife. Place the slices on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper and bake at 425° for approximately 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening and add enough water for a stiff dough.
Knead lightly.
Roll on a floured board 1/2 inch thick.
Cut squares and deep fry in very hot oil until fluffy and brown.

title: apple bars
directions: Sift flour and salt; add brown sugar and oatmeal; mix.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Spread half of the mixture in greased pan.
Dot with butter.
Add sliced apples and sprinkle with sugar. Cover with remaining mixture.
Cook at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Cut into bars.

title: sugared nuts
directions: In skillet, combine sugar, cinnamon and milk. Cook to 236° (soft boil stage). Stir in nuts and vanilla. Immediately turn out on wax paper and separate the nuts working quickly. Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine melted margarine, sugar and crushed graham crackers. Press into 8-inch square pan.
Mix pudding according to directions on box.
Spread pudding over graham cracker crust.
Slice banana and put over pudding.
Top with drained pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Garnish with cherries and nuts.
Drizzle top with chocolate syrup.
Refrigerate.

title: dad's super oyster stew
directions: Mix into smooth paste the flour, salt, pepper and water.
Stir into oysters and their liqueur; simmer over very low heat until edges curl.
Pour into scalded milk.
Remove from heat; cover let stand 15 minutes.
Add butter and reheat.
Dash with paprika.

title: kraut casserole
directions: Fry bacon, drain, crumble and set aside.
Saute onion in 1 tablespoon bacon fat.
Place drained kraut in 2-quart greased or sprayed casserole.
Stir in onion.
Top with the meat of your choice.
Pour the stewed tomatoes over this.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and bacon bits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: veggie bar
directions: Spread crescent rolls out flat on cookie sheet.
Pinch seams together.
Bake according to directions until golden brown.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and dry Hidden Valley dressing in bowl until smooth and well mixed.
Spread mixture on crescent rolls.
Top with veggies and cheese.
Cover and let set overnight in refrigerator to let flavors mix.

title: creamy coleslaw
directions: In large bowl, combine cabbage, carrot, pepper and onion.
For dressing, stir together mayo, vinegar, sugar, celery seed and salt.
Pour dressing over cabbage and toss lightly.
Cover and chill.
Serves 8.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, milk, flavoring and butter.
Pour in an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° to 350° until done.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown together ground beef, onion, green pepper, and celery. Place meat mixture, cheese, zucchini, and soup in alternate layers in casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Dot with margarine. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: holiday honey snaps
directions: Cream shortening and 2 cups sugar in a bowl until smooth. Beat in eggs and honey.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla, mixing well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Melt margarine.
Cool.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix. Add nuts.
Add flour gradually.
Roll in wax paper and chill. Slice and bake at 350° until brown, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: lazy cheese toast
directions: Take a slice of bread, sprinkle some cheese and bake it in the toaster oven until crispy and cheese is melted.
Enjoy with Griffin's Old Santa Fe Picante Sauce!!!

title: tuna boats
directions: Mix all ingredients together well (except buns).
Split buns open, butter both sides lightly and fill.
Bake until hot.

title: upside-down cake
directions: Melt oleo in baking dish or pan.
Add the brown sugar and stir.
Spread in pan.
Place pineapple slices evenly (add cherry in center).
Mix cake mix according to package directions and pour over pineapple slices.
Bake according to package directions. Cool about 5 minutes on wire rack, then invert cake on plate.

title: hot borscht
directions: Combine meat, bones, water and salt in a large saucepan and bring to a boil.
Skim off foam and reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.
Drain liquids from beets.
Set aside. Stir beet liquid, tomatoes and 2 tablespoons of the Worcestershire sauce into broth.
Add cabbage, carrots, onions, parsley, bay leaves and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in beets, 1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce.
Serve in a bowl with a tablespoon of sour cream.
Top with a sprig of dill.

title: old time tomato aspic snacks
directions: Combine tomato juice, onion, celery leaves, sugar, salt, bay leaves and cloves; simmer 5 minutes.
Strain; dissolve gelatin in tomato mixture.
Add lemon juice; chill until partially set.
Add celery; pour small amount in egg cartons that have been sprayed with Pam or Cooking Ease.
Refrigerate until firm.
Unmold on Ritz crackers; top with small amount of dressing with a sprig of parsley stuck in dressing.

title: quick-n-easy pan pizza
directions: With kitchen scissors cut each biscuit into quarters.
Mix with pizza sauce in bowl.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch glass pan; top with your meat and cheese.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: grapefruit and grape salad
directions: Peel and section grapefruits and oranges.
Combine them in a large bowl with about 1 pound of seeded grapes.
Mix 1/4 cup lemon juice, 1/4 cup plain yogurt and 3 tablespoons of honey.
Pour this dressing over the fruit and mix gently.
Sprinkle the salad with 1/4 cup chopped walnuts.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix together whipped topping, dry pudding and strawberries. Stir until well blended and the pudding mix is fully dissolved. Pour into pie crust and garnish with coconut.
Chill 1 hour.

title: beef pot roast
directions: Heat oil in a large pan.
Batter roast with flour on both sides.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place roast in hot oil until brown on all sides, turning as needed.
Cover roast with water. Add chopped onion.
Cook until roast is very tender and the flour makes a gravy.

title: microwave macaroni and cheese
directions: Prepare macaroni and set
aside.
Melt margarine in a 2 quart glass casserole in
microwave
(about 1 minute at High). Add flour, salt and
pepper.
Mix
well.
Add
milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Cook uncovered
6 minutes at High.
Stir every 2 minutes.
Add
cheese to sauce.
Stir.
Cook uncovered for 1 minute at High.
Add
cooked
macaroni
to cheese sauces and stir.
Cook uncovered for 4 minutes at High.
Stir halfway through cooking period.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into balls and bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until done.

title: lemon pie
directions: Put
egg
yolks
(beaten) in top of double boiler.
Add lemon juice and peel, water and 1/2 cup sugar gradually.	Cook over
hot water until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from hot
water. Beat
egg
whites until stiff.
Beat in remaining 1/2 cup sugar and beat until glossy.
Fold 1/2 egg whites into egg mixture.

title: spicy meat balls
directions: Make your meat balls using your favorite recipe.
Mix all of the ingredients together and pour over meat balls that have been placed in several large glass pans that have been sprayed with Pam. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lasagne
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger; drain, then cook in spaghetti sauce for 15 minutes.
Arrange half of lasagne in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Spread half of meat sauce over noodles.
Dot with half of cottage cheese on meat sauce.
Place 5 slices of Mozzarella cheese on top.
Repeat until ingredients run out.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let sit 15 minutes before serving.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Combine all of the ingredients with just 1 package of nuts, then roll all of this in the other package of nuts.
Best served with Ritz crackers.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring to boil and boil 5 to 8 minutes the sugar, cornstarch, salt and water.
Add red food coloring.
Cool and pour over fresh strawberries.
Put in baked pie shell.
Makes glaze for 1 pie.

title: hot taco rice
directions: Brown beef and onion in skille.t
Add salsa, tomato sauce and bouillon cube.
Bring to full boil.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 5 minutes.

title: barbecue slaw
directions: Grind cabbage and carrots in food processor.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over cabbage and carrots.
Mix well. Will keep up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: chunky salsa dip
directions: In small bowl combine all ingredients and mix well.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: christmas punch
directions: Juice the oranges and grind rinds.
Place rinds in bowl. Cover with boiling water.
Let stand for about 5 minutes.
Strain. Mix orange water with sugar and citric acid.
Add fruit juices and water; mix well.
Let stand overnight.
Store in plastic container.

title: banana surprise
directions: Bake cookie dough on baking stone or cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes (one large cookie).

title: harvest cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients well; add eggs and oil and blend well (batter will be thick).
Bake in 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
When cool, sprinkle with confectioners sugar or frost with white frosting.

title: fudge(makes five pounds)
directions: Put sugar, margarine, milk, and salt in large pan.
Bring to boil over medium high heat, stirring constantly.
When mixture begins to boil rapidly, start timing and boil and stir for exactly eight minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add other ingredients.
Stir until completely blended and mixture begins to thicken.
Pour into two buttered pans, about 9 x 13-inch.
When it begins to harden, make creases in top for squares of desired size.

title: frosty strawberry squares
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Crumble; put half back into pan and reserve other half for topping.

title: veal soup
directions: Remove large white and long red pepper from pickling spice. Leave a few cloves.
Boil veal, salt and spice for 20 minutes.
Add onion.
Boil until meat is very tender, 1 hour.

title: squash dressing
directions: Add the first 10 ingredients and cook on low heat until vegetables are tender.
Remove bay leaf.
Add cornbread crumbs and beaten eggs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle with grated cheese and return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: squash soup(4 servings)
directions: Boil cut up squash, onions and spices in broth until tender. Place the mixture in a blender.
Blend until smooth.
Add half and half.
Blend until very smooth.

title: hot mulled cranberry punch
directions: Place sugar, water, spices and sat in 3-quart saucepan; bring to boil.
Add fruit juices; reheat and serve.

title: homemade pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Use about 3 tablespoons of batter for each pancake.
Bake on hot griddle until bubbles appear and edges are cooked.
Turn and brown on other side.
Serve with butter, syrup or honey.

title: gwen's red earth cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat two 9-inch cake pans with shortening and flour.

title: king ranch chicken casserole
directions: Combine soup, chicken broth and tomatoes; set aside.
Oil a 3-quart casserole.
Layer half of tortilla pieces, half of chicken, half of onion and half of cheese in a casserole.
Pour half of chicken broth mixture over layer.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: meatballs in sweet sour sauce
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients and make into balls; bake or brown in skillet.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan; add meatballs.
Simmer about 2 1/2 hours.

title: fruit slush
directions: Mix water and sugar.
Bring to boil and boil until clear.
Set aside to cool.
In another bowl, mix orange juice, pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Set aside.
Mash bananas and mix with juice and sugar mixture.
Pour mixture into shallow containers and freeze solid (need 4 to 5 ice trays).
Before using, thaw for 30 minutes to soften.
Put portion into glass and pour ginger ale or 7-Up over.
Can also mix together in a punch bowl.

title: appreciation party punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in a punch bowl and enjoy.
Yields 5 1/2 quarts.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain and add tomato sauce, water and taco seasoning mix.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add beans and half of chips. Put cheese over top and top with rest of chips.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: m&m's cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Coarsely chop 1 1/2 cups M&M's; reserve remaining whole candies for decorations. Stir together the flour, baking soda and salt.
In a large bowl, cream the butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat until light and fluffy.
Add dry ingredients.
Add candy and nuts.
Drop spoonfuls of batter on cookie sheet.
Bake 6 to 7 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with remaining candies.
Return to oven.
Bake 3 to 5 minutes longer.

title: chicken stroganoff
directions: Cook onion in butter.
Stir in milk, garlic salt, pepper, dill and soup.
Stir in chicken and olives; heat.
Stir in sour cream and heat.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: sumi salad
directions: Add cabbage and green onions to large salad bowl.
Break up Top Ramen noodles (uncooked) into small pieces over top of salad. Toast almond slivers by cooking in a small, dry pan for a few minutes, stirring constantly until lightly browned.
Add to salad. Mix sesame oil, rice vinegar and sugar together.
Add to salad (you may not need all of the dressing) and toss.

title: cabbage and bean soup
directions: Combine broth, water, vegetables, bay leaf, pepper, salt, sugar and lemon juice in large pan.
Simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Add cabbage and Northern beans.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cheese vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables as directed and drain well.
Add the celery, onion, cheese, mayo and salt and pepper to taste.
Spoon the mixture into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with the Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 300°.
Top with crushed crackers and bake an additional 10 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, milk, coconut, butter, vanilla and salt.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: russian tea balls
directions: Mix butter with sugar until creamy.
Add salt, vanilla, flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Chill dough.
Heat oven to 350°.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place
on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown.
While cookies are warm, roll in powdered sugar and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook hen or fryer until tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Use a large pan and cover with plenty of water, so you will have at least 1/2 gallon broth when chicken is done.
Remove chicken; cool and pull off the bone.
Set aside.

title: basic puerto rican white rice
directions: Heat the oil in a medium saucepan with a tight fitting lid. Add the rice and saute quickly over medium-high heat for 2 minutes.
Add the water and cook until almost all of the liquid has evaporated.
Stir well.
Reduce the heat to very low and cover the rice.
Cook for 20 more minutes, stirring after 10 minutes.

title: pistachio pineapple dessert
directions: Mix crushed pineapple with instant pudding until blended.
Add Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Spoon into 9-inch square dish.
Top with crushed nuts and refrigerate for an hour or more.

title: little boys banana bread
directions: Mash bananas.
Add butter.
Mix.
Add the remaining ingredients and stir everything together.
Pour mix into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: fried zucchini strips
directions: Roll zucchini strips in flour mixture and fry.

title: flat apple cake
directions: Take 2 sticks of butter out of the refrigerator and set them aside so they warm.
Grease a 12 x 18-inch teflon cookie sheet and set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel, core and slice 6 pounds of apples; set aside.
Combine flour, baking powder, 1 1/2 cups sugar, 2 sticks of "room temperature" butter, milk, eggs and vanilla. Mixture will be cookie dough thick.
Press into cookie sheet, covering the bottom evenly.
Arrange apples in lines on top of the dough and lightly press one side of the apple into the dough. Sprinkle a mixture of cinnamon and remaining sugar over the top of the tray before baking.
Bake for about 30 to 40 minutes until golden brown, testing dough with a toothpick.
It will come out dry.

title: diane's taco dip
directions: Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan as follows:

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Heat butter in jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch) in oven until melted.
Mix bread crumbs, salt, oregano, garlic powder, Parmesan and pepper in a pie plate.
Cut eggplant (peeled) into 1/2-inch thick slices; cut larger slices in half.
Mix eggs and milk.
Dip eggplant into egg mixture; coat each piece with crumb mixture.
Place in pan; turn each piece over to coat with butter.
Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Turn and bake 5 more minutes until golden brown.
Take out of oven.
Sprinkle 1/2 of the cheese over slices.
Spoon marinara sauce over cheese and sprinkle remaining cheese over the top.
Bake 5 more minutes until cheese is melted.

title: potato balls - deep fried
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Fry in deep fat by dropping from a tablespoon.
Fat is hot enough when a cube of bread browns in 1 minute.
When potato balls are brown, drain onto paper. Serve hot.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onion in oleo, then add soups and chili peppers.
Heat through.
In bottom of casserole, break up 6 tortillas, then add half the chicken, half the soups and about 1/3 of cheese.
Repeat layers, except cheese.
Pour broth over all.
Bake in a 325° oven for 25 minutes.
Add rest of cheese; put back in oven 5 more minutes, or until cheese melts.

title: cheese straws
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together into medium size bowl.
With pastry blender, combine margarine and grated cheese. Mix lightly with a fork until pastry holds together and leaves sides of bowl clean.
Roll out to a 12 inch x 10 inch rectangle on a lightly floured board.
Divide in half and cut each half crosswise into 1/2 strips.
Bake at 450 degrees for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pickled beets and eggs
directions: Put eggs in beets.
Let set one week to pickle eggs.
More eggs can be added later.

title: applesauce meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients, except tomato sauce.
Shape into 24 balls. Season with salt and pepper.
Place in roasting pan.
Pour 2 small cans tomato sauce over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with mashed potatoes or spaghetti.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Prepare apples; set aside.
Add oil, sugar and eggs.
Beat until creamy.
Mix in flour, soda, salt and baking powder a little at a time.
Add nuts and apples.
Bake in 13 x 9 greased pan and floured.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: crunchy - munchies
directions: Combine snacks and cereals and mix well.
Combine remainder of ingredients and pour over snack mixture.
Mix well.
Bake at 200° for 1 1/2 hours, stirring every 30 minutes.
Store in airtight containers.

title: cocoa fudge
directions: Combine cocoa with sugar and salt; add milk.
Bring to boil, stirring frequently.
Cook until small amount of mixture forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
remove from heat, drop in butter.
Cool to lukewarm, add vanilla and beat until mixture thickens.
Pour into buttered pan and cut in squares.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy in pan with 1/2 cup margarine.
Beat the remaining margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Then add flour, soda, milk and vanilla.
Add cooled candy.
Beat together and pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crunchy jumble cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Beat together butter and sugar until creamy.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix well.
Blend in flour mixture.
Stir in Rice Krispies and chocolate chips.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions in water until tender; drain.
Add next 4 ingredients and mix.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Mix dressing; use 1 stick of butter instead of 1/2 stick.
Grease baking dish and line bottom with dressing mix.
Add squash mix on top of dressing. Sprinkle grated cheese on top of squash mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 casseroles.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes, cut in cubes.
Place in pan, cover with water and salt to taste.
Cook until tender.
Peel and chop onion and garlic.
Drain potatoes and mash.
Add onion and garlic.
Mix sour cream and mayonnaise.
Add to potato mixture.
Add milk, if needed, to make mushy.
Pour in casserole dish and place in hot oven (400°).
Brown in peaks on top slightly.
If you wish to make it more colorful, add parsley flakes or (and) bacon bits.
Enjoy!!

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Roll out bread dough until flat. Combine beaten eggs and spices; spread 3/4 on bread dough.
Place pepperoni and cheese on bread and roll up long end.
Spread on remaining egg mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: farmer's casserole
directions: Grease 2-quart square baking dish. Arrange hash browns in dish. Sprinkle with cheese, ham and green onions. In medium bowl, mix eggs, milk, pepper and salt. Pour mixture over potato mixture. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until center appears set.

title: upper crust chicken
directions: Trim crust from bread, reserving crust.
Cut bread slices diagonally into quarters.
Cut reserved crusts into cubes. Combine bread cubes, chicken, celery and 1 3/4 cups cheese; mix well.
Spoon into 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Arrange bread quarters over chicken mixture.
Combine mayonnaise, eggs and seasonings; mix well.
Gradually add milk, mixing until blended. Pour over bread.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Cover. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and dry jello. Add fruit and Cool Whip. Chill until firm.

title: bible cake
directions: Cream softened butter, eggs and sugar.
Add honey and milk. Mix all dry ingredients and add to butter mixture.
Then add dates, raisins and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: crescent chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cream cheese and margarine until smooth; add other ingredients.
Mix together.
Separate dough into rectangles.
Spoon 1/2 cup meat mixture into center of each.
Pull 4 corners up to seal.
Brush with margarine.
Dip in crouton crumbs.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: lamb chops
directions: Trim fat from chops.
Season with salt and pepper.
Broil 5 minutes on 1 side; turn and broil 4 minutes.
Mix together mustard and honey; spread over chops and broil 2 minutes longer.
Makes 4 servings.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add vanilla.
Gradually add 10x sugar, a little at a time.
Beat well.
Add milk and beat at high speed.
Add 2 tablespoons extra milk if you want to spread frosting.

title: taco delight
directions: Fry and drain ground beef.
Add onions and garlic powder.
Add next 7 ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add 1 cup Minute rice and cook 15 minutes.
Serve over Fritos.
Top with tomatoes, avocado, cheese, lettuce, olives and taco sauce.

title: patio beans
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain.
Drain all beans except pork and beans.
Combine and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done, moisture is absorbed.

title: punch
directions: Make lemonade and Kool-Aid as directed on package.
Add ginger ale just before it is served.
Makes 50 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: First Layer:
Cream cheese mixed with green onion.

title: 13 to 15 bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight and rinse.
Add beans to 1 quart of water and bring to a boil.
Reduce to simmer after 5 minutes and add everything else.
After 2 or 3 hours, remove the meat from the bone.
Keep adding water as needed.
Ready in 4 to 6 hours.

title: german town cookies
directions: Mix sugars, margarine and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together, then add to first mixture.
Add oats, coconut and pecans last to the mixture.
Roll into balls the size of a walnut and flatten.
Bake at 350°.
Makes about 80 cookies.

title: cinnamon raisin bread(for bread machines)
directions: Add ingredients into the pan in the order listed.
Select white bread and push "start."
Add the raisins at the "beep" near the end of the second mixing as they tend to remain whole. Sometimes you can add them at the beginning so they are nice and fine.
Try it both ways.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Blend and press
into
x
9 x 1 1/2-inch pan graham crackers and 5 tablespoons melted butter.
Beat together for 5 minutes powdered
sugar,
pound softened butter, eggs and vanilla. Spread this mixture over crumb crust and chill.
Then take bananas
and
slice
over
chilled
cream mixture.
Drain crushed pineapple
and
spread over bananas.
Spread Cool Whip over top and garnish with maraschino cherries and nuts. Serves about 15.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, then add wet ingredients.
Batter will be very thick.
Pour into greased Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
This cake is good plain, but powdered sugar and milk can be mixed until thin enough to pour over cake.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli as directed.
In large bowl, combine rice and broccoli; add onion, mushrooms and 1 soup can of hot water.
Break up cheese and add, stirring until blended.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese on top.
Serves 18 to 20.

title: wacky cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients together for 2 minutes.
Grease and flour cake pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fried pies
directions: Add 2 cups water to 1 cup fruit.
Cook until tender, then cool. Add sugar to fruit; mix good.
Add 1 teaspoon cinnamon.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix and serve with cut vegetables, carrots, celery and broccoli.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken wings, in a large bowl. Rinse chicken wings, pat dry and add to sauce to bowl.
Marinate for 4 hours or overnight.
Shake or mix frequently.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until desired brownness.

title: jello cake
directions: Cut angel food cake into bite size pieces. Place in 9 x 12-inch pan sprayed with cooking oil.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix well together.
Add 1/3 cup mix to cup of boiling water.

title: slumgulleydallas, texas
directions: In a large sauce pan, brown onions, celery, bell pepper and ground meat until brown and crumbly.
Add spices and tomatoes, plus enough water to cook down to add macaroni.

title: quick chicken cacciatore
directions: In large skillet, brown chicken in several tablespoons of oil, cook about 3 minutes each side on medium-low heat.
Put chicken in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix vegetables with pasta.
Add pasta over chicken and top with Provolone cheese.
Cook for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Cover pan with foil while cooking.
Serve with macaroni noodles and chopped parsley.

title: goodle-boodle
directions: You will need an electric frying pan.

title: pecan squares
directions: In a large mixing bowl, blend together flour, sugar, butter and salt until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press firmly and evenly into a greased 15 x 10
x 1 inch baking pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, in another bowl, combine eggs, syrup, sugar, melted butter and vanilla.
Stir in pecans.
Spread evenly over hot crust.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes or until set.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: irish cream iced cappuccino(sugar-free)
directions: Whisk together first 3 ingredients in a large saucepan until smooth. Bring to a boil over medium heat, whisking constantly; boil, whisking constantly 2 minutes. Remove mixture from heat; add Equal and cool slightly. Whisk in milk and creamer. Cover and chill at least 4 hours or up to 2 days. Serve over ice. Makes 8 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In large bowl, combine broccoli florets, bacon and onion.
In small bowl, mix together mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over broccoli mixture.
Toss gently.
Add cream cheese last.
Toss again.

title: cheese straws
directions: Grate cheese and mix with softened margarine.
Add other ingredients and mix really well.
Form into rolls.
Roll in foil and refrigerate for about 30-34 minutes.
Shape according to your desire, press into shapes, form into patties, or cut to 1/4 inch thickness with cutter.
Cook about 12 minutes at 325 degrees. (Will keep in refrigerator uncooked for up to 3 days.)
Once cooked can also freeze.

title: steak and gravy
directions: Cut steak into serving size pieces.
Put in crock-pot.
Add other ingredients.
Cook overnight slowly.
Very good with rice or creamed potatoes.

title: goulash
directions: Cook the macaroni in plenty of salted water; drain and set aside.
Fry together the ground beef, onion and peppers.
Make sure they get done but do not brown.
When done, add the tomatoes, corn and catsup or spaghetti sauce.
Cook slowly for 30 minutes and then add cooked macaroni and cook a few minutes longer.

title: layered ham casserole
directions: Mix milk with undiluted cream of mushroom soup.
Grease a casserole dish with margarine; add layers as follows:

title: "jane powell's" apple cake
directions: Combine all dry ingredients and sift together.
Add eggs, oil, apples, nuts, raisins and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tests done.
Cool on rack for 20 minutes before removing from pan.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a medium saucepan, mix the first 6 ingredients.
Cook until tender.
Add turkey, rice and 3 ounces of cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Pour into an 8-inch pie plate that's been sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle top with remaining cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Let set for 10 minutes before serving.

title: swedish birthday cake
directions: Cut the cake into 3 thin layers;
it's okay if they break a little, the filling will glue it together.
Put one layer of cake on a plate.
Add 1 to 2 Tbsp. of the whipped cream to the vanilla pudding.
Spread one half of this on the cake.
Add the second layer of cake and spread the rest of the mixture on it.
Mix the fruit with the sugar, mashing the fruit.
Pour over second layer of cake.
Add third layer of cake.
Spread the top layer lightly with whipped cream.
Put sliced fruits or candy on top of cake. Happy Birthday!

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix together cans of soup and rice and spread in large baking dish.
Cut up the chicken and lay on top.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Seal top with aluminum foil and bake at 350°
for 2 hours.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Crush
Raisin
Bran
flakes. Add sugar, flour, soda and salt. Mix
well.	Beat the eggs and add them to the Bran flake mixture. Also
add the Wesson oil and the buttermilk. Be sure and
mix well
by
hand.
Fill lightly greased muffin pan 2/3 full.	Bake at	375°
for 15 to 18 minutes.
You can store in refrigerator and use
as needed. It will keep at least 6 to 8 weeks.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Hard-boil eggs, cool and peel.
Bring to boil vinegar, water, salt, sugar and spices.
Layer eggs and onions in a large jar. Pour liquid over.
Cool and put in refrigerator.
It takes about 3 days before ready to eat.
My kids love these!

title: marinated zucchini salad
directions: Mix together.
Let stand 6 hours or overnight.

title: chocolate bars
directions: Cream 1 cup butter and the sugar until light and fluffy.
Stir in oatmeal.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Mix chocolate chips, milk, remaining butter and salt in top of double boiler.
Heat until melted and smooth.
Add
nuts and remaining vanilla.
Spread 2/3 of oatmeal mix on cookie sheet.
Cover with chocolate mix.
Dot remaining oatmeal mix over this.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: crawfish or shrimp pie
directions: Saute green onions in butter in a sauce pan.
Add crawfish (or shrimp) and both soups.
Slowly cook until smooth, adding about 1/4 to 1/2 cups of water until right consistency.
Add salt, pepper and Cajun seasoning to taste.
Prick pie shells with fork.
Pre-cook about 10 minutes at 350 degrees.
Fill pie shells and bake about 10 to 14 minutes more.

title: wrapped chicken breasts
directions: Place beef in bottom of pan. Wrap bacon around chicken breast. Mix soup and sour cream. Pour over chicken that has been placed on beef. Cook slowly at 250° for 3 hours.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Mix together peanut butter, sugar and egg.
Roll into balls. Bake in 350° oven for 8 minutes.
Take out and immediately press Hershey kisses in the middle of each cookie.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together.
Serve with apples, grapes, bananas, etc.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Place peaches in pastry shell.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over peaches.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Yields 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Stir sweet potatoes, margarine and sugar while potatoes are still hot. Add in remaining ingredients and mix well. Roll and cut into biscuits. Bake at 425° until golden brown. Serve hot with butter.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter until soft.
Add chicken soup, celery soup, olives, salt, pepper and chicken.
Put spaghetti in large amount of salted boiling water.
Let return to rolling boil; cover and remove from stove.
Let stand 20 minutes without opening.
Drain spaghetti and add chicken mixture, mixing well.

This may be served immediately with Parmesan cheese or it may be placed into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, dotted with butter and sprinkled generously with Parmesan cheese, heated until bubbly in a 350° oven.
Tastier when prepared the day before.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Cook hamburger and onion until done.
In separate pan, mix soups, milk and sauce.
Drain hamburger and mix other ingredients. Layer tortillas, cheese and hamburger mixture.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: bacon potato corn chowder
directions: Slice bacon and fry.
Add onions and saute for 2 to 3 minutes. Put potatoes and water together and cook for 10 to 12 minutes. Add together soup and sour cream.
Put in bacon mixture.
Add milk slowly.
Add salt, pepper, parsley and corn.
Reheat slowly.

title: blue cheese puffs
directions: Melt butter in an au gratin dish.
Crumble cheese over the butter.
Cut the biscuits into quarters and roll the quarters into balls.
Place them over the Blue cheese and bake according to biscuit directions.
Easy hors d'oeuvre.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Cook (boil) chicken breasts until done.
Save 1 cup broth. Pull chicken off bone, cut into bite size pieces; set aside. After baking cornbread, let cool.
Crumble up cornbread into fine pieces and pour melted margarine over the cornbread.
Mix well; set aside.

title: agilo-olio(garlic and oil)
directions: Prepare spaghetti according to package directions.
While spaghetti is cooking, prepare sauce.

title: grilled chicken summer salad
directions: In covered saucepan, cook potatoes in about 2 inches boiling water until tender (20 to 25 minutes).
Drain and cool potatoes. Cut in 3/4-inch slices.
Place potatoes, mushrooms and beans in a large, shallow dish.
Pour 2/3 cup vinaigrette over to coat completely.
Cover.
Let stand at least 15 minutes.
Add chicken to the remaining vinaigrette in bowl.
Cover and let stand 15 minutes.
Remove chicken.
Grill or broil about 8 minutes, until juices run clear, turning once.

title: sausage and wild rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: aloha loaf
directions: Cream margarine or butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs and mix well.
Stir in banana.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Fold in undrained pineapple and coconut.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until tests done.
Remove from pans to cool.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Add flour to mixture to form a soft dough.
Roll out dough and cut out cookies.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: spicy peach crisp
directions: Arrange peaches in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
In a small bowl, combine oats, sugar, flour and spices.
Cut in butter until coarse crumbs form.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve warm with milk and cream.

title: nona griffin's sugared pecans
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan.
Place on medium heat for 15 to 20 minutes (or until sugar starts sticking to pecans).
Pour out on wax paper (or greased platter).
Break apart when cool.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add salt and pepper.
While browning, mix in large bowl the milk, water and soup.
Put ground beef in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour liquid over top.
Layer Velveeta cheese slices touching sides.
Layer Tater Tots on top of cheese, sides touching.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: audrey's meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tomato sauce; shape into small balls.
Place in baking dish.
Pour over top the tomato sauce. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello good.
Add cranberry sauce, pineapple and pecans.
Mix well and let jell.

title: coconut-pecan frosting
directions: Combine evaporated milk, sugar, egg yolks, margarine and vanilla in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick. Remove from heat.
Stir in coconut and chopped nuts.
Cool until thick enough to spread.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix three dry ingredients as for pastry and save 1 cup.
Mix molasses and baking soda.
Add to dry ingredients and mix after adding water.
Use spoon to mix; batter should be lumpy.
Sprinkle crumbs over batter in greased and floured pan(s), 2 (8-inch) or 1 (9 x 13-inch).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: In one bowl add flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
In another bowl add sugar and eggs; beat well.
Add oil; beat again, then add dry mixture with wet mixture.
Beat again; add pumpkin and beat again.
Add 1/2 stick softened margarine and beat again. Grease tube pan.
Place in tube pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel dip
directions: Leave cream cheese at room temperature for a while.
Add brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat well.
The more you stir it, the creamier it gets.
This is especially good with apples.
It makes a pretty tray for showers and parties with the apples sliced and arranged around the dip.

title: country fair chicken
directions: Combine cheese, flour and seasonings.
Dip chicken in combined egg and milk.
Coat with cheese mixture.
Place in baking pan.
Pour margarine over chicken.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: aunt ruth's potato casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients and place in a buttered casserole dish.
Mix crushed corn flakes (or crackers) and 1/4 cup margarine for topping.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: brisket recipe(for 5 to 6 pounds of meat)
directions: Use a cooking bag.
Shake flour around in cooking bag.
Put meat in bag and add everything.
Kinda shake around to mix up. Marinate in refrigerator for 25 hours, turning bag over every so often.
Cook 6 to 7 hours at 275°.
If you want, when it has about an hour to go, you can pull it out and cover it with barbecue sauce.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Combine cake mix, sugar, eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Pour into 4 (8 or 9-inch) greased cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: ham macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; follow package directions.
Saute green pepper and onion in butter.
Heat ham through.
Dilute soup with milk. Combine ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet sauerkraut
directions: Rinse and drain sauerkraut thoroughly; set aside. Cook bacon. Saut onion in 2 to 3 tablespoons of bacon fat. Add sauerkraut, chopped bacon, mushrooms and water. Add flour to thicken.

title: seafest
directions: Beat cream cheese, sour cream and Tabasco until smooth:. Spread thinly on a regular size dinner plate or platter (or two). Spread salsa.
Top with chopped seafood chunks, onions, olives, and cheese.
Cocktail sauce can be substituted for salsa.
Both are well like by guests.
Serve with tortilla chips or crackers.

title: friendship tea
directions: Combine all ingredients well and store in tightly closed container.
Use 2 to 3 heaping teaspoonfuls per cup of boiling water; suit your own taste.
More sugar may be added per cup.

title: double chocolate cookie bars
directions: Cream together shortening, brown sugar and granulated (white) sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt and unsweetened cocoa.
Stir in.
Mix in semi-sweet chocolate chips.
Drop from small spoon onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in a 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: pan-seared cod with basil sauce
directions: Combine basil, cheese, broth, olive oil and 1/2 teaspoon salt in a bowl. Set aside. Sprinkle pepper and 1/2 teaspoon salt on fillets. Spray skillet with nonstick spray and heat over medium-high heat. Add fish and saut 5 minutes on each side or until fish is flaky. Serve with basil sauce.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute the butter, onion and bell pepper. Add the broccoli to onion and peppers. Add remaining ingredients. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Put bread crumbs on top.

title: quickest quiches in the west
directions: Put 2 cups half and half in large mixing bowl.
Add all cheese and eggs. Mix well.
Place mixture into pie crusts and place in preheated oven (400°) for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand 20 minutes before cutting.

title: louisiana salad
directions: Blend all ingredients except reserve some shrimp and egg slices for garnish.
Add milk to moisten if needed.

title: chili
directions: Pour tomatoes with juice into 5 quart bowl or pan.
Coarsely chop tomatoes.
Pour into 5 quart stockpot.
Add chopped onions and hot chili beans; cook on medium heat until onions are crisp tender.
Add only the following ingredients from Wick Fowler's chili kit:
paprika, garlic, salt, cumin/oregano, chili powder, red pepper to taste.
Cook about 1 hour, stirring frequently.

title: pecan pie
directions: Makes 2 regular pies or 1 deep dish pie.
Bake at 325° until firm.

title: cranberry salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well and taste.
You may need to add additional honey.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 2 cups.

title: scripture cake
directions: Following the advice of Solomon in Proverbs 23:14a (???), cook 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.
(Search the scriptures.)

title: tuna broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions; drain.
In a saucepan, melt butter over low heat; blend in flour and salt.
Add milk, all at once.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add Parmesan, lemon juice and dill.
Stir in broccoli and tuna.
Divide mixture in half.
Pour 1/2 mixture into a greased 1-quart casserole dish. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Snip half biscuits into fourths. Arrange around edge.
Bake 15 minutes more.
Freeze other half for later.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese; add eggs, one at a time.
Mix after each egg.
Add sugar.
Mix well.
Add flour and baking powder gradually, mixing in between.
Then add vanilla and lemon flavor.
Beat well.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, approximately. Let cool about 20 minutes.

title: german apple pancakes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Melt butter in ovenproof skillet.
Add sliced apples; saute until soft.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Place in oven to keep warm.
In mixer, combine flour, milk, eggs, oil, vanilla and nutmeg.
Mix, then add lemon juice and lemon zest.
Remove skillet from oven; pour batter over apples.
Return to oven and bake 15 minutes.
Reduce to 375° and bake 10 minutes longer.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie dough onto 10-inch pan. Bake at 325° until brown (5 to 10 minutes).
Cool. Whip cream cheese.
Add Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Spread this onto the crust.
Layer fruit on next.
Cover entire pizza with Cool Whip.
Top with kiwi fruit slices.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Chill.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: In a large frying pan over medium heat, saute chopped onion in oil until soft.

title: california chicken salad
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Cool to room temperature. In a bowl, gently stir the butter in mayonnaise, parsley, curry powder, garlic, salt and pepper. In a large bowl, combine chicken, grapes and almonds. Arrange this mixture on a bed of fancy lettuce leaves. Pour the dressing on top and sprinkle with paprika.

title: cornflake potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes, slice lengthwise in quarters or eighths, depending on size.
Dip cut sides in melted butter and then in crushed cornflake crumbs. Place in pan and sprinkle with salt and Parmesan cheese.
Bake 1/2 hour at 400°.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in carrots, raisins, nuts, coconut and apple pieces.
Beat together eggs, oil and vanilla.
Stir all together until just combined.
Fill to the top of muffin cups.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 15 muffins.

title: hominy salad
directions: Combine hominy and vegetables in serving bowl.
Blend sour cream, mayonnaise, vinegar and mustard in small bowl.
Add to hominy mixture and mix well.
Chill overnight.

title: quick 'n easy chili
directions: Brown ground beef in heavy saucepan; drain.
Add onions and garlic and cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes; stir occasionally.

title: praline delight pie
directions: Heat butter and brown sugar with nuts in saucepan until melted. Spread in bottom of pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes; cool. Prepare pie filling mix with milk as directed for pie.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Measure 1 cup.
Cover with wax paper and chill thoroughly.
Prepare whipped topping mix as directed; fold in 1 1/3 cups pie filling.
Spread over filling in pie shell.
Chill; garnish with remaining whipped topping and additional pecans, if desired.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Sprinkle gelatin into orange juice to soften.
Let soak 5 minutes.
Stir over low heat until gelatin is dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Add cranberry sauce and sugar.
Fold in apple, celery and nuts.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart mold that has been lightly greased with mayonnaise and chill.
Unmold on lettuce-lined plate. Fill center with mayonnaise.

title: stuff(a complete meal in an electric skillet)
directions: Pat 1/2 ground beef in bottom of skillet.
Cover with layers of vegetables.
Crumble remainder of ground beef on top of vegetables.
Spread soup (straight from can) over this and top with cheese slices.
Start on medium high (325°); lower heat when cooking starts.
Cook on low heat for 20 minutes or until vegetables are done.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix all and cook over low heat until bouillon dissolves. Sauce will thicken when cool.

title: favorite chicken casserole
directions: Place hen in saucepan and cover with cold water.

Boil until tender. Remove from saucepan, reserving broth. Pick meat from bone; set aside. Melt butter and pour over stuffing mix. Add enough broth to moisten. Heat together soups and 1/2 cup broth. Place in a buttered 2-quart baking dish, alternating layers of chicken, soups and stuffing crumbs. Do this twice. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until bubbly. Serves 6.

title: chow chow relish
directions: Combine
cucumbers,
tomatoes,
cabbage
and salt.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain as much juice as possible.
Add onions, vinegar, sugar, flour, mustard, hot peppers and turmeric.
Tie in a bag the pickling spice and black pepper.
Bring it all to a
hot
simmer. Pack
in
clean
jars and seal at once.
This relish compliments pork meat, hot dogs and hamburgers.

title: ryzon dumplings(master recipe)
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and shortening.
Cut with fork or knife.
Add liquid to mix thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls into boiling pot pie.
Cover with lid.
Cook 20 minutes beyond last dropped in.
Yields about 10 dumplings.
Double or triple if needed.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add egg and beat.
Combine flour, salt and soda in creamed mixture and beat.
Stir in chocolate pieces.
Place on cookie sheet with teaspoon.
Remove after 8 minutes.
Let cool for 1 minute on cookie sheet.
Place on wire rack to cool.
Will be chewy!

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, celery, onion and salt in the 2 cups water for about 20 minutes or until done.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Lightly mash with a potato masher and cook, stirring constantly, until soup is hot and thick.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
In a medium saucepan, bring margarine, water and cocoa to a boil.
Add hot mixture to flour mixture.
Mix well and pour into a large greased jelly roll pan, 13 x 10 x 1-inch.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: original banana pudding
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt in top of double boiler. Blend in 3 egg yolks and milk.
Cook uncovered over boiling water, stirring constantly for 10 to 12 minutes or until thickened. Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Layer wafers and sliced bananas in a 1-1/2 quart casserole.
Pour about 1/3 of custard over bananas.
Continue to layer wafers, bananas and custard. Beat egg white until soft peaks form; gradually add remaining 1/4 cup sugar and beat until stiff but not dry.
Spread on top of pudding.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes or until browned.

title: chili
directions: In frying pan, saute meat and drain.
Add water, chili and curry and simmer 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and beans; heat through. Stir in onion.
Ladle into serving bowls and sprinkle on cheese.

title: eggplant dressing
directions: Cube, boil and drain eggplant. Saute onion and bell pepper in oleo. Mix eggplant, sauteed veggies, corn, eggs, and crackers; add salt and pepper to taste. Pour into casserole dish and top with Mozzarella cheese. Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: stuffed bacon rolls
directions: Partially cook bacon, drain and reserve 2 tablespoons drippings. Set the bacon aside.
Cook the onion and the garlic in reserved drippings until tender, but not brown.

In a bowl, combine the egg and tomato sauce. Stir in bread crumbs, mushrooms, onion mixture, parsley, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper. Add the ground beef and mix well. Divide into 4 parts. Roll up meat mixture and wrap with the bacon. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: wild rice shrimp creole
directions: In 3-quart saucepan cook onions and green peppers in butter 5 minutes.
Add undrained tomatoes, water and seasonings.
Stir in wild rice mix.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add shrimp.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes more.

title: rich vanilla milkshake
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of an electric blender; blend mixture until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Yield:
2 1/2 cups.

title: sweet and sour dressing
directions: Mix all together.
Refrigerate at least 15 minutes before using.
Good on cooked ham and chicken.
Also good on salads.

title: broccoli with cheese sauce
directions: Partially cook the broccoli.
Melt 1 stick of margarine and the cheese.
Pour over broccoli.
Mix melted 1/2 stick margarine with crushed crackers.
Scatter on top of broccoli mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: killer brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line the bottom of a 9-inch square baking pan with foil.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt and set aside.
Melt butter with chocolate in the top of a double boiler or a heavy saucepan over very low heat.
Cool.
Beat eggs with sugar until light.
Stir in chocolate mixture and 4 tablespoons of liqueur.
Add flour mixture to blend.
Stir in walnuts.
Turn batter into prepared pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until top springs back when lightly touched in center and edges begin to pull away from pan.
Remove from oven and cool thoroughly in pan placed on rack.
Brush top with remaining 2 tablespoons liqueur.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: not so barbecued chicken
directions: Place oil in skillet, arrange chicken breast over oil in skillet.
In a bowl, mix the ketchup and Coke together.
(If Coke is cold it will not foam as much.)
Pour ketchup mixture over chicken in skillet.
Cover, cook on top of stove at medium to medium high heat, turning chicken once.
Stir 'gravy' and continue cooking until it thickens.
Cook about 25-30 minutes.
This gravy is great served over mashed potatoes or rice.
Serve with a salad and crescent rolls, and wow, what a meal!

title: no bake fruit peanut bars
directions: Combine peanut butter, honey and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Remove; quickly stir in fruit and cereal.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Cool 15 minutes. Cut into squares.

title: meringue
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cook until clear; cool. Beat egg whites; gradually add sugar.
Whip.
Pour in cooled mixture.
Beat until very stiff, 5 minutes.
Cover pie and bake at 400° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Put cream of tartar in egg whites.

title: chow mein casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven about 45 to 60 minutes.

title: 4 layer "yum" dessert
directions: Melt oleo.
Mix with flour and nuts. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown. Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and confectioners sugar together. Spread over first layer.
Beat instant pudding and milk together. Pour over cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip and cool overnight in refrigerator.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Put 2 cups water over chicken and boil until done.
When cool, cut chicken into small chunks.
Mix together in a 9 x 12-inch casserole, the chicken chunks, 1 1/2 cups chicken broth, celery soup, melted margarine and peas and carrots.
(I just cut up some carrots and onions and cook until almost done; then add some frozen peas and use this.)
Mix Bisquick and milk together; pour over the top.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until brown.
(In a glass dish, bake at 325°.)

title: oatmeal raisin drop cookies
directions: Combine and mix flour, salt, soda, water and cinnamon.
Stir in oatmeal; reserve.
Beat shortening and sugar together until creamy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, raisins and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven until done and brown, 12 to 14 minutes.
Yields about 5 1/2 dozen cookies about 2 1/2-inches in diameter.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake
in greased 13 x 9-inch pan or iron skillet.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine. Add sugar, cocoa, vanilla, eggs and milk. Bake in unbaked pie shell at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Add next five ingredients.
Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Cover with 1/2 of herb dressing. Add squash mixture and top with remaining dressing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: orange segment marmalade
directions: Cook all together slow until thick.
Pour in clean, sterilized glasses and seal.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Blend butter and flour in saucepan.
Stir in milk.
Gradually cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add shredded cheese and cook over low heat until cheese is melted, stirring frequently. Microwave broccoli on High for 4 minutes.
Add to soup. Heat to serving temperature.
Season to taste.
Yields 4 servings.

title: five pound fudge
directions: Pour into buttered pan. Cut while warm.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Melt butter and cheese on low heat. Add remaining ingredients, including broccoli.
Keep hot. Serve with taco chips.

title: chocolate-chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, combine dry cake mix, vegetable oil and eggs; mix well.
Add chocolate chips (and nuts if desired) with a large spoon or hands.
Form into small balls (approximately 1 teaspoon).
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields approximately 3 dozen.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop beef in blender; divide in half and set aside.
Use mixer to cream the cream cheese, half of the chopped beef, onion tops, Accent and Worcestershire sauce; mix well.
Roll into ball shape and roll into the remaining chopped beef on aluminum foil.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Serve with crackers; roll into the chopped nuts if desired.

title: chicken wings - buffalo style
directions: Split chicken wings at each joint and discard tips.
Pre-cook chicken in covered frypan in water (poach) for 30 minutes.
Pat dry with paper towels.

title: milk and honey balls
directions: Mix honey and peanut butter. Gradually add milk. Mix well. With greased hands, form into small balls. Roll balls in additional milk powder. Chill until firm.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Mix last 3 ingredients and pour over other ingredients. Mix thoroughly.

title: french lemon pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and sweetened condensed milk.
Add Cool Whip and pineapple.
Stir vigorously.
Spoon into pie crust and refrigerate.

title: spiced tea
directions: Prepare an infusion by bringing to a boil water and sugar. Remove from heat and add the juices, cloves and cinnamon. Meanwhile, prepare tea.
Put the hot, spiced infusion in crystal bowl.
Pour the steeped tea over the mixture and serve.

title: glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and cut into large chunks 4 or 5 sweet potatoes.
Boil until tender.
Pour over potatoes and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ground beef cornbread pie
directions: Brown meat in skillet, mix in onion and green pepper.
Saute 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except cornbread mix.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Pour into casserole dish.
Mix cornbread according to package directions and spoon over top of casserole.
Bake uncovered 20 minutes at 425° or until cornbread is golden brown. Bake in deep dish (9 x 9-inches).
Serves 8.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine sour cream, dill weed, parsley and onion in a bowl. Cut beef into small squares and add to mixture.
Fold in beef and chill.
Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: cool whip pie
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges well.
Mix milk and lemon juice. Add pineapple and oranges.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into 2 graham cracker or vanilla wafer pie crusts.
Chill and serve.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together.
Mix in corn meal.
Blend until mixed.
Put egg, milk and oil in bowl and beat until smooth.
Pour in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Bake 20 minutes at 425°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix first five ingredients together. Melt 1 stick of butter, and 1 pkg. Pepperidge Farm Dressing Mix together. Put 1/2 dressing mixture in casserole dish, pour squash mixture over dressing. Top with the other 1/2
of dressing mixture. Bake at 350 degree for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: orange romaine salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a jar.
Cover tightly and shake well; set aside.
Combine next 5 ingredients in a large salad bowl.
Just before serving, pour dressing over lettuce mixture and toss gently.
Sprinkle salad with crumbled bacon.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: sun tea
directions: Place a sun tea jar or shallow pan in sunny spot outside. Fill with water, tea bags and cinnamon sticks.
Let steep in sun for 4 hours. Serve over ice with lime slices.

title: heavenly cookie freeze
directions: Crush cookies and mix with melted margarine.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.
Soften ice cream and spread on top of the cookies.
Refreeze.

title: champagne chicken
directions: Place all ingredients into a Ziploc bag.
Shake well to distribute evenly.
Let chicken mixture sit for 1/2 hour to 3 hours to marinate.
Heat oven to 400°.
Place chicken on lightly greased baking pan.
Let cook for about 45 minutes or until done. Baste occasionally with remaining marinade.
When done, discard marinade.
Serve chicken with rice and choice of veggies.
Serves 2.

title: lemon sour cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Blend in cold water, lemon juice and beaten egg yolks.
Mix well.
Add boiling water gradually.
Add butter.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute. Stir in lemon peel.
Pour in large bowl.
Cool 10 minutes.
Add sour cream.
Mix.
Pour in pie shell.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and pour into greased casserole dish.

title: cocktail salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail.
Sprinkle Jell-O over fruit cocktail (do not stir).
Set in covered dish in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, add sour cream and mix well.
Put back in refrigerator and let chill (1 hour).
Add Cool Whip, nuts, marshmallows and cherries.
Save a few nuts and cherries for top of salad.

title: oyster stew
directions: Melt butter over low heat in saucepan.
Add oysters and Texas Pete. Saute on low for about 5 minutes. Add milk and salt and pepper to taste. Stir until hot, but not boiling.
Serve with crackers.

title: quick casserole
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in margarine for about 10 minutes.
Break spaghetti in pieces and cook in salt water until tender; drain.
Combine meat, onion and green pepper in casserole dish.
Mix water and soup and add to meat mixture.
Add 1 1/4 cups cheese and spaghetti.
Season to taste.
Toss lightly and coat with sauce.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Combine vanilla pudding with milk.
Let stand until stiff, stir in Cool Whip.
In 3-inch baking dish, mix flour, margarine and pecans.
Spread over bottom of dish and bake until brown at 350°.
Let cool and pour in liquid contents.
Cover with blueberries.

title: oven barbecue spareribs
directions: Pour sauce over ribs, let stand several hours in refrigerator (overnight is better).
Cover baking dish with aluminum foil. Bake in 350° oven about 2 hours or until tender.
Remove foil the last few minutes to brown meat.

title: oven barbecued ribs
directions: Arrange spareribs, rounded side up, in shallow pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and onions.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over spareribs.
Bake in hot oven (450°) for 45 minutes, then reduce heat to 350°.
Bake another 45 minutes.
Baste occasionally.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: judy's company vegetable dish
directions: Combine and heat soups and cheese; stir until blended.
Pour over vegetables in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: roll-ups
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Add chicken and other ingredients.
Save enough cheese to use on top.
Bake in casserole at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: chili supper salad
directions: Layer
2 (15 ounce) cans refried beans (or 20 ounce can), 1
envelope
taco
seasoning.
Stir together and put in bottom of casserole.

title: bible cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift salt, flour, baking powder and spices.
Mix honey with water and add alternately to first mixture with dry ingredients.
Add raisins, figs and nuts.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 375° until tests done.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat, onion, salt (you may want to omit this because of other seasonings), pepper and garlic in a large 8-quart pan.
Add all other ingredients, except cheese.
Simmer as long as you like. Serve with grated cheese.

title: cauliflower scallop
directions: Combine soup, milk and eggs. Stir in half the cheese, bread crumbs, parsley, pimiento, onion, 1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper. Chop cauliflower. Stir into soup mixture.
Put in a 10 x 10 x 2-inch dish. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Top with cheese and bake 5 minutes until cheese melts.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: holiday spinach rice
directions: In 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, in hot butter, cook onions, almonds and rice until onions are tender, stirring constantly.
Add broth and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 15 minutes.
Add spinach.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes more or until liquid is absorbed, breaking up spinach with fork.
Add cheese and pimento.
Heat until cheese melts.
Garnish with sliced almonds.
Makes 8 cups or 12 servings.

title: barbecue rib sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Add enough vinegar to give sauce a bite.
Store in refrigerator.
Not necessary to cook.
Rub ribs with dry rubbing powder recipe first.

title: sweet 'n' dill pickles
directions: Pour off and discard the juice from the dill pickles.
Combine sugar, vinegar and seeds in a measuring cup.
Let stand several hours, stirring occasionally to dissolve the sugar.
Cut the pickles into thick slices and return them to the jar.
Pour the liquid mixture over them.
Cover tightly and chill thoroughly so that the pickles are crisp.

title: easy brownies
directions: Stir ingredients together (mixture will be thick).
Press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes for chewy type. Slightly longer for cake type.

title: chicken-vegetable soup
directions: Boil the chicken for 45 minutes or until done.
Remove from bones.
Add remaining ingredients and cook for 30 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken with salt, pepper, onion and a dash of red cayenne pepper until tender.
Cool and chop chicken.
Add chopped, boiled eggs.
Add desired amount of pickles, salt, black pepper, celery salt and seasoned salt.
Mix well until spreading consistency.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onion in water in saucepan until tender. Add milk, butter, salt and pepper.
Heat to serving temperature. Add cheese to soup (optional) and let melt.
Wonderful taste!

title: cheese and hamburger
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Cut bars of cheese into slices for easier melting.
Combine all ingredients in a crock-pot, or until cheese is melted.
Stir occasionally.
Serve with chips.

title: chewy chocolate chip bars
directions: Cream together oleo and sugars until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and baking soda; mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips, nuts and oats.
Spread dough into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool; cut into bars.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: spectacular popovers
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Grease 6 deep custard cups or 8 medium muffin cups.

title: calico beans
directions: The cans of beans should all be the same size. Combine all ingredients and place in crock pot. Cook on low for 3 hours.

title: gunk
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add onion, potatoes, water, parsley, basil, salt and pepper and sugar.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Add both cans of corn.
Let boil and add milk.

title: cream sauce for fruit
directions: Mix well and chill several hours.
Pour over fruit or use as a dip for fruit.

title: pioneer biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients except sour cream in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Stir in sour cream.
Mix to make a soft dough.
Turn onto floured surface.
Knead about 2 minutes.
Roll dough to about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut out biscuits using a cookie cutter or drinking glass turned upside down.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Cook in preheated oven at 400° for 12 minutes or until done.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix mayonnaise with crumbled cheese and mix in package of cheese mixed with oregano.
Add all this to mayonnaise left in jar; then add buttermilk and stir with spoon to blend.
Put lid on jar and shake well.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Bake in hot oven at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream the shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add egg; beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in milk.
Add dry ingredients; blend into creamed mixture.
Divide dough in half; chill for 1 hour.
On lightly floured surface, roll dough to 1/8 to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into desired shapes with cutters.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for about 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet.
Makes approximately 2 dozen.

title: hot sauce
directions: Cook until as thick as you like.

title: hootnanny pancakes
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all other ingredients in bowl with mixer until smooth.
Pour onto melted margarine. Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Cut in squares and serve immediately with syrup.

title: fat free fantasy fudge
directions: I can remember of a time one summer at about 6:00 a.m.
I was awakened by my brother yelling to my Dad, "Get up, Dad, get up, the devil is in the toilet (out house)".
Dad got dressed, went outside and looked down the hole.
Sure enough, there was two pointed horns floating around down there.
Dad got a rope, lassoed the creature and ran down to the pond.
He threw it out into the middle of the pond 4 or 5 times and each time it would swim to shore.
Then it followed him to the house.
When we came out to see what happened, Dad told us to get some soap and water and wash our dog.

title: hamburger corn casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; add all other ingredients, except bread crumbs.
(Can be frozen at this time.)
Saute bread crumbs in butter.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: scallops
directions: Mix all, adding scallops last.
Bake at 500° for 10 minutes.

title: roast beef
