directions: The day before, prepare the meat with all the spices (condiments).
You put in the oven for 1 hour at 450°, then you put the potatoes, mushrooms and carrots and let everything cook.
You take the meat out, you slice and put it back in the oven.
You then, take it out and serve it on a platter.
Total cooking time:
2 1/2 hours.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake cake as directed in 19 x 13 inch pan. Prick top of baked cake and pour Kahlua or coffee over cake. Cover cake and allow liquid to soak in overnight. Make pudding as directed. Crumble half of cake in bottom of large glass bowl; layer half of pudding, then half whipped topping followed by half of crumbled candy bars. Repeat layers, ending with candy.

title: homemade fried pies
directions: Cook fruit covered with water until very tender; drain well. Mix with sugar and flavoring.
Mash fruit well.
Flour aluminum foil well.
Roll biscuits out thin into round circle.
Put 2 tablespoons of fruit on one side of circle.
Fold other side over fruit; press edges tightly with fork prongs.
Place gently into pan of medium heated cooking oil.
Brown and turn to other side and brown.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10-inch dish or 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Cook and stir ground beef and onions until brown and drain. Stir in seasoning mix as directed.
Spread in plate; sprinkle with chilies.
Beat milk, Bisquick mix and egg until smooth.
Pour into plate.
Do not stir.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Take out and sprinkle with cheese and bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes. Serve with sour cream, chopped tomatoes and shredded lettuce, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: bourbon dogs
directions: In a very heavy skillet, put ketchup, sugar and hot dogs (cut into bite size pieces).
Simmer uncovered 30 minutes.
Add bourbon and simmer 30 minutes more.

title: raspberry parfait pie
directions: Beat first four ingredients until it holds shape.
Add raspberries; beat until will stand in peaks.
In another bowl, mix up Dream Whip, milk and vanilla; fold into raspberry mixture. Pour into crust; chill for one hour before serving.

title: lazy fruit cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk together.
Pour into dish on top of butter.
Do not stir.
Add fruit to top.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream of ice cream, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Use this recipe for any seasonal fruit.

title: spanish rice
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan over medium heat.
Add rice and stir until coated with the oil.
Blend tomatoes or tomato sauce, garlic, onion and 1/3 cup of broth or water in food processor or blender until smooth.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Sift flour, baking powder, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg.
Add baking soda to tomato soup.
Add soup to creamed ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and place in 9 x 13 pan. Cover with picante sauce. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Add cheese. Bake until cheese melts.

title: apple tart
directions: Cream together margarine/butter, sugar, vanilla and flour. Wrap in Saran Wrap and refrigerate.
Peel, core and slice the apples.
Press dough into bottom of pan and up sides of an 11-inch fluted tart pan with a removable bottom.
I invert the dough in Saran Wrap and spread the dough through the wrap into the pan (easy).

title: potato soup
directions: Cover potatoes and onion with water.
Add salt and butter. Cook until tender.
Mash with potato masher.
Add cheese and soup. Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir while cheese melts.

title: vanilla brownies
directions: *If using plain flour (instead of self-rising), add 1/2 teaspoon of
baking
powder and 1/8 teaspoon of baking soda to plain flour.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Heat juices from pineapple and cherries.
Dissolve jello in juices.
Add cream cheese, stir.
Pour over fruit, nuts and marshmallows.
Slowly add colas.
Mix and congeal.

title: mounds bars
directions: Melt margarine and mix with graham cracker crumbs and sugar. Spread into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix coconut and milk together and spread over baked graham cracker crust.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips in double boiler.
Spread melted chips over coconut layer.
Chill until firm.
Cut into bars.

title: tangy fruit
directions: Whisk together pudding mix, Tang and pineapple juice.
Toss with fruit.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Any combination of melons and fruits may be used.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix with mixer the oil, sugar and eggs. Add the remaining ingredients. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
When done and cool, top with icing.

title: layered enchilada pie
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic. Add seasonings and tomato sauce. In round 2-quart dish, alternate layers of tortillas, meat sauce and grated cheese. Add water. Cover and bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Combine meat, bread crumbs, onion, Parmesan cheese, eggs and seasonings.
Press mixture into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Pour off drippings.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Place butter, sugar and water in microwave bowl, but do not stir.
Cook on High for 8 minutes, until light brown in color. Pour over nuts in foil-lined 8 x 11-inch pan.
Cool and crack in pieces.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Drain peaches and reserve syrup. Combine syrup, lemon juice, honey, spice and orange peel in 2-quart pan. Bring to boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved. Cover and simmer about 10 minutes. Strain and pour hot syrup over peaches in bowl. Cover and let stand 1 hour, turning occasionally. Yields 6 servings.

title: hawaiian haystacks
directions: Make a gravy out of 2 cans cream of chicken soup and 1 can of chicken broth.
Stack other ingredients up on plate and pour gravy over it.
Very good!

title: chocolate chip pudding cake
directions: Mix pudding according to directions in large pan.
When pudding comes to a boil, remove from heat.
Add cake mix to pudding and mix thoroughly.
Pour into oblong pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Bring to a rolling boil the syrup, sugars and vanilla.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, corn flakes and peanuts.
Spread in buttered pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top and place pan in oven at 350° for 1 minute until chocolate is softened to spread.

title: dusty miller cookies
directions: Mix in order as listed.
Chill dough.
Form dough into balls. Roll in powdered sugar.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix and press 1/2 dry mixture in 13 x 9-inch greased pan. Pour in 4 cups diced rhubarb.
Combine and cook the sugar, water, vanilla and cornstarch until thick.
Pour over rhubarb and top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Put everything in a bowl and beat until mixed.
Grease 3 bread pans; fill half full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool before removing.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Place thawed potatoes in 9 x 13 pan. Mix next 6 ingredients and pour over potatoes. Top with crushed corn flakes; drizzle melted butter over all. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dane meyer's famous veggie pizza
directions: Put fresh vegetables (cauliflower, broccoli, black olives, fresh mushrooms, green pepper, tomatoes (diced and drained), cheese, anything you like, chopped fine) and sprinkled on top.

title: banana nut cake
directions: In a large bowl mix together flour, salt, sugar, baking powder and baking soda.
Add shortening, 1/3 cup buttermilk and bananas. Beat for 2 minutes.
Add 1/3 cup buttermilk and eggs, beating for 2 minutes.
Fold in chopped nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: easy chicken italiano
directions: In large skillet, combine chicken and about 1/4 of the dressing.
Saute until chicken begins to brown.
Add vegetables and remaining dressing.
Cover and simmer about 7 to 9 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Serve over pasta or rice. Sprinkle with the cheese.
Makes 5 servings.
This will take about 15 minutes to make.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Beat eggs. Add spices, sugar, milk and butter.
Add potatoes to mixture and pour into baking dish. Bake until firm.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Put onions in the bottom of the pie shell.
Cover with well drained broccoli.
Beat the eggs well and add milk and Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour egg mixture in and top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until knife inserted comes out clean and top is browned.

title: swiss mocha coffee
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in container with lid.
Put 2 heaping teaspoonfuls into each cup of hot water.
Amounts can be adjusted to suit your taste.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Mix and pour in pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then roll in chopped nuts. Chill 24 hours before serving.

title: frozen fruit pie
directions: Mix milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Mix until blended well. Fold in remaining ingredients, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Pour mix in crust.
Freeze until firm, approximately 2 to 3 hours.
Let stand 20 to 30 minutes at room temperature before serving.

title: nachos casserole
directions: Combine taco sauce and chilies.
Set aside.
In large frypan, cook beef and onions until meat is browned.
Drain off excess drippings.
Add cumin, beans, 1 cup of cheese, 1/2 of taco sauce mixture and water.
Pour 2 cups corn flakes into lightly greased 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch 2-quart glass baking dish.
Cover with meat mixture.
Top with remaining taco sauce mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining cereal.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake just until cheese melts.
Garnish with chopped tomatoes, sour cream, chopped green onions and sliced olives, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cut tomatoes in halves.
Make topping of onion, fine bread crumbs, salt, pepper, oregano and basil.
Mix together with plenty of melted butter.
Put crumb mixture on top of each tomato half. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Mix well and roll in walnut size or smaller. Flatten with glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: blackened shark
directions: Heat oil in a large griddle or skillet over medium to high heat until very hot.
Meanwhile, combine red pepper, paprika, garlic powder and salt; cut lemon in half.
Squeeze lemon over each side of all fillets.
Place fillets in hot skillet or griddle.
Sprinkle lightly with spices; cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Turn fillets.
Sprinkle lightly with spices.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and drain grease.
Combine all other ingredients and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: string beans mignonnette
directions: Oil the bottom of a steel pan or Dutch oven.
First, add the onion, then the zucchini (sliced with the skin on), then the string beans and herbs.
Add 1/4 cup water.
Cover tightly.
Cook on very low heat for about 20 minutes.

title: zucchini veggie-stuffing casserole
directions: Drop veggies into boiling water 5 minutes and drain.
Add chicken soup and sour cream.
Mix together stuffing, dry packet and margarine, melted.
Line casserole dish with half cubes, then veggies, then cubes on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Set cheeses out at room temperature.
Mix the cream cheese and Velveeta with a fork until mixed well, then add Longhorn cheese. Add garlic or onion flakes into cheeses.
Roll into ball; roll it in pecans and chili powder.
Chill.

title: squash patties
directions: Cook squash with onion in a little water to get it cooked. Drain and add butter; then mash. To this, add egg, cracker crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper. Put into balls and roll in cracker crumbs. Fry in skillet.

title: cabbage rolls(galombke)
directions: Mix together all ingredients except 1 can of tomato sauce and roll into steamed cabbage leaves. Bake in a 325° oven for approximately 1 hour.
May use spaghetti sauce in place of plain sauce.

title: sugar and spice cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg and molasses, blending well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Form into balls (1 teaspoon dough).
Roll in a mixture of 2 teaspoons sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Place 2-inches apart on greased pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; add milk and egg.
Add chopped green onions.
Drop by spoonful into hot cooking oil.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburg.
Spoon off fat and cool.
Shred lettuce, dice tomatoes and cucumbers.
Drain can of corn.
Toss together cooled hamburg, lettuce, tomatoes, cucumbers and corn.
Break up nacho chips for individual servings.
Add hamburg mixture and toss with Catalina dressing.

title: pancakes
directions: Beat eggs with salt, milk, baking powder and vanilla.
Add flour to mixture.
Using a whisk, mix thoroughly.
(Small lumps in batter are okay.)
Heat 2 to 3 tablespoons oil in medium sized pan on medium heat.
Coat bottom of pan with oil evenly.
(Lift pan and gently tip from side to side to coat pan.)
Pour approximately a 1/4 cup of the batter into the heated pan.
Spread batter over surface of pan with spoon.
Fry until light golden.
Using spatula, flip pancake over to bake second side.
Makes 10 to 12 pancakes.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Fry bacon or sausage until done.
Drain fat.
Dice bread. Sprinkle bread in 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Sprinkle meat over bread and then cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper all together.
Pour over other ingredients.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: bread pudding with whiskey sauce
directions: Combine sugar, egg, milk, nutmeg, cinnamon and vanilla. Add bread
and	raisins;
stir.
Spoon	mixture
into
8 cups. Place in	shallow
pan
with 3/4 inch hot water.	Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Add Whiskey Sauce.

title: south american coffee punch
directions: Add cinnamon sticks to coffee and cool.
Add whipped cream, vanilla, ice cream and sugar and stir.
Fill tall glass with ice and pour punch over.

title: peanut butter eggs
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Add peanut butter and vanilla; cream.
Add salt and sugar.
Mix well.
Melt chocolate chips with paraffin wax.
Let eggs set in refrigerator overnight.
Dip in chocolate next day.

title: hot or cold crab hors d'oeuvre
directions: Melt cheese and butter; add rest of ingredients.
Spread on English muffins, cut into 1/4's.
Run under broiler until bubbly.

title: grandpa's barbecue sauce
directions: Chop onions very fine.
Put in saucepan with water.
Cook until onions are tender.
Add all other ingredients and simmer until thick and flavors have blended.
If it cooks too thick, add a little water.
Good on all meats.
Will keep for weeks.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until thick.
Pour into baking dish. Brown ground beef.
Chop onion and jalapeno pepper in meat.
Add tomato sauce and chili powder.
Pour on top of cornmeal mixture and top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until done.

title: buffalo chips(cookies)
directions: Cream together oleo, shortening, brown sugar and sugar.
Add eggs, flour, baking powder, vanilla and baking soda.
Mix in oatmeal, corn flakes, chocolate chips, dates, coconut, nuts and raisins.
Use ice cream scoop or 1/4 cup to drop six cookies to cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 40 large cookies.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream the cheese and peanut butter.
Add sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Makes 2 pies (not real full).
Double the recipe makes 3 full pies.
Good in graham cracker crust.
Keep refrigerated (freezes well).

title: orange-tapioca salad
directions: In a pan, mix together the first three ingredients.
Add 3 cups boiling water; stir well and let stand 1/2 hour.
Cook until thick, about 5 minutes, after it boils.
Cool.
Add oranges and pineapple.
Fold in whipped topping.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes and onions with salt cooking until tender. Pour off excess water.
Add butter, soup and cheese.
Mix well. Cover all with milk.
Cook on low until thicken; about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican green rice
directions: Saute all vegetables in butter.
Place in blender and mush. Add sour cream.
Layer rice mush and cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until cheese melts and is hot through.

title: church window cookies
directions: Melt butter and chips.
Beat until cold and add nuts and vanilla.
Finally add marshmallows.
Divide into 2 rolls.
Roll in coconut that has been spread on waxed paper.
Wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate until firm, at least 2 hours.
Slice and serve. These freeze well.

title: ruby fruit prune compote
directions: In 2 to 3-quart saucepan, combine prunes, figs, Port, water and honey.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer until fruits are tender but not soft, about 10 minutes.
Remove fruits to bowl with slotted spoon.
Bring liquid in saucepan to boil over medium heat. Cook about 5 minutes until reduced by one-third.
Remove from heat; stir in lemon juice, then pour over fruit.
Cool, cover and chill. To serve, place in serving dishes with orange segments and pour liquid over.
Makes 6 servings.
Contains 232 calories, dietary fiber 8.3 g and fat 6 g.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine the soups and evaporated milk.
Layer sauce, tortillas, chicken and cheese, like lasagna.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, covered, and 10 minutes uncovered.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix diced apples and sugar thoroughly.
Add oil, nuts, eggs and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients together and then add to apple mixture.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch or angel cake pan (line with waxed paper).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Spread Fritos in bottom of pan. Mix all other ingredients except cheese and spread over Fritos. Spread cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: phoenix baked potato
directions: Split and squeeze potato to open.
Add salsa.
Top with sour cream.

title: holiday spritz cookie(pressed cookie)
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Mix butter, sugar, egg, salt, flavoring and coloring thoroughly. Measure and mix flour into dough mixture. Using 1/4 dough from mixture, force dough through cookie press on ungreased baking sheet in desired shapes. Bake 6 to 9 minutes or until set but not brown. Glaze when cool. Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: grapefruit bird baskets
directions: This recipe is "for the birds!"
Also makes a great gift for bird lovers and the kids can do this one.

title: play dough
directions: In a heavy saucepan, mix dry ingredients.
Add oil, water and food coloring.
Cook 3 minutes at medium high heat or until mixture pulls away from sides of pan.
Knead slightly almost immediately.
Store in airtight container.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Blend together cream cheese, sour cream and chopped ham.
Add green onions and Mrs. Dash to taste.
Spread on crackers.

title: students ragout
directions: Cut round steak in thin strips across grain.
Cut onions, carrots and potatoes into thick slices.
Prepare in an electric skillet with lid.
Cover skillet bottom with bacon, then layer meat over bacon. Layer onions, carrots, peppers and mushrooms. Potatoes go on last.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cook on High for 3 minutes.
Add water and cover.
Cook 45 minutes on low heat.

title: cherry chocolate cakespringfield, missouri
directions: 1st layer:
1 stick melted oleo, 2 c. graham cracker crumbs. Combine and press in 9 X 13-inch pan.

title: mexican "corn" bread
directions: Stir all together and pour in large hot iron skillet that has melted bacon grease or shortening.
Bake in preheated 450°
oven for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: soul tater salad
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, cook potatoes, uncovered, in boiling salted water about 25 minutes or until tender.
Drain, peel and cube potatoes.
In a large bowl, combine pickle juice, prepared mustard and bottled hot pepper sauce.
Add cubed potatoes, onions, chopped pepper, chopped eggs and pickle slices; toss to coat. Serve warm or chilled.
Garnish with pickled pepper strips and pickle slices, if desired.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: healthy ranch dressing
directions: Blend mayonnaise and buttermilk together gradually.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: barbecue crescent rolls
directions: Cook, crumble and drain ground beef.
Mix in barbecue sauce. Roll out 1 can of crescent rolls in a baking dish.
Spread ground beef mixture on top of crescent rolls.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top of ground beef mixture.
Roll out second can of crescent rolls on top of cheese.
Pinch sides together to seal crescent rolls together.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes, until golden brown. Serve with a salad.

title: affies chicken
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Sauce butter, onion, and bell pepper.
Add all other ingredients, putting cheese last.
Once cheese is melted, pour over spaghetti and bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheezies
directions: Mix cheese and pepper with mayo, enough to make a spread. Spread on buns halves.
Broil until light brown.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6.

title: rye treats
directions: Brown sausage and ground chuck together.
Pour off excess grease.
Melt Velveeta cheese; pour cheese into meat pan.
Add oregano, Worcestershire sauce, salt, basil, parsley and garlic salt.
Toast bread on one side under broiler; spoon mixture on toasted side of bread.
Leave on cookie sheets to freeze; transfer to airtight freezer containers.
Take out amount needed for each occasion.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 48 treats.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil oleo, sugar and Karo for 5 minutes.
Add salt and baking soda.
Pour over popped corn.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
I stir it 10 minutes after I put it in the oven.
It burns if you don't stir it often.

title: caramel layer chocolate squares
directions: Combine caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk in double boiler; cook until melted or melt in microwave.
Set aside.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine dry cake mix, butter and 1/3 cup milk and nuts.
Stir by hand.
Press 1/2 of the dough into pan (keep 1/2).
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle chips over baked crust.
Spread caramel mixture over chips.
Crumb remaining mixture over top and bake 15 to 18 minutes. Cool slightly, refrigerate about 30 minutes to set caramel.
Cut into 36 bars.

title: strawberry dip
directions: Mix these ingredients together and serve as a dip.
Can also be used with any fruit.

title: lenten soft pretzels(bake on ash wednesday)
directions: Christians used to twist their bread into little arms, crossed in prayer, called pretzels.
People gave pretzels to each other during Lent to remind them to stick to fasting and prayer.

title: impossible pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly with electric mixer.
Add melted butter, sugar, flour and milk.
Beat again until well blended.
Stir in coconut.
Pour into 2 ungreased 8-inch pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool and cut.
Makes 16 servings.
Do not use a pie crust.
This makes its own.

title: artichoke dip with parmesan cheese
directions: Combine and bake at 325 degrees for 30 minutes.
Serve hot. (Double recipe to make a 9 x 13-inch pan.)

title: curried fruit casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Drain fruit well and dry on paper towels.
Mix butter, brown sugar and curry powder.
Put fruit in a large shallow baking dish.
Dot all over with the curry-sugar mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, basting frequently.
Serves 10.

title: apple cake(serve with ice cream)
directions: Add sugar to well beaten egg.
Add all other ingredients at once.
Pour batter into greased pie pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Serve hot wedges with ice cream.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°, placing rack in lowest position.
Grease bottoms only of 2 loaf pans.

title: pickled beets
directions: Drain beets; cover with vinegar.
Add cloves, sugar, lemon and onion.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; let stand for a few hours.
Serve hot or cold.

title: twinkies
directions: Cream
cup
margarine in mixer bowl; add cake mix, eggs and
water and beat for 4 minutes.	Pour into greased and floured 10 x 15-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes; cool. Whisk
flour
into milk in saucepan; add 1/2 cup margarine.
Cook until
thickened,
whisking
constantly;	cool. Combine
with remaining
ingredients in bowl; beat for 4 minutes.
Cut
cake into
1 1/3 x 2 1/4-inch pieces.
Split each piece into 2 layers. Spread with filling.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Mix eggs, butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy. Add flour, cocoa and salt; beat until well blended.
Fold in pecans.
Spread batter evenly in baking pan or dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
After removing pan from oven, place dollops of Marshmallow Creme on cake.
Spread all over.
Let cool for 1 hour, then frost.

title: barbecued rice
directions: Cook celery, onion and broth.
Add soup, liquid smoke, salt and pepper.
Mix melted margarine with rice and add to mixture. Pour mixture into casserole.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes, uncovered.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hash
directions: Brown together hamburger, diced onion and oil.
Add chili powder, salt, pepper, chicken broth, tomatoes and corn.
Bring this to a boil and stir in rice.
Simmer for 5 minutes or until rice is cooked.
Serve with salad and garlic bread for a complete meal.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Blend sugar, salt, dry mustard and cider vinegar.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Makes a shaker full.

title: pan chicken and dressing
directions: Mix package of seasoned bread stuffing with 1 stick of melted butter and 1 cup of water.	Put 1/2 of mixture in greased 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Mix together diced cooked chicken, onions, chopped green onion tops, chopped celery, mayonnaise, and salt. Pour over the dressing in casserole. Top with remaining stuffing mixture. Spread well.
Mix together eggs and milk. Then pour over casserole. Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
One hour before baking remove from refrigerator.
Add 1 can cream of mushroom soup mix with 1 can of water.
Spread over top.
Bake uncovered on 325° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and bake additional 10 minutes.
Serves 10-12.

title: green chili
directions: Boil meat with garlic until tender (can cook in pressure cooker until tender).
Cool and cut or shred meat in small pieces.

title: diet quiche
directions: Cook spinach; drain.
Mix eggs, cottage cheese and seasonings. Blend in spinach and put in Pam-sprayed pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sweet-sour beef vegetables for slow cooker
directions: Brown meat in hot oil in skillet.
Place in cooker; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cook 6 to 7 hours on low or 4 hours on high.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix water, sugar, cornstarch and a few of the berries together and heat until thickened.
Pour in remaining berries and pour into baked pie shell.
Let it set for a few hours.
Serve cold with whipped cream.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill before serving.

title: potato sausage chowder
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until tender, but not browned.
Add the chicken broth, salt, pepper and potato.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until the potato is tender, about 10 minutes.
Add milk, cream, parsley and cheese. Heat just until cheese begins to melt.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: In large bowl, sift sugar and flour.
In a saucepan, bring to boil margarine, cocoa and water.
Pour margarine mixture into flour and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients into bowl.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch sheet pan.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saute chopped vegetables in margarine.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Combine egg yolks, sugar and nuts.
Add dry ingredients and milk.
Beat egg whites and fold into mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake in loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: lemonade concentrate
directions: Put sugar and lemon rinds in a large bowl and cover with boiling water (enough to cover lemon rinds).
Add lemon juice and tartaric acid.
Let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Strain and bottle.
Dilute with cold water to taste.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat together cream cheese, sour cream and pineapple juice. Mix in marshmallow cream and fold in Cool Whip.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: orange carrots
directions: Wash and peel, scrub or scrape carrots.
Slice crosswise into rounds or lengthwise into sticks.
Bring water and salt to a boil in saucepan.
Add carrots and cover pan.
Cook over medium heat for 10 to 20 minutes, until tender.
Drain well.
Meanwhile, grate 1/2 teaspoon peel from orange.
Peel orange and cut into bite size pieces. Add orange pieces and peel, margarine and syrup to drained carrots.
Place over low heat and stir gently until margarine is melted and orange are heated.
Serve at once.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole combine soup with milk, mixing until smooth.
Add tuna, peas and olives, mixing well.
Top with corn chips.
Bake uncovered 25 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat; mix in soup and green beans.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake until golden brown at 350°.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat oil and sugar together.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Mix sugar, milk and cream cheese together; add Cool Whip.
Mix until blended.
Break cake into small bite size pieces.
Add to cream cheese and Cool Whip mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Evenly spread cherries over top.
Refrigerate 2 to 4 hours.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Set aside 1/4 cup jello. Add pineapple and congeal.
Cream sugar and cream cheese.
Add vanilla and Cool Whip.
Mix with the 1/4 cup jello mixture. Spread on jello.
Sprinkle with nuts if desired.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: In the cooked beef, mix hominy, mushroom soup and chili with beans.
Add grated cheese, as much as you like.
Top with Fritos chips.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: zucchini stuffing casserole
directions: Boil the zucchini until tender and drain. In saucepan, cook onion and carrot in 4 tablespoons butter until tender.
Remove from heat. Stir in stuffing cubes, soup and sour cream.
Gently stir in zucchini and place into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Melt remaining butter and add remaining stuffing cubes.
Toss.
Top casserole and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Set jello and chill to "soft set".
Grind all fruit and add to jello.
Add sweetener to taste.
Makes 8 servings.
Weight Watchers: 8 calories, 1 fat.

title: better than sex cake(first prize)
directions: Bake a German chocolate cake in an oblong pan.
Poke holes in it with a fork as soon as it comes from the oven.
Pour one jar of caramel ice cream topping over the cake, then pour one can of Eagle Brand milk over the caramel topping.
Refrigerate right away until the next day.
In the morning, spread Cool Whip over the top and add broken pieces of a Heath candy bar over all.

title: cocktail biscuits
directions: Sift flour with salt.
Cut in cheese and margarine.
Add milk. Roll as for pastry.
Cut tiny rounds.
Spread deviled ham between 2 rounds.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: the best chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a bowl mix together the flour, baking soda and salt.
In a large bowl, beat butter, sugars and vanilla until creamy.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Gradually add dry mixture, stirring well.
Add chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: strawberry-banana split cake
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and 1/2 cup melted margarine; press into 8 x 12-inch pan.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook until begins to thicken.

title: quiche
directions: Prick pie shell with fork and bake 5 minutes at 450° (afterwards pie at 350°).

title: snowy spiced nuts
directions: Place butter in a glass pie plate and microwave on High 30 seconds, or until melted.
Add nuts and stir to coat evenly. Microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes, or until butter is absorbed and nuts are roasted, stirring midway through cooking.
Combine sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice in a bag.
Add nuts and shake to coat nuts.
Let cool on a plate.
Serve in a candy dish or bowl.
Yields 2 cups.

title: cranberry pineapple relish
directions: Cook cranberries and water until cranberries crack, then mash. Add jello and sugar.
Mix together and add pineapple and let set to jell.

title: less tomato sauce lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions, drain and set aside.
Brown ground beef with onion and green pepper until onion is transparent.
Drain off excess liquid.
Add pepper.
Heat thoroughly.

title: continental zucchini
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet.
Saute zucchini and garlic for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add pimiento, corn, salt (if desired) and lemon pepper; cook and stir for 2 to 3 minutes or until zucchini is tender.
Sprinkle with cheese and heat until cheese melts.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: chewy date cookies
directions: Cook dates, 1/4 cup sugar and water until thick.
Cool.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Cream oleo, white sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix all together and beat well.
Add nuts.
Drop on a greased cookie sheet pan and bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.
Before baking, brush tops of cookies with beaten egg.

title: apple roly-poly
directions: Prepare biscuit mix as directed on package.
Roll dough on lightly floured board, about 10 x 12-inches.
Spread honey to within 1 inch of edge of dough.
Combine spices and sugar; toss with apples.
Spread apples and spices evenly over dough.
Roll like a jelly roll.
Bake in a greased pan with sides at 350° for 40 minutes.
Slice and serve warm with whipped cream or hot vanilla sauce.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Cook on high 8 to 10 hours.
Stir about every hour.
Cook last 1/2 hour, uncovered.
This is for a 3-quart pot.
Can be doubled for a larger pot.

title: cheese ball
directions: Put aside 5 slices of meat to wrap cheese ball.
Mix together all ingredients, place in middle of the four slices, place last slice on top of ball and wrap edges around ball.
Place upside down on plate.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix mayo, sugar, cream and vinegar together.
This makes more dressing than you will use.
I use milk in place of cream; it just isn't quite as creamy.
You can mix the dressing with the salad or let your guests use as much as they like.

title: lazy day stew
directions: Place raw beef in single layer in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Add vegetables.
Sprinkle tapioca, salt and pepper over the top.
Mix tomato sauce and water and pour over.
Crumble brown sugar on top. Do not mix ingredients.
Cover; do not peek.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours.
Can also be made in slow cooker.

title: cookies
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil for one minute; add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Drop by tablespoon on waxed paper.

title: baked beans
directions: In small skillet fry bacon until crisp.
Remove from grease and add onion; fry until golden brown.
Break bacon into pieces and remove onion to drain on paper towel.
Put beans in colander and run water over to remove sauce.
Put beans and all other ingredients in casserole dish and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
